      "church_affiliations": "No documented Reformed Church baptism for Wolphert nor any of his children (Kouwenhoven 1997 fn 51 cp_sou_043) — likely not Gereformeerd by birth. The 1605-01-17 Amersfoort Reformed marriage entry attributed to him by L.P. de Boer (1912) is REJECTED — refers to a different Wolfert Gerritse + Aeltgen Jansdochter (see feedback_1605_amersfoort_entry_different_couple.md). Marriage to Neeltgen Jacobsdr likely solemnized before 1611-12-15 but church record not located. Civic-rank marker: 1657-04-18 admitted to Small Burgher right of New Amsterdam (CNYHS 1885:24, cp_sou_042) — the Small Burgher right was a civic privilege, not a church affiliation, but membership in the Reformed Church was the social default for residents of New Amsterdam at this date.",
