      "children_summary": "Four children with Aeltje Cornelis Cool: Willem Gerritsz (cp_fam_007; WikiTree Couwenhoven-4, b. 1636 Flatlands); Jan Gerretse (cp_fam_008; WikiTree Van_Couwenhoven-39, abt.1639-abt.1724); Neeltje Gerrits Schenck (cp_fam_009; WikiTree Van_Couwenhoven-29, 1641-abt.1672); Marretje Gerretse Van Voorhees (cp_fam_010; bp. 1644-04-10 RDC Manhattan, d. 1702-1709).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "WikiTree: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Wolphertsen-1 (via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24) | Geni mirror (not authoritative): https://www.geni.com/people/Gerret-Wolfersen-van-Cowenhoven/6000000001713422869 | Cocheu, NYG&BR 70:3 (July 1939), pp. 230-235 (cp_sou_042) | Kouwenhoven NYG&BR 129:2 (Apr 1998), pp. 109-120 (cp_sou_045) — Table 2 confirms birth ca. 1610 + 3-son family list | Cocheu NYG&BR 70:4 (Oct 1939), pp. 353-356 (cp_sou_046)",
      "notes": "Eldest of the three sons who emigrated with Wolphert + Neeltje in April 1625 (age ca. 15 at arrival). A 'Jan Wolfertsen' appearing as a 4th son on Wolphert's WikiTree profile is likely a confusion with this Gerrit's son Jan Gerretse (Van_Couwenhoven-39) — per Chris 2026-04-24 that Jan is a grandson of Wolphert, not a son. FOLLOW-UP: verify full children list; confirm exact death date. | 2026-04-24 UPDATE: Gerrit's wife (cp_fam_006) and 4 children (cp_fam_007-010) added in this session. LINE-CLOSURE NOTE: Willem Gerritsz Couwenhoven (cp_fam_007) is the progenitor of the \"Willem-Gerritsz line\" from which project enslavers cp_ens_002 (Albert Willemse, Van_Couwenhoven-69), cp_ens_003 (Cornelius Albertse, Couwenhoven-16), and cp_ens_004 (Cornelis Willemse, Couwenhove-2) descend — this is the first direct kinship link between the immigrant patriarch (cp_fam_001) and our documented enslaver records.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **Gerret** = paternal grandfather's name (Wolphert's father, ca. 1590 undocumented tenant of Couwenhoven Hoogland). Eldest-son patrilineal-grandfather pattern.\n- Daughters' names from his wife's side: Neeltje (cp_fam_009 — but ALSO matches his mother Neeltgen Jacobsdr name); Marretje (cp_fam_010, name origin unclear).\n- Sons named for: Willem (cp_fam_007, after Wolphert's brother — patrilineal-uncle); Jan (cp_fam_008, common Dutch given name).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- ca. 1610 b. Amersfoort, Utrecht, NL\n- 1625 emigrated NA with parents at age ~15 (one of three sons; Cocheu 70.3 says only 3 sons interested in either parent's estate)\n- 1625–1638 Manhattan (with parents at Bouwerie 3, then Bouwerie 6)\n- 1635 m. Aeltje Cornelis Cool (cp_fam_006) at Flatlands (some sources say Oyster Bay; Cocheu 70.4)\n- 1638-07-26 (per KCo 78) father purchased Flatlands land; Gerret settled there\n- 1641-09-20 dau. Neeltje cp_fam_009 bp. New Amsterdam BDC 12\n- 1644-04-10 dau. Marretje cp_fam_010 bp. New Amsterdam BDC 17\n- 1644 magistrate at Flatlands (KCo 77)\n- d. abt. 1645 (between 1644-04-10 dau. Marretje's bp. and 1645-08-27 widow Aeltje's remarriage to Stoothoff per MDC 13)\n\n## Civic offices\n- 1644 magistrate at Flatlands (KCo 77 cp_sou_046)\n- (Cocheu 70.4 notes the 1647 Stiles attribution of Gerret to the founding of Breuckelen on Fulton St — but this contradicts the established 1645 death window; flag as historiographical error or different person.)\n\n## Kin network\n- Wife **Aeltje Cornelis Cool** cp_fam_006, dau. of Cornelis Lambertse Cool of Gowanus. After Gerret's death 1645, Aeltje m.(2) 1645-08-27 Capt. Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff cp_fam_025 (emigrated 1637 from Nieukerken; settled Flatlands; m.(2 widow) 1663-07-21 Sara Roelofse).\n- 4 children with Aeltje: Willem cp_fam_007, Jan cp_fam_008, Neeltje cp_fam_009, Marretje cp_fam_010.\n- Brothers cp_fam_004 Jacob, cp_fam_005 Pieter — joint heirs to Wolphert + Neeltgen's estate (per 1656 lawsuit + 1658 still-undivided estate per CDM 177; RNA 2:425).\n- Predeceased both parents; his estate referenced in 1656-12-06 Pieter v. Jacob lawsuit (cp_sou_042).\n\n## RETROFIT NOTE (5/9 evening)\n## sub-sections added from cp_sou_042 + cp_sou_046. | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_025 1646 Gerrit estate settlement): PRIMARY source for his estate settlement at Fort Amsterdam in 1646. Confirms death window between 1644-04-10 (daughter Marretje baptism) and the 1646 settlement. Widow cp_fam_006 Aeltje Cornelis Cool had remarried cp_fam_025 Elbert Elbertsen Stoothoff by 1646. Surviving children's 1646 ages primary-attested: cp_fam_007 Willem 10, cp_fam_008 Jan 7, cp_fam_009 Neeltjen 5, cp_fam_010 Marrtijen 2.5. Joint guardians: father cp_fam_001 Wolphert + brothers cp_fam_004 Jacob + cp_fam_005 Pieter. Stepfather cp_fam_025 Elbert obligated to bring up children + educate them + pay paternal-property guilder inheritances at majority/marriage. | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_lan_064 1647 Gowanus Land Patent): POSTHUMOUS patent of March 11, 1647 by Director Willem Kieft formalized his ~40-acre (19 morgens 341 rods) farm at Rechkeweck / Gowanus marsh, between the lands of Jacob Stoffelsen + Frederik Lubbertsen, near Andries Hudde's land. Earliest documented Cowenhoven LAND record in workbook. Effective title successor per cp_famsou_025 1646 settlement = cp_fam_025 Elbert Elbertsen Stoothoff (widow's 2nd husband). NYSA Series A1880, doc NYSA_A1880-78_VGG_0172.",
