      "children_summary": "At least two children: Neeltje Jacobse Wolphertz (bp. 1639-09-25); Johannes Jacobs \"Johanes\" Van Cowenhoven (cp_fam_012; b. ca. 1641; WikiTree Kouwenhoven-31) — canonical per Cocheu, \"The Couenhovens and Kinsfolk\" (FamilySearch item 284005), which traces descent through \"Jacob Wolphertsen van Couwenhoven and his first wife Hester Jansen\". Likely also Petronel Jacobs Van Vleck (whose row is listed on cp_fam_004 Jacob's WikiTree children list).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu, Lincoln C., \"The Couenhovens and Kinsfolk: Some descendants of Wolphert Gerritse van Kouwenhoven and Neeltje Janse through their son Jacob Wolphertsen van Couwenhoven and his first wife Hester Jansen\" — FamilySearch item 284005: https://www.familysearch.org/library/books/records/item/284005-the-couenhovens-and-kinsfolk | Internet Archive full text: https://archive.org/stream/couenhovenskinsf00coch/couenhovenskinsf00coch_djvu.txt | Jacob Wolphertse WikiTree profile (Van_Couwenhoven-38) — notes first wife Hester Jansen | Cocheu NYG&BR 70:4 (Oct 1939), pp. 353-356 (cp_sou_046)",
      "notes": "First wife of Jacob (cp_fam_004). No standalone WikiTree profile identified via WebSearch (2026-04-24) — she appears on Jacob's profile only. Sister of Ariaentje Jans, who was married to Govert Loockermans, the influential New Amsterdam merchant — this is a significant social-network tie. Also noted: Johanes (cp_fam_012) is confirmed as her son via Cocheu's published genealogy title (mother-link approved by Chris 2026-04-24). FOLLOW-UP: check whether a Jansen-series WikiTree profile exists; pull Neeltje Jacobse Wolphertz (bp. 1639-09-25) into FAMILY if warranted; map the Loockermans-Couwenhoven social tie for enslaver-network context.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- Brings **Hester** (her own name) — recurs heavily: dau. cp_fam_079 Hester Jansen, descendant Hester Risley nee cp_fam_090.\n- Brings 'Lijsbet' from her mother Lijsbet Setten — recurs as dau. cp_fam_063 Lysbeth Jacobs.\n- Brings 'Pieter' / 'Petronel' from her father Jan side or Setten lineage — recurs as dau. cp_fam_065 Petronel.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- ca. 1612 b. Haarlem (per Cocheu 71:1 MDC 30 / Kouwenhoven 1997)\n- by 1637 resided Princes' Canal Amsterdam with mother Lijsbet Setten\n- 1637-11-14 banns / 1637-12-01 m. Jacob Wolphertse Couwenhoven, Nieuwe Kerk Amsterdam\n- post-1637 emigrated NA with Jacob; resided NY City Pearl St\n- d. after 1653-04-20 (date of her will, Min. Orphans Court 1:12)\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n\n## Kin network\n- Mother **Lijsbet Setten** of Princes' Canal Amsterdam (alive 1637; not minted)\n- Father unknown but patronymic Jansen = daughter of Jan; her uncle (mother's brother?) **Rutgert Jansz** assisted at her 1637 wedding (could be Rutger Jansz of Ceulhorst or of Nederseldert Hoogland per Kouwenhoven 1998 cp_sou_045 — relation possibly through Wolphert's family rather than Hester's, since Hester was from Haarlem not Hoogland).\n- Husband cp_fam_004 Jacob Wolphertse Couwenhoven\n- 6 children all bp. RDC NY (cp_fam_062, cp_fam_012, cp_fam_063, cp_fam_064, son d. infant 1647, cp_fam_065)\n\n## RETROFIT NOTE (5/9 evening)\n## sub-sections from cp_sou_046 + cp_sou_043 + cp_sou_047.",
