      "spouse_text": "1st: Hester Jansen (cp_fam_011; m. 1637-12-01 Amsterdam, d. aft.1653-04-20); 2nd: Magdaleentje Jacobuse Bysen (m. abt. 1655-09-26)",
      "children_summary": "Children named on WikiTree profile: Neeltje (Couwenhoven) Van Couwenhoven; Johannes Jacobs (Kouwenhoven) Van Couwenhoven = cp_fam_012 Johanes (WikiTree Kouwenhoven-31); Petronel Jacobs (van Couwenhoven) Van Vleck. | Three additional children per Cocheu 70:4 (cp_sou_046) citing a family-Bible record + BDC: Lysbeth (b. 1643-08-30 / bp. 1643-09-06 BDC 15; m. Samuel Gerretzsen); Aeltje (b. 1645-08-20 / bp. 1645-08-27 BDC 19; m. 1669-07-07 Bernardus Hassen MDC 34); infant son (b. 1647-03-06 / d. 1647-03-07).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "WikiTree: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Van_Couwenhoven-38 (via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24) | Kouwenhoven NYG&BR 128:4 (Oct 1997), pp. 209-218 (cp_sou_043) — Amsterdam 1637 marriage record + birth-year correction to 1615 | Cocheu NYG&BR 70:4 (Oct 1939), pp. 353-356 (cp_sou_046)",
      "notes": "Middle of the three emigrant sons (age ca. 10 at arrival April 1625). WikiTree profile explicitly names 'Johannes Jacobs (Kouwenhoven) Van Couwenhoven' as a child — this CONFIRMS the hypothesis on cp_fam_006 Johanes that Jacob-38 is his father (previously HYPOTHESIS on patronymic 'Jacobs'; now confirmed). Died intestate; administrators Johanes Van Brugh, Paulus Leendertson Van der Gruff, and Isaac Greveratt appointed by Court of Mayor and Aldermen on 1670-04-21. FOLLOW-UP: consult Court of Mayor and Aldermen minutes for the administration record; research enslaver_status — a New Amsterdam brewer/Pearl Street resident in the 1650s-60s plausibly engaged with enslaved labor; confirm first-marriage date to Hester Jansen. | KOUWENHOVEN 1997 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_043, NYG&BR 128:4 pp. 211-212): Per Amsterdam marriage-intentions register vol. 447 p. 34, banns dated 14 Nov 1637 read: 'Jacobus Couwenhoven of Amersfoort, residing in the Jonge Roelen Alley, 22 years old, assisted by his uncle Rutgert Jansz., parents still living, marries Hester Jans of Haarlem, 22 years old, living on the Princes' Canal with her mother Lijsbet Setten.' Jacob signed as 'Jacobus Couwehooven' — FIRST DOCUMENTED USE OF THE SURNAME 'Couwenhoven' in this branch. Jacob's age 22 at this 1637 marriage establishes birth ca. 1615 (correcting Cocheu 1939's 1612 by three years). Wedding performed 1 December 1637 by Dominee Gelldorpus in the Nieuwe Kerk, Amsterdam (DTB 990 p. 63 microfiche 7434; DTB 1013 entry 1 Dec 1637). Uncle Rutger Jansz's exact relationship to Wolfert/Neeltgen is unresolved; Kouwenhoven 1998 (cp_sou_045) pp. 115-117 explores two Hoogland candidates (one in Ceulhorst, one in Nederseldert) without confirming which one was at Jacob's wedding.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **Jacob** = maternal grandfather's name (Jacob Petersz, Neeltgen's father). Maternal-grandfather naming.\n- 1st wife Hester Jansen brings **Hester** into Cowenhoven name pool — recurs as daughter cp_fam (Cocheu 71.1 #56 Hester Pluvier via dau. Neeltje cp_fam_062), daughter cp_fam_079, granddaughter cp_fam_018 (Pieter-line) — Hester proliferation.\n- 2nd wife Magdalena Jacobs brings **Magdaleentje / Magdalena** — recurs in Jacob-branch.\n- Children: Neeltje (mother Neeltgen + grandmother), Jan (uncle cp_fam_008 + common), Lysbeth, Aeltje (in-law route), son d.young, Petronel.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- ca. 1615 b. Amersfoort, Utrecht, NL (per his 1637 Amsterdam marriage banns stating age 22)\n- 1625 emigrated NA with parents at age ~10\n- 1637-11-14 to 1637-12-01 in Amsterdam for marriage to Hester Jansen (resided Jonge Roelen Alley; signed as 'Jacobus Couwehooven' — first documented use of surname in this branch)\n- post-1637 NY City — High (Pearl) Street; carried on a brewery (VM 1856 cp_sou_046)\n- 1647, 1649, 1650 one of the Nine Men of New Netherland\n- 1655-09-26 m.(2) Magdalena Jacobs van Amsterdam (MDC 20)\n- 1656-08-19 bouwery at Gravesend ordered sold for debt (cp_sou_046)\n- 1664-09-24 Gov. Nicolls licensed him to trade with Albany Indians via sloop\n- 1665 living on Hoogh Straat (Pearl St)\n- 1666 member RDC NY\n- 1670-04-21 d. NY (Wills NYHS 1:12); buried old graveyard NA West side Broadway just above Morris St\n\n## Civic offices\n- One of the **Nine Men** of New Netherland 1647, 1649, 1650 (cp_sou_046)\n- Signer of the **Vertoogh** (1649 colonial petition to States General)\n- One of the **Great Burghers** (ICON 2:304-5 cp_sou_046)\n- **Captain of the Burghery** (Documents relating to the Hist. of the State of N. Y. I:397 cp_sou_046)\n- 1664-09-24 Albany trading licensee (Gov. Nicolls)\n\n## Kin network\n- 1st wife **Hester Jansen** of Haarlem (cp_fam_011) — bp. ca. 1612; lived on Princes' Canal Amsterdam in 1637 with mother **Lijsbet Setten** (not minted); uncle **Rutgert Jansz** assisted at Amsterdam wedding (per Kouwenhoven 1998 cp_sou_045 may be Rutger Jansz of Ceulhorst near Amersfoort, or Rutger Jansz of Nederseldert — Hoogland-area uncle, relationship to cp_fam_001 OR cp_fam_002 unclear).\n- 2nd wife **Magdalena Jacobs van Amsterdam** (m. 1655-09-26 MDC 20; later m.(2 widow) banns 1675-05-30 / m. 1675-06-20 Henricus Van Dyck widower of Dievertje Corn., MDC 40).\n- 6 children with Hester: cp_fam_062 Neeltje (FIRST baptism on record in NY DRC), cp_fam_012 Jan/Johannes, cp_fam_063 Lysbeth, cp_fam_064 Aeltje, son #13 d. infant 1647-03-07 (not minted), cp_fam_065 Petronel.\n- Brothers cp_fam_003 Gerret + cp_fam_005 Pieter — joint estate heirs.\n- 1656-12-06 Pieter v. Jacob lawsuit: Pieter sought injunction against execution of judgment because Jacob's debts triggered guarantor liability for father Wolphert (CDM 177; RNA 2:425, cp_sou_042).\n\n## RETROFIT NOTE (5/9 evening)\n## sub-sections added from cp_sou_042 + cp_sou_046 + cp_sou_043. | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_025 1646 Gerrit estate settlement): named as \"Jacob Wolphersen, brother of the aforesaid Gerrit Wolphersen, deceased\" — joint guardian (first party) of deceased brother Gerrit's 4 children (cp_fam_007-010) alongside father cp_fam_001 Wolphert + brother cp_fam_005 Pieter. Signed the document as \"Jacob van Kouwenh[oven]\" (per signature list). Confirms his active role as Couwenhoven family elder by 1646 at age ~31.",
