      "notes": "First wife of immigrant-generation Gerrit (cp_fam_003); mother of all four Gerrit children currently on FAMILY. After Gerrit's death (aft.1647) she remarried Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff on 1645-08-27 in New Amsterdam — this creates a potentially relevant Stoothoff-Couwenhoven kinship bridge for future enslaver-network research. FOLLOW-UP: full Cool-29 profile pull (birth place, death date precision, Stoothoff children); clarify Gerrit death date vs. 1645 remarriage date (possible source conflict — marriage 1645 precedes \"aft.1647\" death window).\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- Brings **Cornelis** (her father Cornelis Lambertse Cool of Gowanus) into Cowenhoven name pool — recurs as grandson cp_ens_004 (Cornelis Willemse Couwenhoven b.1672).\n- Brings **Aeltje** — recurs as granddaughter cp_fam_067 (Altie Willemse) and as the half-illegitimate cp_fam_022 (named for either Aeltje Sibrants or Aeltgen Jacobs).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- ca. 1615 b. (place uncertain; Gowanus area implied by father)\n- abt. 1635 m.(1) Gerret Wolphertse cp_fam_003 at Flatlands or Oyster Bay\n- 1641-09-20 dau. Neeltje cp_fam_009 bp. NA\n- 1644-04-10 dau. Marretje cp_fam_010 bp. NA\n- 1645 widowed when Gerret d. abt. 1645\n- 1645-08-27 m.(2) Capt. Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff (cp_fam_025; emigrated 1637 from Nieukerken; settled Flatlands; MDC 13)\n- d. before 1683 (cp_sou_046)\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n\n## Kin network\n- Father **Cornelis Lambertse Cool of Gowanus** (not minted as cp_fam — Cool family lineage outside project scope)\n- 1st husband **Gerret Wolphertse** cp_fam_003 (d. abt. 1645)\n- 2nd husband **Capt. Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff** cp_fam_025 (emigrated 1637; m.(2 widow) 1663-07-21 Sara Roelofse, widow of Cornelius Van Bossum, AnN 86 + MDC 53)\n- 4 Cowenhoven children (cp_fam_007, _008, _009, _010); Stoothoff children not yet researched in this project\n\n## RETROFIT NOTE (5/9 evening)\n## sub-sections from cp_sou_046. | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_025 1646 Gerrit estate settlement): named as \"Aeltjen Cornelis, surviving widow of the late Gerrit Wolphersen\" — primary attestation that she had REMARRIED cp_fam_025 Elbert Elbertsen Stoothoff by 1646. The settlement designates her 2nd husband Elbert as guardian and possessor of all means + effects from cp_fam_003 Gerrit's estate, with obligations to bring up + educate the 4 children + pay them their paternal-property inheritances at majority/marriage. | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_lan_064 1647 Gowanus Land Patent): Inherited ~40-acre Gowanus farm via cp_famsou_025 1646 estate settlement; 2nd husband cp_fam_025 Elbert Elbertsen Stoothoff took possession + formalized title via the March 1647 Kieft patent. Aeltje's tenure on this Gowanus property continued through her 2nd marriage; she died 1683.",
