      "spouse_text": "1st: Aeltje Jorisen Brinckerhoff — m. 1660-03-21 Flatlands; 2nd: Jannetje Pieters Montfort — m. 1665-02-12 Flatlands | 1st wife Altje Joris Brinckerhoff was widow of Cornelis Mattys (Matthews) at marriage; she died 1663-06-03 (per Cocheu 71:1 cp_sou_047 citing Willem's family Bible, NJMis 2:353)",
      "children_summary": "Twelve children per Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) citing Willem's original family Bible record (NJMis 2:353).\nBy 1st marriage to Aeltje Joris Brinckerhoff (m. 1660, d. 1663-06-03):\n  19. Gerret = cp_fam_066, b. 1662-01-04, bp. 1662-01-15 (Brkn 146); m. Aeltie — (KCo 77).\nBy 2nd marriage to Jannetje Pieterse Monfoort (cp_fam_061; m. 1665-02-12):\n  20. Altie = cp_fam_067, b. 1665-12-14, d. abt. 1689; m. 1687-03-16 Cornelis Symonse Van Arsdalen.\n  21. Neeltje = cp_fam_068, b. 1669-02-07; m. 1692 John Pieterse Wyckoff.\n  22. Pieter = cp_fam_069, b. 1671-02-12, d. abt. Feb 1755; m. abt. 1694 Patience Daws.\n  23. Cornelis = cp_ens_004, b. 1672-11-20, d. 1736-05-16; m. 1700-09-03 Margarieta Schenck (cousin, cp_fam_009's #43).\n  24. Sara = cp_fam_071, b. 1674-12-20, d. 1761-01-31; m. 1692-10-01 Jan Roelofse Schenck (cousin, cp_fam_009's #41).\n  25. Albert = cp_ens_002, b. 1676-12-07, d. 1748-09-13; m. 1701-10-02 Neeltje Schenck (cousin, cp_fam_009's #44).\n  26. Jacob = cp_ens_009, b. 1679-01-29, bp. 1679-02-02 (Flat 111); m. 1705-11-12 Sarah Schenck (cousin, cp_fam_009's #46).\n  27. Jan = cp_fam_057 (existing John Willemse Couwenhoven), b. 1681-04-09, bp. 1681-04-11 (Flat 120); m. abt. 1704 Coba Vanderveer.\n  28. Annetje = cp_fam_074, b. 1683-04-13, bp. 1683-04-22 (Flat 128); m.(1 sup.) 1704-11-11 Aert Willemse; m.(2 sup.) Johannes Antonides.\n  29. William = cp_fam_054 (existing Willem Willemse Kowenhoven), b. 1686-03-07, d. 1769-01-19; m. 1709-06-05 Annetie Lucasse Van Voorhees.\n  30. Jacomina = cp_fam_075, b. 1689-12-28; m. 1709-06-05 Elbert Willemsen.\nBergen (KCo 80) suggests possible 13th child Joris — Cocheu places him as #92 (next gen).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "WikiTree: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Couwenhoven-4 (via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24) | WikiTree descendants page: https://www.wikitree.com/genealogy/Couwenhoven-Descendants-4 | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047)",
      "notes": "LINE-CLOSURE: progenitor of the \"Willem-Gerritsz line\" from which our project enslavers cp_ens_002 (Albert Willemse, Van_Couwenhoven-69), cp_ens_003 (Cornelius Albertse, Couwenhoven-16), and cp_ens_004 (Cornelis Willemse, Couwenhove-2) descend. This row is the first link between the immigrant patriarch cp_fam_001 and the documented enslaver records in the project dataset. DATA-QUALITY FLAG: the Couwenhoven-4 WebSearch snippet oddly reports a \"twin brother Willem Gerret\" with the same given name — almost certainly a WikiTree data-entry issue, not an actual twin. FOLLOW-UP: verify directly from the profile page; build the descendants chain linking Couwenhoven-4 → cp_ens_002-004 (intermediate generations); consult Couwenhoven-Descendants-4 for the chain; determine enslaver_status for Willem himself. STEP-FATHER: Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff (cp_fam_025) via mother Aeltje Cool's 1645-08-27 remarriage after father Gerrit's death; step-relations documented in notes per project convention, not in related_family.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- 1st wife Aeltje Brinckerhoff brings Joris (her father Joris Dircksen) into in-law network; Cocheu/Bergen note Joris is curiously absent from Willem's children's first names.\n- 2nd wife Jannetje Monfoort brings Pieter (her father) — recurs as son cp_fam_069.\n- Children's names: Gerret (patrilineal), Cornelis (maternal Cornelis Lambertse Cool), Pieter, Albert (in-law), Jan (uncle cp_fam_008), Jacob (uncle cp_fam_004), Sara, Annetje, William (Wolphert's brother, recurring 4-gen patrilineal), Neeltje, Altie, Jacomina.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1636 b. Flatlands or Brooklyn vicinity (father's land purchases 1638 Flatlands, 1647 Brooklyn)\n- 1660-1666 Brooklyn (magistrate 1661/62/64)\n- 1667+ Flatlands (on patent 1667; Elder DRC 1677; assessment rolls 1675/83/93)\n- 1709-11-01 sold Flatlands farm to son William\n- last years Monmouth Co., NJ; member Brick Church Marlborough by 1721\n\n## Civic offices\n- Magistrate Brooklyn 1661, 1662, 1664 (KCo 80; Stiles I:143)\n- Schepen Brooklyn 1662-05-25 petition signer\n- Deacon DRC Brooklyn 1663\n- Signer Flatlands patent 1667\n- Elder DRC Flatlands 1677\n- Assessment rolls Flatlands 1675, 1683, 1693\n- Oath of allegiance 1687-09-26/30 (DHNY 1:661)\n\n## Kin network\n- One of three heirs to Brooklyn grant of father-in-law Joris Dircksen Brinckerhoff (sold 1661-01-16, KCo 49)\n- 4 children married Schenck cousins (children of cp_fam_009 + Roelof Martense Schenck): #23, #24, #25, #26 = cp_ens_004/071/072/073 — significant intra-family cousin density.\n\n## COCHEU 71:1 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_047)\nDeath window narrowed via Brick Church Marlborough membership rolls (1721 with wife → 1723 wife alone). 1st wife Altje Brinckerhoff's death 1663-06-03 + Cornelis Mattys widowhood per Cocheu citing Bible record (NJMis 2:353). 12-children directory above sourced to NJMis 2:353 + Brkn + Flat + KCo 77. | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_025 1646 Gerrit estate settlement): named as \"Willem Gerritsz, at present ten years of age\" in 1646 — confirms birth year ca. 1636. Eldest surviving child of cp_fam_003 Gerrit + cp_fam_006 Aeltje. Inheritance: 200 guilders, payable in cash by stepfather cp_fam_025 Elbert Elbertsen at majority or marriage.",
