      "spouse_text": "Gerardina (Gerdientje / Godardina) de Sille (cp_fam_030; dau. of Nicasius de Sille De_Sille-11 + Cornelia Meulmans; b. 1642-02-10 Amsterdam, d. aft. 1681) — m. 1670-05-18/19 New York",
      "children_summary": "Six children per Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047). By Gerardina de Sille (cp_fam_030):\n  31. Gerret = cp_fam_026 (existing Gerret Janse Van Couwenhoven), b. abt. 1676, d. 1712; m.(1) Lysbet —, m.(2) Aeltje.\n  32. Aeltje = cp_fam_076, bp. 1678-04-28 Flatbush (Flat 108), d. 1740-03-09 (AnN 297); m. 1700 Derick Abramse Brinckerhoff (his 1st wife).\n  33. Nicasius = cp_fam_027 (existing Nicasius Janse Van Couwenhoven), b. 1681-06-30, bp. 1681-07-08 Flatbush (Flat 120), d. 1749-09-16; m. 1703-11-03 Elsie —.\n  34. Cornelia = cp_fam_077; m. 1691-09-25 at Flatbush, Gerret Aertsen Middagh (Flat 94).\n  35. Neeltje = cp_fam_078; m. 1694-07-27 Joris Rapelye.\n  36. Williamtje (supposed; CANDIDATE only) — m. 1685-02-08 Hendrick Emans of NJ (KCo 79). Cocheu flags as 'supposed to belong here'; not minted.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "WikiTree: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Van_Couwenhoven-39 (via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24); NY Surrogate's Office Liber 8 p.275 — will of son Gerret Janse Van Couwenhoven, dated 1711-04-06, proved 1712-11-03 (names 'John Gerittse Van Cowenhoven' as father) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047)",
      "notes": "Second-born child of Gerrit and Aeltje per birth-order (abt. 1639). NOTE: the 'Jan Wolfertsen' appearing as a putative 4th son on Wolphert's (cp_fam_001) WikiTree profile is almost certainly a confusion with THIS Jan Gerretse (a grandson of Wolphert, not a son) — see cp_fam_001 notes. FOLLOW-UP: full profile pull (spouse, children, marriage, occupation, residence). STEP-FATHER: Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff (cp_fam_025) via mother Aeltje Cool's 1645-08-27 remarriage after father Gerrit's death; step-relations documented in notes per project convention, not in related_family.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **HIS MARRIAGE INTRODUCES NICASIUS / NICHOLAS INTO THE COWENHOVEN ONOMASTIC POOL** via wife Gerardina de Sille's father Nicasius de Sille of New Utrecht. Son cp_fam_027 carries the name; this is the entry point for any later 'Nicholas Cowenhoven' in the Jan-Gerretse sub-branch.\n- Children's names: Gerret (patrilineal), Aeltje (cp_fam_006 grandmother), Nicasius (De Sille), Cornelia (De Sille mother Cornelia Meulmans), Neeltje, Williamtje (Wolphert's brother, supposed).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- abt. 1639 b. Flatlands\n- 1665 trading at Albany\n- 1670+ Brooklyn Ferry residence (member DRC Brooklyn 1677, 1685)\n- 1690 commissioner of Brooklyn (Court of General Sessions)\n- abt. 1724 d.\n\n## Civic offices\n- 1665 licensed to trade in Albany (KCo 78)\n- 1690 commissioner of Brooklyn (Court of General Sessions); same year grand juryman\n\n## Kin network\n- Allowed more from father's estate than his brother because he was lame (KCo 78) — inheritance-adjustment kin signal.\n- Wife Gerardina's father Nicasius de Sille (Schout-fiscal of New Netherland; resided New Utrecht LI; high social rank).\n\n## COCHEU 71:1 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_047)\nSix-children directory sourced to KCo 78, Flat 108, Flat 120, AnN 297, Flat 94. Williamtje #36 flagged as Bergen's CANDIDATE — not minted. | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_025 1646 Gerrit estate settlement): named as \"Jan Gerritsen, aged seven years\" in 1646 — confirms birth year ca. 1639. **UNIQUE HEALTH/DISABILITY DETAIL: \"not possessed of as good health as the other, and is weak in his limbs and to all appearances will not be a strong man.\" Despite the 1646 prediction, workbook records his death abt. 1724 — he lived to ~85, contrary to the settlement's expectation.** Differential inheritance: 300 Carolus guilders (= 200 standard + 100 extra to compensate for disability), payable in cash by stepfather cp_fam_025 Elbert at majority or marriage. Earliest documented Cowenhoven disability/health datapoint.",
