      "spouse_text": "Roelof Martense Schenck (CORRECTED 5/9 — workbook prior 'Jan Martense Schenck — pending' was wrong) — b. abt. 1630, son of Marten Schenck; emigrated NA 1650; d. 1705 Flatlands; will dated 1704-09-04, pro. 1705-07-26 NY Co. (WNYHS 1:408). Schenck m.(2) abt. 1675 Annetje Pieterse Wyckoff (dau. of Pieter Claesen Wyckoff, bp. 1650-11-27, d. 1688-11-09); m.(3) 1688-11-30 Catryntyna Crigers (Cregier), widow of Christoffle Hooglandt.",
      "children_summary": "Six children with Roelof Martense Schenck per Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) citing KCo 254, Anc. and Desc. of Rulef Schenck p. 61, Van Voorhees Family p. 379. (Schenck children: NOT minted as cp_fam rows per project policy — non-Cowenhoven surname.)\n  37. Martin Schenck, b. 1661-01 or 1661-06-22, d. 1721-05-02 or 1727; m.(1) 1686-06-20 Susanna Abramse Brinkerhoff (d.1690), m.(2) 1693-04-11 Elizabeth Minne Voorhees (d.1703), m.(3) 1704-02-25 or 1704-06-24 Jannetje Lucase Voorhees (b.1681-10-08, d.1758-04-17).\n  38. Annetje Schenck, b. abt. 1663, d. 1685-10; m. 1684-06-10 Jan Albertse Terhune.\n  39. Jonica/Jannetje Schenck, b. 1665; m. 1684-06-07 Peter Nevius.\n  40. Marike Schenck, b. 1667-02-14; m. 1687-02-15 Isaac Hegeman.\n  41. Jan Roelofse Schenck, b. 1670-03-01, d. 1753-01-30; m. Flatlands 1692-10-01 his cousin Sara Willemse Cowenhoven (= cp_fam_007's #24 = cp_fam_071).\n  42. Gerret Roelofse Schenck, b. 1671-10-27, d. 1745-09-05; m. Flatlands abt. 1693 his cousin Neeltje Coertse Van Voorhees (cp_fam_010's #51).\nBy Schenck's 2nd marriage to Annetje Wyckoff: 43. Margaretta (m. cousin Cornelis Willemse Cowenhoven = cp_fam_007's #23 = cp_ens_004); 44. Neeltje (m. cousin Albert Willemse Cowenhoven = cp_fam_007's #25 = cp_ens_002); 45. Mayke; 46. Sara (m. cousin Jacob Willemse Cowenhoven = cp_fam_007's #26 = cp_ens_009). [Schenck 2nd-marriage children noted for cousin-marriage tracking only.]",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "WikiTree: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Van_Couwenhoven-29 (via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 81:2 (Apr 1950), pp. 123-125 (cp_sou_051)",
      "notes": "Third-born child of Gerrit and Aeltje (1641). Married into the Schenck family — another prominent New Netherland Dutch lineage. Short life (d. abt. 1672, age ~31). FOLLOW-UP: verify spouse name/marriage date from direct WikiTree profile; map the Schenck-Couwenhoven intermarriage for enslaver-network research. STEP-FATHER: Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff (cp_fam_025) via mother Aeltje Cool's 1645-08-27 remarriage after father Gerrit's death; step-relations documented in notes per project convention, not in related_family.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **HER MARRIAGE INTRODUCES ROELOF INTO THE COWENHOVEN COUSIN POOL** via husband Roelof Martense Schenck. Roelof recurs in Schenck-side cousins.\n- Schenck's later wives bring Wyckoff (m.2 Annetje Pieterse Wyckoff) and Crigers (m.3 Catryntyna Crigers) into the Schenck network — those don't propagate to Neeltje's own children but DO produce Schenck cousins (Margaretta, Neeltje, Sara) who later married back into Cowenhoven (cp_fam_007's children #23, #25, #26).\n- Children's first names: Martin (Schenck patriarch), Jan / Gerret (Cowenhoven patrilineal), Annetje / Jannetje / Sara / Margaretta (in-law / cousin-marriage routes), Marike, Mayke, Neeltje (Cowenhoven maternal).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1641-09-20 bp. New Amsterdam (BDC 12)\n- 1660 m. Flatlands\n- abt. 1672 d. Flatlands\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none — wife who died young)\n- Husband Roelof Schenck: magistrate Flatlands 1662-1664; rep Hempstead convention 1665; sheriff of county 1685; JP 1684/89/92; captain of horse 1690.\n\n## Kin network\n- Husband Roelof Schenck obtained 23-morgen patent at Flatlands 1661-01-29; bought 200 acres in Amersfort 1674-03-19 from heirs of Gerret Loockermans; bought 1/2 of a mill + island 1688-04-20 from a brother (KCo 253-4; CEM 28, 132, 185, 192, 225).\n- After Neeltje's death, Schenck remarried into Wyckoff (Annetje Pieterse).\n- 4 children of Roelof's lines (Jan #41, Gerret #42, Margaretta #43, Neeltje #44, Sara #46) married back into Cowenhoven cousins (cp_fam_007's children + cp_fam_010's daughter Neeltje #51).\n\n## COCHEU 71:1 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_047)\n**SPOUSE CORRECTION**: workbook prior 'Jan Martense Schenck — pending' is REPLACED by Roelof Martense Schenck per Cocheu 71:1 + KCo 78 + 253. Critical for branch resolution — any later attribution to a 'Jan-Martense-Schenck' line needs re-evaluation.\n\n## Cocheu 81:2 (cp_sou_051) — son #42 Gerrit Schenck added (omitted from 71:3 by Cocheu's own admission)\nCocheu 81:2 explicitly notes #42 Gerrit Schenck was 'omitted in its proper sequence (Rec. v.71, p.275) but is introduced at this point to show the involved family relationships.'\nGerrit Schenck #42 b. Flatlands LI 1671-10-27, d. 1745-09-05 (will dated 1739-01-02, pro. 1745-10-07 NJA 30:417). m. Flatlands ~1693 his cousin Neeltje Van Voorhees #51 (b. 1676-06-30, d. 1750-08-04, dau. of Coert Stevense Van Voorhees + cp_fam_010 Marretje).\n→ DOUBLE COWENHOVEN-GRANDMOTHER MARRIAGE: both Gerrit Schenck and his wife Neeltje Van Voorhees had Cowenhoven mothers.\n→ 12 children #226-237: 5 of 12 (#229 Koert, #233 Gerrit, #234 Margaret, #235 Jan, #236 Albert) married Cowenhoven cousins. Per Chris's 5/9 rule, only 4 of these 5 are minted (cp_fam_187-190); #229 Koert remains text-only on cp_fam_095's row.\n→ Chris's 5/9 footnote summary (Cocheu): 'Both Gerrit and his wife had Kouwenhoven mothers; a brother and three sisters of Gerrit married Kouwenhoven cousins and five of his 12 children married Kouwenhovens, four of whom were brothers and sisters.'\n  ('A brother and three sisters of Gerrit' = Jan Roelofse Schenck (m. cp_fam_071 Sara) + Margaretta (m. cp_ens_004 Cornelis) + Neeltje (m. cp_ens_002 Albert) + Sarah (m. cp_ens_009 Jacob) — 4 of cp_fam_009's children's marriages already in workbook from 71:2 retrofit.) | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_025 1646 Gerrit estate settlement): named as \"Neeltjen Gerrits, aged five years\" in 1646 — confirms birth year ca. 1641. Third surviving child of cp_fam_003 Gerrit + cp_fam_006 Aeltje. Inheritance: 200 Carolus guilders, payable in cash by stepfather cp_fam_025 Elbert Elbertsen at majority or marriage.",
