      "notes": "Pieter's acknowledged extramarital daughter with Maria du Trieux. The 1642 adoption document stipulated that if Pieter had no legitimate children, Aeltje would be his sole heir; if he did, she would receive an equal child's portion. She was raised by Pieter and his 1st wife Hester Simons (cp_fam_015). STUB — no standalone WikiTree profile identified 2026-04-24. All siblings listed as Sibling| are HALF-SIBLINGS (different mother); the Sibling vocabulary is used per project convention (feedback_enslaver_r_col_vocab.md) but the half-relation should be understood. DISAMBIGUATION: distinct from cp_fam_020 Aeltje Couwenhoven (legitimate daughter of Pieter by Hester Simons). FOLLOW-UP: locate a WikiTree profile; dates/places for her two marriages; children; whether she or her husbands appear in any Couwenhoven-project archival records.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **Aeltje** — common Dutch given name. Mother's natal family was du Trieux (Maria du Trieux cp_fam_021 = daughter of Philippe Antoni du Trieux); the surname 'du Trieux' was Aeltje's birth/maiden name despite being Pieter's natural daughter.\n- Married surnames: Cobes (1st husband), Ofmuller (2nd husband) per Cocheu 70:4 KCo 79 + TDC.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- before 1642-01-07 b. (date of court adoption document)\n- 1st m. Ludovicus Cobes (date unknown)\n- 2nd m. Dirk Ofmuller (date unknown)\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n\n## Kin network\n- Biological father cp_fam_005 Pieter Wolphertse (acknowledged via 1642-01-07 court document)\n- Biological mother cp_fam_021 Maria du Trieux (extramarital relationship)\n- Half-siblings via Pieter + Hester Symons: cp_fam_016/_017/_018/_019/_020\n- Half-sibling via Pieter + Aeltje Sibrants: cp_fam_024 Petrus #2 (Peter Peterse)\n- 1st husband Ludovicus Cobes\n- 2nd husband Dirk Ofmuller\n\n## RETROFIT NOTE (5/9 evening)\n## sub-sections from cp_sou_046. See project_cp_fam_022_natural_daughter.md for status of natural-daughter classification (biologically Pieter's blood, marital surname du Trieux).",
