      "notes": "Wife of cp_fam_008 Jan Gerretse Van Couwenhoven and mother of at least 6 named children (including cp_fam_026 Gerret and cp_fam_027 Nicasius already on FAMILY). Father Nicasius de Sille (De_Sille-11) was a prominent New Netherland figure (schout-fiscal of New Netherland under Stuyvesant, 1654); namesake of grandson cp_fam_027 Nicasius Van Couwenhoven. Mother Cornelia Meulmans was from Maastricht. Known sister: Anna de Sille (WikiTree De_Sille-21, 1640–aft.1711). No standalone WikiTree profile for Gerardina located 2026-04-24 — candidate for profile creation. FOLLOW-UP: consider future FAMILY rows for parents Nicasius de Sille and Cornelia Meulmans as in-law context (parallels cp_fam_021 Maria du Trieux).\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **SHE BRINGS NICASIUS / NICHOLAS INTO THE COWENHOVEN FAMILY** via her father Nicasius de Sille of New Utrecht. Son cp_fam_027 is direct namesake. See cp_fam_008 + reference_first_name_lineage_heuristic.md.\n- Mother Cornelia Meulmans (Maastricht-origin) brings 'Cornelia' — recurs as her own daughter cp_fam_077.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1642-02-10 b. Amsterdam, NL\n- emigrated NA at unknown date with parents Nicasius + Cornelia\n- 1670-05-18 m. NY (cp_fam_008 Jan Gerretse)\n- aft. 1681 d. (Cocheu 71:1 doesn't pin)\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n- Father Nicasius de Sille: high social rank, of New Utrecht LI.\n\n## Kin network\n- Sister-in-laws cp_fam_007 (Brinckerhoff/Monfoort), cp_fam_009 (Schenck), cp_fam_010 (Van Voorhees) — densely connected Gen-3 Cowenhoven women.\n\n## COCHEU 71:1 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_047)\nConfirms b. 1642-02-10 Amsterdam + father Nicasius de Sille of New Utrecht + mother Cornelia Meulmans (REC 34:26).",
