      "notes": "Youngest child of Gerrit and Aeltje. No standalone WikiTree profile ID found in WebSearch snippets as of 2026-04-24 — she is named on her siblings' WikiTree profiles but appears to lack her own managed profile. Married into the Van Voorhees family — another significant New Netherland Dutch lineage. FOLLOW-UP: locate or request a WikiTree profile for her; verify death date (FindAGrave says 1708, Geni says c.1709); map the Voorhees-Couwenhoven intermarriage for enslaver-network research. STEP-FATHER: Elbert Elbertse Stoothoff (cp_fam_025) via mother Aeltje Cool's 1645-08-27 remarriage after father Gerrit's death; step-relations documented in notes per project convention, not in related_family.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **HER MARRIAGE INTRODUCES COERT / STEPHEN / STEVEN INTO THE COWENHOVEN COUSIN POOL** via husband Coert Stevense Van Voorhees (son of Steven Coerts Van Voorhees of Drenthe, NL). Stephen recurs as her son #47.\n- Children's first names: Stephen (Van Voorhees), Albert / Cornelis / Johannes / Gerrit (mix), Aeltje / Neeltje (Cowenhoven maternal), Annetje, Marretje (her own).\n- 1 child (Neeltje #51) married back into Schenck cousins (cp_fam_009's son Gerret #42) — cousin-marriage kin loop.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1644-04-10 bp. New Amsterdam (BDC 17)\n- bef. 1664 m. Coert Van Voorhees, settled Flatlands\n- bef. 1709 d. Flatlands\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n- Husband Coert Van Voorhees: magistrate Flatlands 1664/73; deacon DRC Flatlands 1677; captain of militia 1689; one of two reps for Flatlands in Assembly NA 1664-04-10 (KCo 376).\n\n## Kin network\n- Daughter Neeltje #51 married Gerret Roelofse Schenck = grandson of cp_fam_009 (Marretje's sister) via Schenck route. Closes a 4-Cowenhoven-grandchildren-marrying-Schenck-grandchildren loop.\n\n## COCHEU 71:1 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_047)\nNine-children directory + cousin-marriage tracking. Coert Van Voorhees from Hees, Drenthe NL (kin-origin marker).\n\n## Cocheu 81:2 (cp_sou_051) — daughter #51 Neeltje Van Voorhees as Schenck-Cowenhoven cousin marriage anchor\nCocheu 81:2 #42 names Neeltje Van Voorhees b. 1676-06-30, d. 1750-08-04, m. Flatlands ~1693 her cousin Gerrit Schenck #42 (son of cp_fam_009).\n→ 12 grandchildren #226-237 by this marriage.\n→ Marretje cp_fam_010 + Neeltje cp_fam_009 are sisters; their children's marriage = first-cousin marriage between sister-aunt-Cowenhovens' descendants.\n→ This Schenck/Voorhees double-Cowenhoven-grandmother cluster is the KIN-NETWORK ANCHOR for the 5 Cowenhoven-Schenck marriages of Gen 5-6 (cp_fam_141/142/145/146 + cp_fam_095). | 2026-05-18 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_025 1646 Gerrit estate settlement): named as \"Marrtijen Gerrits, aged two and a half years\" in 1646 — confirms birth ~late 1643/early 1644 (consistent with 1644-04-10 baptism per workbook). Youngest child of cp_fam_003 Gerrit + cp_fam_006 Aeltje. Inheritance: 200 guilders, payable in cash by stepfather cp_fam_025 Elbert at majority or marriage.",
