      "notes": "Second wife of cp_fam_007 Willem Gerritsz Couwenhoven; mother of John Willemse (cp_fam_057) and the larger Willemse-generation cohort. Discrepancy: cp_fam_007 records 1665 marriage at Flatlands; FS records New Amsterdam — possibly recording vs. residence distinction. Eldest Willemse child Aeltje (1665) named after husband's first wife per Dutch convention. Patronymic 'Pieterse' implies father named Pieter; Monfoort surname appears in New Netherland records but family-of-origin not yet anchored to primary source.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- **SHE BRINGS PIETER (her father Pieter Monfort) AND THE MONFORT IN-LAW SURNAME INTO THE WILLEM-GERRETSE SUB-BRANCH.** Pieter recurs via her son cp_fam_069 (#22 Pieter b. 1671-02-12).\n- 11 of cp_fam_007's 12 children are by her (only #19 Gerret was 1st-wife child). See cp_fam_007 children_summary for the directory.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1646-05-08 bp. New Amsterdam (DRC NA)\n- 1665-02-12 m. Willem Gerretse Couwenhoven (cp_fam_007), settled Flatlands\n- 1721 member Brick Church Marlborough NJ with husband Willem\n- 1723 alone as member (husband d. between 1721 and 1723)\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n\n## Kin network\n- Wife of Willem Gerretse cp_fam_007 (mother of his 11 of 12 children).\n- Daughter of Pieter Monfort.\n\n## COCHEU 71:1 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_047)\nFather confirmed Pieter Monfort (no longer hypothesis). Baptism record located: BDC 20 = DRC NA 1646-05-08. Confidence_flag upgraded HYPOTHESIS → MATCH.\n\nBurial confirmed at Old Brick Reformed Church Cemetery per 2026-05-19 FaG cohort screenshot — supports prior d.1723 hypothesis (church membership 1721-1723 per Brick Church Mem. 1877). FaG individual memorial ID pending capture.",
