      "wikitree_url": "https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Couwenhoven-72",
      "wikitree_id": "Couwenhoven-72",
      "birth_date": "ca. 1669 (bp. 1669-02-27, BDC 94, per Cocheu 71:1 cp_sou_047) — supersedes WikiTree '1665'",
      "birth_year": 1669,
      "birth_place": "New Amsterdam / New York — unverified",
      "baptism_date": "1669-02-27",
      "baptism_place": "Reformed Dutch Church, New York City",
      "marriage_date": "",
      "marriage_place": "",
      "death_date": "between 1700-11-10 and 1705-03-17 (will dated 10 Nov 1700 OR 30 Nov 1702 — Cocheu 71:1 notes ambiguity; inventory taken 1704/5-03-17, pro. 1704/5-03-21, NJ Wills 1:112)",
      "death_year": 1700,
      "death_place": "unverified",
      "burial_date": "",
      "burial_place": "",
      "residence_primary": "",
      "occupation": "Brewer in Elizabethtown NJ 1688-89 (per Deed Bk. H-2:386 Trenton); previously settler/merchant New Amsterdam. Signed name 'Cownover' on his will.",
      "father_text": "Pieter Wolphertsen van Couwenhoven (cp_fam_005)",
      "mother_text": "Aeltje Sybrants (cp_fam_023; WikiTree Sybrants-2)",
      "spouse_text": "Mary (surname unknown) — alive at time of his will (per Cocheu 71:1 cp_sou_047 + NJ Wills 1:112)",
      "children_summary": "Five children with Mary per Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047):\n  87. Peter (Jr.) = cp_fam_087; m. Elizabeth —. His will dated 1730-06-26, pro. 1730-08-21 (NJ Wills 2:116).\n  88. John = cp_fam_088; m. Sarah Adams, dau. of Rebecca Adams whose 1750-08-01 will (pro. 1754-06-28) mentions her dau. Sarah Covenover (NJ Wills 3:6).\n  89. David = cp_fam_089; m. (unnamed) dau. of Samuel + Mary (—) Gale.\n  90. Hester = cp_fam_090; m. Richard Risley.\n  91. Mary = cp_fam_091; m. John Adams.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "WikiTree Couwenhoven-72: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Couwenhoven-72 (via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 (Jul 1952), pp. 147-156 (cp_sou_058)",
      "notes": "SECOND Petrus in Pieter's WikiTree children list (cp_fam_016 is Petrus #1, who likely died young). This is the surviving Petrus with a full WikiTree profile. Half-sibling to cp_fam_016-020 (through father Pieter) and to cp_fam_022 Aeltje du Trieux (through father). FOLLOW-UP: pull full profile (spouse, children, occupation, residence); determine whether this line produced any project-record enslavers.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- Children's names — Peter (patrilineal), John, David, Hester (his sister cp_fam_018 + grandmother), Mary (his wife) — notably Anglicized, consistent with Pieter-branch NJ Conover migration pattern.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1669-02-27 bp. NY City (BDC 94)\n- moved to Waymouth Township, Gloucester County NJ (per his will NJ Wills 1:112)\n- between 1700-11-10 and 1705-03-17 d. NJ\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none documented in Cocheu 71:1)\n\n## Kin network\n- Son John m. Sarah Adams, dau. of Rebecca Adams (Adams family connection — bears watching for Conover-Adams cluster in NJ).\n- Son David m. dau. of Samuel + Mary (—) Gale.\n- Daughter Hester m. Richard Risley; daughter Mary m. John Adams (continuing Adams kin).\n\n## COCHEU 71:1 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_047)\nBirth tightened from WikiTree-derived '1665' to bp. 1669-02-27. Death window from '1705' to between 1700-11-10 (or 1702-11-30) and 1705-03-17. Wife Mary identified. 5 children directory with NJ Wills sources.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #18)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #18 — concluding article reaffirms Peter³ as the Great Egg Harbor settler (definitively refuting Muchmore's Cornelius³ hypothesis). Key new field-level evidence:\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1675: \"Here begins the Rights of Land due according to the Concessions — Peter Wolverson, wife and servants, 480 acres\" East Jersey (NJA:21:46-47).\n- 1681-82: Return of Survey in Elizabethtown for Gov. Carteret: \"in right of Peter Wollverson, wife and servant, 256 acres\" (NJA:21:50).\n- 1688-89: BREWER living in Elizabethtown, sold 12 acres to John Woodruff \"his first division in said towne 1688-9\" — deed signed by both Peter and his 2nd wife Aeltje (Deed Bk. H-2, p.386, Trenton).\n- 1695-11-29: bought 259 acres along Patconk Creek in Great Egg Harbor Twp from Thomas Budd (Phila. merchant) at \"ye yearly quit rent of one ear of Indian Corne.\" Called \"of Long Island\" in this deed (Glou. Co. Deeds:3:59-60).\n- 1698-01-30: bought additional 150 acres from Daniel Leeds (Glou. Co. Deeds:3:131-32).\n\n## Civic + occupation\n- BREWER in Elizabethtown 1688-89 (per deed Bk. H-2:386).\n\n## Naming-pattern signal\n- Signed his own name \"Cownover\" in his will (NJA:23:112). Earliest documented use of the Conover spelling in this branch.\n\n## Marriage\n- 1640-12-02 New York Dutch Church to (1) widow Hester Symons. 1665-11-22 to (2) widow Aeltje Sibrants (MDC: 10 & 31). 83:3 explicitly REJECTS the alleged 3rd marriage to Josyntje Thomas in 1699 (\"we have no record of this third marriage\") — closes a long-standing genealogical question.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_005;Parent|cp_fam_023;Sibling|cp_fam_016;Sibling|cp_fam_017;Sibling|cp_fam_018;Sibling|cp_fam_019;Sibling|cp_fam_020;Half-sibling|cp_fam_022;Child|cp_fam_087;Child|cp_fam_088;Child|cp_fam_089;Child|cp_fam_090;Child|cp_fam_091",
