      "spouse_text": "Two marriages per Cocheu 1989 A&C p.17 (Mrs. John Spell): 1st wife name unknown (m. 1690 per Flatbush DRC fee book — Frost Coll. v.1 p.28); 2nd wife Lysbeth ——— surname unknown (m. 1692 per Flatbush DRC fee book — Frost Coll. v.1 p.29; named on baptismal entries 1699-1721 as mother of his children; still living 1721 at a grandchild's baptism). Earlier 'Aeltie' attribution (Cocheu 71:1 / Bergen KCo 77) was Bergen's conflation with cousin Gerret Jans⁴ #31 — A&C ruled out via Flatbush DRC fee-book chronology (Gerret Jans⁴ not yet of marriageable age in 1690 or 1692). Crowd-sourced surname candidates for Lysbeth (UNVERIFIED): 'Hoos' (FindaGrave 173362300); 'Andut' (FamilySearch GDT6-282).",
      "children_summary": "Per Cocheu 1989 A&C p.17 (Mrs. John Spell): 6 children by 2nd wife Lysbeth, retaining Cocheu's original entry numbering under #31. The earlier Cocheu 71:1 statement 'no record of any children for them has been found' is SUPERSEDED by this correction. Children: (#201) Willem⁵ b. abt. 1693; m. Ariantje Bennet, dau. Willem Willemse Bennet × Ariantje Van de Water (Record v.94, p.156) — NOT YET MINTED. (#92) Joris⁵ = cp_fam_092, b. abt. 1695; m. 1719-05-26 Flatbush DRC Aletta Luyster. Unnamed child b. abt. 1697, d. infancy (Census, Doc.Hist.NY v.3 p.133) — NOT YET MINTED. (#197) Jacomyntje⁵ bp. Brooklyn 1699-01-15, d. infancy — NOT YET MINTED. (#198) Jacomyntje⁵ bp. Brooklyn 1701-03-02; m. 1720-09-17 Elbert Luyster, brother of Joris's wife Aletta Luyster (Frost Coll. Fbush Marr. v.1 p.61 — double Cowenhoven-Luyster sibling-marriage) — NOT YET MINTED. (#199) Aeltje⁵ bp. Brooklyn 1701-03-02 (twin of #198); no further record — NOT YET MINTED.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #19 — Willem's only child by 1st wife Aeltje Joris Brinckerhoff. Mother Aeltje d. 1663-06-03 when Gerret was barely 1.5 years old; raised by stepmother Jannetje Monfoort cp_fam_061 from 1665.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1701-04-27 bought from stepmother Jannetje Monfort cp_fam_061 + other Pieter Monfort heirs the Pieter Monfort farm and patent at the Wallabout (Brooklyn — KCo 77)\n- 1704 also owned land in Bushwick (per Bushwick town records, KCo 77)\n\n### Civic offices\n- (none specifically documented)\n\n### Kin network\n- Stepmother Jannetje Monfort cp_fam_061 (Cocheu's word — actually his STEPMOTHER given his birth-mother Aeltje Brinckerhoff died 1663 + father remarried 1665 to Jannetje when Gerret was 3 yo)\n- 1701 Wallabout farm transaction with Pieter Monfort heirs links him to maternal-side Monfort kin\n\n### THE JORIS #92 QUESTION (RESOLVED 2026-05-30 — see below)\nCocheu 71:2 pp. 157-158 devotes a full discussion to whether **Joris Couwenhoven** (m. 1719-05-26 at Flatbush, Aeltje Luyster — Flatb 99; AnN 360) was Gerret Willemse cp_fam_066's son or a grandson. Cocheu's reasoning AGAINST Joris being Willem cp_fam_007's son (per earlier authorities Bergen + Honeyman + Schenck Conover): if Joris = Willem's son via 1st wife Aeltje Brinckerhoff (m. 1660, d. 1663-06-03), Joris would have been 56-58 at his 1719 marriage and ~73 at last child — improbable but possible. Cocheu's 1937 leading hypothesis: Joris was a GRANDSON of Willem cp_fam_007, possibly son of Gerret Willemse cp_fam_066. Supporting: 1902 letter from L.H. Schenck Conover of Marlboro NJ (in Rowland J. Conover file gifted by Capt. Willis C. Conover) explicitly retracts the earlier 'second-son' attribution as 'an error' — admits couldn't prove sonship. Stage 1c HYPOTHESIS: Joris = Gerret cp_fam_066's son, b. ca. 1693-1700 estimated. WILL BE MINTED IN PHASE B with confidence_flag=HYPOTHESIS-WEAK pending primary archival research (Long Island records flagged by Schenck Conover as 'proper place to search').\n\n## 2026-05-30 JORIS RESOLUTION — Cocheu 1989 A&C upgrade\n\nThe \"Stage 1c HYPOTHESIS\" above is upgraded to MATCH by the Cocheu 1989 reprint's embedded Addition & Correction (Mrs. John Spell, p.17, .md lines 668, 674, 688):\n\n- Gerret Willemse⁴ was twice married (NOT once to 'Aeltie' as Bergen/KCo 77 said). 1st wife name unknown (m. 1690). 2nd wife Lysbeth ——— (m. 1692, surname unknown). Both marriages documented by Flatbush DRC fee book — Frost Coll. v.1 pp.28-29: 6 g. paid by 'Gerret Couwenhoven, bridegroom' in each year. Cousin Gerret Jans⁴ #31 was not yet of marriageable age in either year, ruling out the Bergen conflation.\n- The earlier 'no record of any children' statement is superseded: A&C lists 6 children of Gerret Willemse + Lysbeth (see children_summary).\n- cp_fam_092 Joris confidence upgraded HYPOTHESIS-WEAK → MATCH.\n- 5 unminted full-siblings flagged for follow-up: #201 Willem (m. Ariantje Bennet); 1697 unnamed infant; #197 + #198 Jacomyntje (latter m. Elbert Luyster, brother of Joris's wife — double Cowenhoven-Luyster marriage); #199 Aeltje (twin of #198).\n- Triangulation confirms: Cocheu A&C + FamilySearch L2QL-9CD (this row) + FindaGrave (no direct memorial for Gerret Willemse located, but FG 173362300 for son Joris names 'Garret Cowenhoven' as father).",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_007;Half-sibling|cp_fam_054;Half-sibling|cp_fam_057;Sibling|cp_fam_067;Sibling|cp_fam_068;Sibling|cp_fam_069;Sibling|cp_ens_004;Sibling|cp_fam_071;Sibling|cp_ens_002;Sibling|cp_ens_009;Sibling|cp_fam_074;Sibling|cp_fam_075;Spouse|Lysbeth ___ (2nd wife);Child|cp_fam_092;Parent|cp_fam_125",
