      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #20.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1665-12-14 b. New Amersfoort (Flatlands), Long Island\n- 1687-03-16 m. Cornelius Symonse Van Arsdale at Flatbush (his 2nd wife)\n- abt. 1689 d. (per SCoQ 8:100) — only ~24 years old; left ONE child Jannetje\n- (Husband Van Arsdale m.(3) 1691; resided Flatlands; Cornelius's family later removed to Freehold NJ after 1710; Aeltje predeceased the NJ migration)\n\n### Kin network\n- ONE child by Van Arsdale: 93. Jannetje (b. abt. 1690 SCoQ 8:101; m. 1709-09-17 Dirck Barkeloo; 1709 they resided Freehold NJ — Dirck's will 1744-07-16 pro. 1744-08-16 NJ Wills 2:36).\n- Husband's later children by 3rd wife Marretje Dirkse: 9 children (Dirck #94 settled Three Mile Run Somerset Co. NJ; Jan #95 d.1750 settled Harlingen NJ; Symon #96 b.1697-08-16 m.1716-10-30 Yannetje Romeyn settled Bucks Co. PA; Philip #97 b.Flatbush 1702-02-25 d.1796-06-28 m.(1) 1726-04-30 Jane Van Dyke m.(2) 1750-04-13 Hannah Macknish; Abraham #98 d.1753 m. Maria Stryker NJ Wills 3:332; Jacobus #99 m. Alida Hoagland b.1710-03-19 d.1781-11-06; Altie #100 m.1719-09-19 Jeronimus Rapalje; Petronella #101 living 1738 possibly m. Dirck Van Dyke; Maria #102 living 1738). NOT minted as cp_fam (Van Arsdale surname, non-Cowenhoven).\n- Cornelius Van Arsdale's mother Peternelle Claesen Wyckoff connects this branch to the broader Wyckoff network (also entered via cp_fam_068 Neeltje's marriage).\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- Brings 'Van Arsdale' as in-law surname; her brief life means little Van Arsdale propagation through her direct descendants.",
