      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #21. Wyckoff connection: marries into the same Wyckoff family that her aunt cp_fam_009 Neeltje Schenck's husband Roelof married into (Annetje Pieterse Wyckoff was Roelof's 2nd wife).\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1669-02-07 b. Flatlands LI\n- 1692 m. John Pieterse Wyckoff\n- 1707 removed Flatlands → Monmouth County NJ (per Cocheu 71:2)\n- 1709 both members Marlborough Brick Church\n\n### Kin network — NJ migration anchor\n- Husband's family: Peter Claesen Wyckoff + Griete Van Ness — major Long Island Wyckoff family.\n- 7 children listed in husband's 1746 will: Cornelius (eldest), John, Pieter, Jacob, Geertie, Neeltie, Johannes. Plus Cocheu lists possible 8th child William (b. 1707 Freehold, d. 1782, m.1729 Angenietje Van Dorn — sup. KCo 396 + Wyckoff Fam. 445; NOT in will so possibly stillborn or omitted).\n- Children's bp. dates: 103. Pieter bp. Flatbush 1695-06-08 d. 1698 (Flatb Ch ms copy 80); 104. Pieter bp. NY 1704-04-23 BDC 298 (ancestor of Newtown branch per KCo 396); 105. Cornelius bp. NJ 1710-04-04 (SCoQ 6:137); 106. Johannes bp. Freehold 1711-12-10 (FM Ch Rec) m. Aeltje Barkaloo bp. 1710-10-30 EDSM 106 dau. of Dirk Barkaloo — links Wyckoff to Barkaloo via cp_fam_067's daughter Jannetje's husband; 107. William sup., bp. Freehold b. 1707, d. 1782, m. 1729 Angenietje Van Dorn; 108. Jacob; 109. Geertie b. 1693 d. 1765-12-21 m. 1713 Jonathan Forman SCoQ 6:137; 110. Neeltje. ALL Wyckoff surname, NOT minted as cp_fam.\n- Daughter Geertie's marriage to Jonathan Forman is the FIRST documented Cowenhoven-Wyckoff-Forman link — Forman family later marries back into Cowenhoven multiple times (NJ cluster bridge).\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- Children's first names show Cowenhoven patrilineal echoes via Wyckoff descent: Pieter (twice — first d. young), Cornelius, Johannes, Jacob, Geertie (Wyckoff side).",
