      "spouse_text": "Patience Daws — daughter of Elias Daws of Gravesend; b. Flatlands abt. 1672. Both members Brick Church Marlborough NJ 1709, at which time Pieter was an Elder (Ch. Mem. Marlborough 81, 84, per Cocheu 71:2 cp_sou_048).",
      "children_summary": "",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #22. Named for maternal grandfather Pieter Monfort — confirms Pieter-from-Monfort first-name route in the Willem sub-branch.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1671-02-12 b. Flatlands LI\n- abt. 1694 m. Patience Daws (Flatlands area)\n- by 1709 settled Freehold NJ as yeoman; Elder Brick Church Marlborough that year\n- 1743-03-15 will dated\n- abt. February 1755 d. near Freehold NJ\n- 1755-04-23 will pro.\n\n### Civic offices\n- Elder Brick Church Marlborough NJ 1709 (Ch. Mem. Marlborough 81, 84 — first NJ-arrival generation civic leadership)\n\n### Kin network\n- 10 children all NJ-born or NJ-raised — major founding generation of Freehold/Englishtown/Middletown NJ Cowenhoven cluster.\n- 4 of 10 children married into other Cowenhoven cousin lines: #114 Mary m. Koert Schenck; #116 Aeltie m. cousin Willem Williamsen (cp_fam_074's son); #119 Peter m. cousin Leah Janse Schenck (cp_fam_009 line); #120 Anney m. John Longstreet.\n- Wife's father Elias Daws of Gravesend (Brooklyn) — Daws/Daws family ties LI to NJ migration cluster.\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- 10 children's names: Johanna/Hannah, Jane (Anglicized), Allice (d. y.), Mary, William, Aeltie/Alice, Elias (after maternal grandfather Elias Daws — strong maternal-grandfather naming!), Nelke/Eleanora (d. y.), Peter, Amey/Anney.\n- 'Elias' enters Cowenhoven name pool via wife's father — recurs in #117 Elias d. 1750-12-25 — small but distinctive Daws-route signal.\n- Heavy ANGLICIZATION (Hannah, Jane, Allice, Mary, William, Alice, Eleanora, Amey/Anney) — typical of NJ Conover-bound branches.\n\n### Children directory (Phase B will mint)\n  111. Johanna (Hannah)5, b. 1695-09-26, bp. Brooklyn 1695-10-20 (Brkn 169); m. Johannes Antonides.\n  112. Jane5, b. 1697-07-28; m. Wilem Williamsen (150th Ann RDC New Brunswick 209).\n  113. Allice5, b. 1699-09-02; d. y.\n  114. Mary5, b. 1701-07-25, d. 1787-05-17; m. 1725-10-10 Koert Gerretse Schenck (KCo 80).\n  115. William5 of Englishtown NJ, b. 1703-07-11, d. 1777-05-03; will dated 1777-04-10, pro. 1777-05-20 (NJ Wills 5:112); m. 1725-05-01 Mary Theodorus Colyer.\n  116. Aeltie (Alice)5, b. 1705-05-21, d. 1797-11-16; m. 1730-01-16 her cousin Willem Williamsen (#177, son of cp_fam_074).\n  117. Elias5, b. 1707-09-12, d. 1750-12-25; will dated 1750-12-15, pro. 1751-01-30 (NJ Wills 2:115; NJMis 2:354); m. 1729 Willempie Wall of Middletown.\n  118. Nelke (Eleanora)5, b. 1709-09-02, bp. 1710-01-22 (FM); prob. d. y.\n  119. Peter5, b. 1712-01-27, bp. 1712-04-06 (FM), d. 1774 (KCo 80); will dated 1774-03-22, pro. 1774-06-07 (NJ Wills 5:111); m. 1735-12-17 his cousin Leah Janse Schenck (#140, dau. cp_fam_071 + Jan Roelofse Schenck).\n  120. Amey or Anney5, b. 1714-09-29, bp. 1714-11-19 (FM); m. 1736-12-17 John Longstreet.\n\n\n\n2026-05-20: Spouse Patience Daws promoted to own row cp_fam_320 per Old Brick mint batch.",
