      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 (Jul 1940), pp. 273-276 (cp_sou_049)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #70.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3)\n- Husband Abraham Mesier was a New Amersfoort native (bp. 1663) who became NYC Freeman (1698) + Asst. Alderman (Out Ward 1698-1702) — civic anchor.\n- 1st daughter Zara b. Bergen NJ (1691) — couple temporarily in Bergen NJ early in marriage.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1671-03-22 bp. NY (BDC 101)\n- 1690-11-19 m. NY DRC (banns 1690-10-30)\n- 1691 brief Bergen NJ residence (1st daughter Zara b. there)\n- 1692+ NY DRC baptisms — settled NY City\n- 1742-08-01 d.; bur. Dutch Ch., NY\n\n## Civic offices (husband, by association)\n- 1698-08-30 husband Abraham made NY City Freeman\n- 1698-1702 husband Asst. Alderman Out Ward\n\n## Kin network\n- Mesier surname = New Amersfoort Dutch line; Pieter Jansen Mesier was likely a community elder.\n- Daughter #244 Marritje m. Samuel Pell (Pell surname enters Mesier-Cowenhoven kin-network).",
