      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #24. **First-cousin marriage** — husband Jan Roelofse Schenck is son of Sara's aunt cp_fam_009 + Roelof Martense Schenck.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1674-12-20 (or 1674-12-27) b. Flatlands LI\n- 1692-10-01 m. her cousin Jan Roelofse Schenck\n- abt. 1695 settled Monmouth County NJ — EARLIEST DOCUMENTED Willem-Gerretse-line NJ migrant per Cocheu 71:2. The 1695 settlement establishes the core of the Pleasant Valley Schenck-Couwenhoven cluster.\n- 1709 both members Marlborough Brick Church\n- 1761-01-31 d. ae. 86; bur. Schenck-Couwenhoven Cem Pleasant Valley\n\n### Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n\n### Kin network — FIRST-COUSIN MARRIAGE; major NJ founder\n- Husband Jan Roelofse Schenck = SON of her aunt cp_fam_009 Neeltje + Roelof Martense Schenck. Her first cousin.\n- 11+ children listed in Cocheu 71:2 (Schenck surname, NOT minted). Major Schenck-Couwenhoven NJ kin density.\n- 1746 will of Jan Schenck (NJ Wills 3:281) — useful for descendant tracking; pro. 1755-06-03 indicates Jan d. 1753.\n- Children directory (Schenck surname; NOT minted as cp_fam): 135. Roelof b. Flatlands 1692-02-21 d. 1766-01-19 m. 1716 Geesie Hendrickson; 136. Sarah b. 1696 m.(1) 1721-05-16 Johannes Voorhees of New Brunswick m.(2) abt. 1737 Hendrick Voorhees of Freehold; 137. Altje b. NJ 1705-05-25 bp. Brooklyn 1705-05-29 m. 1723-12-11 Christjan Van Doren; 138. Rachel b. NJ 1709-02-19 m. — Boon of Kentucky; 139. Maria b. NJ 1712-08-08 d. 1756-10-31 m. Jacob Van Doren; 140. Leah b. NJ 1714-12-24 d. 1769-03-14 m. 1735-12-17 Pieter cp_fam_069's son #119 Peter Cowenhoven (cousin); 141. William bp. 1718-04-13 d. y.; 142. Jannetje bp. 1719-04-12 m. Bernardus Ver Bryck Sheriff Monmouth Co. (settled Neshaminy PA); 143. Jan b. 1722-06-27 d. 1808-12-24 m. 1750-06-28 Nellie Eleanor Bennet; 144. Antje m. abt. 1720 Arie Van Doren; 145. Peter m.(1) Jannetje Hansen Van Noostrand m.(2) 1747 Jannetje Hendrickson (widow of Roelof cp_ens_009's son #161).\n- Daughter #140 Leah's marriage to her cousin Peter Cowenhoven (cp_fam_069's son #119) closes another Cowenhoven-Schenck cousin loop.\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- 11 children's names heavy on Schenck-line: Roelof (Schenck patriarch), Jan, Antje (Wyckoff route), Peter (her brother cp_fam_069 + grandfather Pieter Monfort).\n- Several daughters anglicized in second-marriage events (Sarah's daughter Sarah Schenck m. Voorhees twice, etc.) — typical of early NJ migration cluster.\n- Daughter named 'Boon of Kentucky' — early NJ→KY migration signal in this branch (Boone family connection? — flag for further research; possibly Daniel Boone family).",
