      "death_place": "New York City (Greenwich, Out Ward of NYC)",
      "burial_date": "",
      "burial_place": "Originally entombed in vault at Collegiate Church Cemetery, Houston St. between Forsyth & Eldridge Sts., NYC (cp_pla_069). Remains relocated 1868 to Cypress Hills Cemetery (cp_pla_068).",
      "residence_primary": "Greenwich, Out Ward of NYC (Lower Manhattan, contemporary West Village area; cp_pla_038)",
      "occupation": "Joiner (woodworker / cabinetmaker) — per his 1745 will",
      "father_text": "Johanes Van Cowenhoven (cp_fam_012) — CONFIRMED via Cocheu 71:4 (cp_sou_050) #72: 'son of Johannes Jacobse³ and Saertje Frans'",
      "mother_text": "Saartie Frans (cp_fam_013) — CONFIRMED via Cocheu 71:4 (cp_sou_050) #72",
      "spouse_text": "3 marriages per Cocheu 71:4: (1) m. 1709-12-03 Catharine Olivier (cp_fam_155; MDC 112); (2) m. 1727-11-12 Maria Brouwn (cp_fam_038; MDC 147) — d. before 1745-08-15, the 'late wife Mary' in his will; (3) m. 1746-04-14 Hillegond (—) Bogart (cp_fam_156; MDC 174), widow; she d. 1749/50-03-15 (HSYB 1899), bur. Du. Ref. Ch. NY 1749-03-17 (DDC 174).",
      "children_summary": "Natural (illegitimate) son Samuel Cowenhoven (cp_fam_039; main heir; father of Frans's grandchildren Edward cp_fam_042 and Mary cp_fam_043). \"Son-in-law John Fred and his wife Martha\" (cp_fam_040, cp_fam_041) named in the will — uncertain whether Martha was Frans's biological daughter or his stepdaughter via Mary's prior Herring marriage (HYPOTHESIS per genealogy.com forum; see Martha's row).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "NY Surrogate's Office Liber 16 p.400 — will of Frans Cowenhoven of Greenwich, Out Ward of New York, joiner, dated 1745-08-15, proved 1749-02-20 (1748/9 old-style) (FamilySearch book 111896 pp.207-208: https://www.familysearch.org/library/books/viewer/111896/?offset=0#page=217). Witnesses: Abraham Lefferts, Abraham Van Wyck, Abraham Lynsen. | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050)",
      "notes": "Testator of 1745 will. Occupation 'joiner' (woodworker/cabinetmaker). Residence Greenwich in the Out Ward of New York — this is the LOWER MANHATTAN / contemporary Greenwich Village / West Village area, geographically distinct from the Flatlands-Brooklyn-Raritan concentration of the Wolphert line. **Lineage unresolved**: no standalone WikiTree profile located as of 2026-04-24; unclear whether Frans descends from cp_fam_001 Wolphert Gerritsz (via an as-yet-unmapped branch) or represents a separate Couwenhoven immigrant lineage. Flag follow-up. Preserves the legal phrasing 'my natural son Samuel' — 18th-century legal term for formally acknowledged illegitimate child (parallels cp_fam_022 Aeltje (du Trieux) Pieters, Pieter Wolphertsen's acknowledged extramarital daughter). Will also references the tankard + 3 spoons that 'did belong to my late wife Mary, before our marriage' — heirloom provenance supports Martha-as-stepdaughter hypothesis since the silver passes through to Martha's household. Son-in-law John Fred + wife Martha + Peter Messier + Simon Johnson named as executors; probate handled by John Fred and Martha per 1749 filing.\n\n## RESOLUTION via Cocheu 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — Greenwich joiner identified\nCocheu's #72 Frans (Francois)⁴ Van Kouwenhoven matches cp_fam_037 exactly: 'resided Greenwich, NY (City)... bp. NY 1675-02-24 (BDC 118); d. NY 1749-02-02 (DDC 174); buried in vault in Collegiate Church Cemetery, Houston St., between Forsyth and Eldridge Sts., NYC; remains removed in 1868 to Cypress Hills Cemetery. Will (\"Joiner,\" Greenwich, NY) dated Aug. 15, 1745; pro. Feb. 20, 1748/9 (WNYHS, 4:208)'.\n→ branch=Jacob, gen=4, parents=cp_fam_012/013. Resolves the 5/9 morning Stage 1b deferred cluster (cp_fam_037 to cp_fam_043 all cascade to Jacob branch).\n\n## Three marriages (Cocheu 71:4 #72)\n1. 1709-12-03 m. Catharine Olivier (cp_fam_155 — newly minted as in-law, surname suggests French Huguenot origin)\n2. 1727-11-12 m. Maria Brouwn (cp_fam_038 — RENAMED FROM 'Mary Jansen', see correction note below)\n3. 1746-04-14 m. Hillegond (—) Bogart (cp_fam_156 — newly minted, prior marriage to a Bogart; 'late wife Mary' provision in 1745 will means he was a widower when he married her)\n\n## CORRECTION: cp_fam_038 wife was Maria Brouwn, NOT Mary Jansen\nPre-71:4 workbook entry for cp_fam_038 was 'Mary Jansen', sourced from a genealogy.com forum snippet. Cocheu 71:4 (citing primary Manhattan Reformed Dutch Church marriage register MDC 147) gives the actual surname: Maria Brouwn. The 'Herring prior marriage' hypothesis (also from same forum) is REFUTED by Cocheu — Cocheu lists Martha (cp_fam_040) directly as Frans's biological 'daughter'.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- Son cp_fam_039 Samuel = paternal grandfather Saartje's brother(?) or Frans's choice\n- Daughter cp_fam_040 Martha = uncertain naming pattern; possible Olivier-line name\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1675-02-24 bp. NYC RDC\n- ca. 1690-1709 trained as joiner (woodworker)\n- 1709-12-03 m. (1) Catharine Olivier NYC RDC\n- 1727-11-12 m. (2) Maria Brouwn NYC RDC\n- ca. 1735-1745 residing Greenwich (Out Ward of NYC) — joiner trade\n- 1745-08-15 will dated\n- 1746-04-14 m. (3) Hillegond Bogart\n- 1749-02-02 d. NYC; bur. Collegiate Church Cemetery Houston St. (cp_pla_069)\n- 1748/9-02-20 will pro. (WNYHS 4:208)\n- 1868 remains relocated Cypress Hills Cemetery (cp_pla_068)\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none documented; tradesman, not civic figure)\n\n## Kin network\n- 4th generation Jacob branch — sibling cluster: cp_fam_014 Jacob, cp_fam_079 Hester, cp_fam_080 Lysbeth, cp_fam_081 Jacomyntie, cp_fam_082 Francois (d.y.; not minted), cp_fam_083 Johannes, cp_fam_084 Maria, cp_fam_085 Catalyntie, cp_fam_086 Pieter\n- Greenwich/NYC Jacob-branch outpost — distinct geographically + occupationally from sibling cp_fam_014's Hackensack 1718 relocation and from sibling cp_fam_083's Hackensack 1718 relocation.\n- Marriage pool = NYC Reformed Dutch Church milieu (Olivier, Brouwn, Bogart all NYC Dutch families).",
      "raw_related_family": "Spouse|cp_fam_038;Child|cp_fam_039;Parent|cp_fam_012;Parent|cp_fam_013;Sibling|cp_fam_014;Sibling|cp_fam_079;Sibling|cp_fam_080;Sibling|cp_fam_081;Sibling|cp_fam_082;Sibling|cp_fam_083;Sibling|cp_fam_084;Sibling|cp_fam_085;Sibling|cp_fam_086;Spouse|cp_fam_155;Spouse|cp_fam_156;Child|cp_fam_040",
