      "spouse_text": "Neeltje Roelofse (Schenck) Couwenhoven (cp_fam_316) — m. 1701-10-02, Flatlands, Kings Co. NY",
      "children_summary": "Eleven children named in 1748 will: William (eldest), Ruluff, Anna, Jane, Alice, Marget, Sarah, Peter, Jarratt, John, Cornelius. UPDATE 2026-04-25: Son William now identified as cp_ens_011 (William Albertse Couwenhoven, 1702-1790-03-19 Manalapan/Freehold). Parent of project ENSLAVER row.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_002",
      "sources": "WikiTree: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Van_Couwenhoven-69 | FamilySearch Ancestors: https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LW1V-KTM/albert-willemse-van-couwenhoven-1676-1748 | Geni: https://www.geni.com/people/Albert-Covenhoven/6000000001713417336 | NJ Abstract of Wills Vol. XXX p.115 (Ancestry.com)",
      "notes": "Moved from Flatbush, NY to Freehold, NJ c. 1702. Member of Reformed Dutch Church, Freehold, from 1709. Possible son: Cornelius (named in will) — may be the Cornelius Albertse Couwenhoven who enslaved cp_per_174 Thomas and cp_per_175 Jude (pending confirmation). Possible brother: Cornelis Willemse van Couwenhoven (WikiTree Couwenhove-2, abt.1672-1736). Sister-marriage CONFIRMED 2026-04-24 late: Albert's wife Neeltje Roelofse and Cornelis (cp_ens_004)'s wife Margaretta are both daughters of Roelof Schenck + Annetje Wyckoff per WikiTree Couwenhove-2 snippet. Two Couwenhoven brothers married two Schenck sisters — Schenck kin-network bridge between Brooklyn and Monmouth NJ. THREE-BROTHERS CLUSTER confirmed 2026-04-25: Albert (this row), Cornelis (cp_ens_004), and Jacob (cp_ens_009) are the three sons of cp_fam_007 Willem Gerritsz Couwenhoven (Couwenhoven-4) who all settled Monmouth Co. NJ as enslaving yeomen — Albert in Freehold, Cornelis in Pleasant Valley, Jacob in Middletown.\n\n## CONSOLIDATED FROM cp_ens_002 (audit 2026-05-10)\nFAMILY-row enrichment merged into this ENSLAVER row; original FAMILY row deleted. Original FAMILY notes preserved below.\n\nCocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #25. **Cousin marriage** — wife Neeltje Schenck is granddaughter of Albert's aunt cp_fam_009 via Roelof's 2nd marriage.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1676-12-07 b. Flatlands LI\n- 1701-10-02 m. cousin Neeltje Schenck (KCo 254)\n- abt. 1702 removed to vicinity of Freehold NJ\n- 1709 both members RDC Freehold\n- 1715-11 member of grand jury Court of Quarter Session Freehold\n- 1748-09-06 will dated\n- 1748-09-13 d. Pleasant Valley NJ, ae. 72-9-6, bur. Schenck-Couwenhoven Cem\n- 1748-10-03 will pro.\n\n### Civic offices\n- 1715-11 grand jury, Court of Quarter Session, Freehold NJ (Cocheu 71:2)\n\n### Kin network\n- Wife = his cousin Neeltje Schenck (3rd of 4 Cowenhoven-Schenck cousin marriages among siblings).\n- 12 children listed by Cocheu (will mentions 11 + acknowledges Neeltje #154 predeceased him): #146 William b. 1702-03-09 m. Lysbeth Van Cleef; #147 Roelof b. 1703-09-08 m. Annetje Strycker; #148 Antje b. 1705-08-21 m. Abraham Polhemus; #149 Jannetje b. 1707-09-30 m. Joseph Coernel; #150 Aelke b. 1709-01-20 bp. 1709/10-02-19 m. Hendrick Hendrickson; #151 Margaretta b. 1711/12-02-15 bp. 1712-04-06 m. Daniel Polhemus; #152 Sarah b. 1714-06-21 m. Joseph or Johannes Van Cleef; #153 Peter b. 1716-10-21 bp. 1716-12-09 m. 1740 or 1741-05-19 Williampe Van Voorhees; #154 Neeltje b. 1719-02-07 d. 1738-04-22 ae. 19-2-15 unmarried bur. Schenck-Couwenhoven Cem; #155 Gerret b. 1721-06-16 bp. 1721-07-16 m. Sarah Van Voorhees; #156 Jan b. 1723-02-18 bp. 1723-03-24 m. Catherine Van Voorhees; #157 Cornelius b. 1728-10-29 m. by lic 1750-05-28 Antje Williamson, m. 1770-07-12 Mary Logan.\n- 3 children married Van Voorhees (Peter+Williampe; Gerret+Sarah; Jan+Catherine VV) — VAN VOORHEES becomes major in-law pattern in Pleasant Valley cluster.\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- 12 children's names: William, Roelof (Schenck), Antje/Aelke (Schenck), Jannetje (mother cp_fam_061), Margaretta (wife's name), Sarah, Peter, Neeltje (Cowenhoven matriarchs), Gerret, Jan, Cornelius — comprehensive Cowenhoven-Schenck kin echo.\n- 'Cornelius' #157 = grand-uncle Cornelius cp_fam_017 of Pieter line — possibly cross-branch naming via Wyckoff link.\n\n## FIELD-SEMANTICS CLEANUP 2026-05-21\nSpouse field previously carried parents-of-spouse + sister-of content (added 2026-04-24 from WikiTree snippet). Relocated per 5/21 cp_ens_002 pilot lesson: (a) parents-of-spouse (Roelof Martense Schenck × Annetje Pieterse Wyckoff) now in cp_fam_316.father/mother per Cocheu #25 p.21 canonical reading; (b) sister-of-cp_fam_308 relationship already captured in cp_fam_316.related_family Sister token. No information lost; only restructured.\n\n2026-05-23 PM5: Added 10 Child| tokens to related_enslavers (cp_fam_115 through cp_fam_124) closing bidirectional gap. cp_ens_002 already had Child|cp_ens_003 (=former cp_fam_125, #157 Cornelius) + Child|cp_ens_011 (=former cp_fam_114, #146 William). With these 10 additions all 12 of Albert's Cocheu-listed children (#146-#157) now have explicit Child| forward tokens. Reverse Parent|cp_ens_002 tokens already on all 10 cp_fam rows. Required by Step 5 of Cocheu_Discrepancy_Workflow.md (Parent/Child bidirectional including cross-sheet).",
