      "sources": "NY Surrogate's Office Liber 8 p.275 — will of Gerret Jansen Cowenhoven, dated 1711-04-06, proved 1712-11-03 (FamilySearch book 161766, p.131: https://www.familysearch.org/library/books/viewer/161766/?offset=0#page=131); Geni: https://www.geni.com/people/Gerret-Kouvenhoven/6000000001255006434 | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) — Cocheu 71:1 confirms parentage cp_fam_008 + cp_fam_030, b. abt. 1676, d. 1712, m.(1) Lysbet —, m.(2) Aeltje | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 (Jul 1940), pp. 273-276 (cp_sou_049)",
      "notes": "Testator of 1711 will. Leaves estate to wife Aeltie and son John (real and personal, Kings County or elsewhere). Executors may sell houses and lands at Bushwyck. Executors named: wife Aeltie, brother 'Nicesimus' (=Nicasius, cp_fam_027), and Theodorus Van Wyck. Probate note: 'Altie Cowenhoven being then the wife of Jacobus Cosine.' HYPOTHESIS: two marriages per WikiTree (Lysbet 1st, Aaltje 2nd); will doesn't disambiguate which wife was John's mother — flag follow-up. UPDATE 2026-04-24: son Jan/John's mother-ambiguity resolved — he is son of 2nd wife Aaltje van der Wijk (cp_fam_028), not 1st wife Lysbet (who predeceased Gerret and cannot have borne a child with post-1712 half-siblings). Confirmed via John's own 1753 will naming Cozyn half-brothers.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3)\n- 71:3 reaffirms b. Brooklyn ~1676, d. ~1712, will Apr 16 1711 / pro Nov 3 1712 (WNYHS 2:121) — already in record.\n- 2nd wife Aeltje was the wife of Jacobus Cosine when Gerret's will was proved (already in record).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- ca. 1676 b. Brooklyn\n- 1699-1701 children's baptisms Brooklyn DRC (Brkn 173, 177)\n- 1711-04-16 will dated; ~1712 d. Brooklyn area\n\n## Kin network\n- Son cp_fam_151 William⁵ established Three Mile Run NJ branch (m. Ariantje Bennet) — early NJ cluster outpost; not in same Brick Church Marlborough cluster as cp_fam_007's NJ descendants.",
