      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #73. Patrilineal Jan / Johannes recurrence.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_050 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 #73)\nFirst Cowenhoven anchor in Harlem NY then BERGEN COUNTY NJ via 1718-07-06 admission to Hackensack DRC by letter (Hack 8). Same year as brother cp_fam_014 Jacob⁴ joined Hackensack Ch. 1718 — TWO Johannes-Jacobse sons relocating to Bergen Co. NJ in 1718.\n\nThis is a load-bearing anchor for any future Bergen-branch enslaver disambiguation work (Case 37536, Black Births register, etc.).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1677-04-14 bp. NYC RDC (BDC 127)\n- 1708-05-08 m. NYC RDC Rachel Benson\n- 1709-1717 NYC RDC baptisms of first 5 children — Harlem residence\n- 1718-07-06 admitted to Hackensack DRC by letter (Hack 8) — relocated\n- 1723+ Hackensack DRC baptisms of later children (Elena #268, Petrus #271)\n\n## Civic offices\n- (none documented in 71:4)\n\n## Kin network\n- Wife Rachel Benson dau. Johannes Benson + Lysbet Van Deusen — Benson + Van Deusen NYC Dutch families. Brings Van Deusen surname into Cowenhoven kin-network (relevant: cp_fam_083's wife's mother is Lysbet Van Deusen — possible disambiguation signal for 'Lysbet' first names downstream).\n- 4 of 10 children: Hoogland-related marriages (#263 Marytjin Hoogland, #265 Neeltje Hoogland) + De Groot marriages (#262 Arien De Groot, #268 Peter De Groot — likely brothers).\n- Bergen-branch Jacob-line outpost. Distinct from sibling cp_fam_014's children (no overlap with Hackensack 1718 by-letter admittance entries for Jacob's children).\n- Daughter cp_fam_165 Benjamin m. Elizabeth Banta — Banta surname (Hackensack-area Bergen family).",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_012;Parent|cp_fam_013;Sibling|cp_fam_014;Sibling|cp_fam_079;Sibling|cp_fam_080;Sibling|cp_fam_081;Sibling|cp_fam_082;Sibling|cp_fam_084;Sibling|cp_fam_085;Sibling|cp_fam_086;Spouse|Rachel Benson;Child|cp_fam_157;Child|cp_fam_158;Child|cp_fam_159;Child|cp_fam_160;Child|cp_fam_161;Child|cp_fam_162;Child|cp_fam_163;Child|cp_fam_164;Child|cp_fam_165;Child|cp_fam_166",
