      "spouse_text": "Derick Abramse Brinckerhoff of Fishkill NY (originally of Flushing LI), son of Abraham Brinckerhoff + Aeltie Stryker; b. Flushing 1677-03-16, bp. 1677-04-02 (Brinckerhoff Bible); d. 1748-04-26. He m.(2) Elizabeth Anthony (no issue). Will dated 1744-03-16, pro. 1749-05-18 (WNYHS 4:221). m. Aeltje 1700 (Cocheu 71:3).",
      "children_summary": "9 Brinckerhoff children (matriline; not minted as cp_fam) per Cocheu 71:3 #203-211: (203) Abraham b. Flushing ~1701, d. 1738-07-11 ae. 38, bur. DChyd Fishkill, m. Femmetje Remsen (1703-1771); (204) Jan bp. NY 1703-08-15 BDC 292, d. 1785-03-20, m. 1725-03-12 Jannetje Van Voorhees; (205) Joris b. Flushing 1705-10-15, bp. Jamaica LI 1705-10-18, d. 1768-09-03, m.(1) 1727-03-24 Elizabeth Byvanck, m.(2) 1742-10-23 Maria Van Deursen; (206) Gerret bp. Jamaica 1708-10-05; (207) Isaac b. Fishkill 1714-01-12, bp. Jamaica 1714-03-24, d. 1770-04-22, m. 1737-02-28 Sarah Rapalje; (208) Jacob (twin of Isaac) b. 1714-01-12, d. 1758-05-06, m. Elizabeth Lent (Lent Gen. 12); (209) Gerardina d. 1749-09-13, m. Isaac Brinckerhoff of Newtown; (210) Aeltje m. 1736-06-19 William Hoogland; (211) Susannah bp. Jamaica 1717-02-10, m. Cornelius Luyster. See also Documentary History of Dutch Congregation of Oyster Bay, vol. 1 p. 157.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 (Jul 1940), pp. 273-276 (cp_sou_049)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #32. Marriage to Brinckerhoff — Brinckerhoff family had earlier married into Cowenhoven via cp_fam_007's 1st wife Aeltje Joris Brinckerhoff (Aeltje's aunt-by-marriage).\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3)\n- Husband Derick Brinckerhoff was eldest son in Fishkill NY branch of Brinckerhoff family; couple migrated from LI to Fishkill ~1700-1714.\n- Brinckerhoff family children's burials at Dutch Church yard, Fishkill (DChyd Fishkill / Dutchess Co. Gravestones, 74) — POTENTIAL cp_pla mint if a Cowenhoven row gets buried there in future research, but skipping for now per scope.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1678-04-28 bp. Flatbush DRC (already in baptism_date)\n- ca. 1700 m. + relocate to Flushing LI (husband's home)\n- ca. 1714 family in Fishkill NY (children's baptisms recorded Jamaica + Fishkill)\n- 1740-03-09 d. (presumed Fishkill area) ae. 62 (AnN 297)\n\n## Kin network\n- Brinckerhoff cluster Fishkill — ~9 children, several with Cowenhoven-line descent surfacing later (e.g., Joris #205 b.1705 may be the Joris Brinckerhoff who appears in 18th-c. NJ records as a Cowenhoven kin).\n- Daughter #207 Isaac m. Sarah Rapalje (Rapelje cousin link via cp_fam_078's Rapelje children).",
