      "children_summary": "10 children with Sarah Schenck (cp_fam_138) per Cocheu #26 + p.22 issue list (#158-167): (i) Jannetie⁵ b.1706-12-10 m.Hendrick Bennett (#158, cp_fam_126); (ii) Annie⁵ b.1708-02 m.John Hendrickson (#159, cp_fam_127); (iii) William⁵ b.1710-02 m.Antje Hendrickson #121 (#160, cp_fam_128); (iv) Ruleph (Roelof)⁵ b.1712-03-01 m.1741-08-12 Jannetie Hendrickson #145 (#161, cp_ens_010; intestate 1746-10-24 admin); (v) Jacob Jr⁵ b.1714-02-01 m.1742-12-21 Margaret⁶ Covenhoven (#162, cp_fam_130); (vi) Gerret⁵ b.1716-11-05 m.1744-10-12 Neeltje Schenck (#163, cp_fam_131); (vii) Peter⁵ b.1718-12-14 d.1719-01-04 d.y. (#164, NOT MINTED — infant); (viii) Peter⁵(II) b.1720-05 m.1749 Catherine Schenck wid.De Hart (#165, cp_fam_132); (ix) John⁵ b.1722-05-17 m.1750 Mary Van Dorn (#166, cp_fam_133); (x) Matthias (Martin)⁵ b.1725 m.1749 Williampe⁶ Kouwenhoven (#167, cp_ens_036). 1743 will also references granddaughter Sarah Covenhoven + grandsons Daniel Covenhoven, Daniel Hendrickson, Jacob Hendrickson (Hendrickson surname suggests at least one daughter married into Hendrickson family — likely #159 Annie m. John Hendrickson).",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_009",
      "sources": "New Jersey, U.S., Abstract of Wills, 1670-1817 [database online]. Provo, UT: Ancestry.com Operations, Inc., 2011. Original: New Jersey State Archives. New Jersey, Published Archives Series, First Series, Volume XXX, Abstracts of Wills, 1730-1750. Trenton, NJ: John L. Murphy Publishing Company. Will of Jacob Covenhoven of Middletown, Monmouth Co., yeoman, dated 1743-07-05; proved 1744-07-17. Lib. D, p. 152. Inventory taken 1744-12-03 (£618.18.8) by Samuel Ogborne, Hendrick Hendrickson and Edward Taylor — includes \"six negros, large Bible, 217 bushels Indian corn, books, 32 barrels flour\" plus extensive bonds and book debts. WikiTree Van_Couwenhoven-70 (https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Van_Couwenhoven-70).",
      "notes": "Third Willemse Couwenhoven brother NJ enslaver — sons of cp_fam_007 Willem Gerritsz Couwenhoven (1636-1728). Brothers: cp_ens_002 Albert (1676-1748, Freehold) m. Neeltje Roelofse Schenck; cp_ens_004 Cornelis (1672-1736, Pleasant Valley) m. Margaretta Schenck (cp_fam_308) (sister of Neeltje); cp_ens_009 Jacob (this row, 1679-1744, Middletown). All three lived/died in Monmouth Co. NJ; all three had documented enslaved people in their wills. Cross-cutting witness pattern: Garritt Schenck witnessed Cornelis's 1735 will (cp_ens_004), and a Schenck brother-in-law network connects all three brothers. (Jacob's witnesses are NOT Schenck — Joseph Goulder, George Crawford, Elias Golden, Charles Henderson — so Jacob's witness circle is more local-Middletown rather than Schenck-kin.) FAMILY-sheet row pending — Jacob is currently a FAMILY-as-superset gap. Will-vs-WikiTree son-name discrepancy: will names 6 sons (Martin/Roeloff/Jacob/Garret/Peter/John); WikiTree adds Matthias + lists William Jacobse where will says Jacob. Some sons may have predeceased + Dutch patronymic overlap; will is primary source. Note: distinct from cp_eve_004 = Jacob Covenhoven 1815 will (different person, likely grandson; \"sons spelled Conover at probate\" per memory). Do not conflate. Added 2026-04-25 from Jacob Covenhoven 1743 will (NJ Abstract of Wills Vol XXX p.152).\n\n## CONSOLIDATED FROM cp_ens_009 (audit 2026-05-10)\nFAMILY-row enrichment merged into this ENSLAVER row; original FAMILY row deleted. Original FAMILY notes preserved below.\n\nCocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #26. **Cousin marriage** — wife Sarah Schenck is granddaughter of Jacob's aunt cp_fam_009 via Roelof's 2nd marriage. Fourth Schenck-Cowenhoven cousin marriage among Willem's children (siblings #23, #24, #25, #26 all married Schenck cousins).\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1679-01-29 b. Flatlands LI; bp. 1679-02-02 Flatbush DRC (Flat 111)\n- 1705-11-12 m. Sarah Schenck at Flatlands (EDSM 29)\n- by 1709 settled Middletown NJ; member Freehold Church 1709\n- 1727-11-01 wife Sarah d.; bur. Golden Farm\n- 1743-07-05 will dated\n- 1744-06-04 d. Middletown NJ, ae. 65-4-6; bur. Golden Farm with wife\n- 1744-07-17 will pro. (NJ Wills 2:115)\n\n### Civic offices\n- (none specifically documented)\n\n### Kin network\n- Wife = his cousin Sarah Schenck (4th and final Cowenhoven-Schenck cousin marriage among Willem cp_fam_007's children).\n- 10 children + 1 d. infant: #158 Jannetie b. 1706-12-10 m. Hendrick Bennett; #159 Annie b. 1708-02 m. John Hendrickson; #160 William b. 1710-02 m. Antje Hendrickson — wife later remarried his cousin William cp_ens_004's son #121; #161 Ruleph b. 1712-03-01 bp. 1713-03-22 m. 1741-08-12 Jannetie Hendrickson (later remarried Peter Schenck #145); #162 Jacob b. 1714-02-01 m. 1742-12-21 cousin Margaret cp_fam_057's son William #168's daughter Margaret Covenhoven; #163 Gerret b. 1716-11-05 bp. 1716-12-23 m. 1744-10-12 Neeltje Schenck (NJ Mar 76); #164 Peter b. 1718-12-14 bp. 1718-12-21 d. 1719-01-04 (infant); #165 Peter b. 1720-05 bp. 1720-05-29 m. 1749-07-27 Catherine Schenck widow of Simeon De Hart; #166 John b. 1722-05-17 bp. 1722-07-15 m. 1750-11-05 Mary Van Dorn; #167 Matthias b. 1725 m. 1749-07-27 Williampe Kouwenhoven (his cousin via cp_ens_004's son William #121's daughter).\n- Children's marriages: 4 of 10 to Hendrickson (Annie+John, William+Antje, Ruleph+Jannetie, possibly Antje route); 3 to Schenck (Gerret+Neeltje, Peter+Catherine, Jacob+Margaret-via-cousin-cluster); plus Bennett, Van Dorn. Massive intra-cluster kin density.\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- 10 children's names: Jannetie (mother cp_fam_061), Annie/Antje (Wyckoff), William (great-grandfather pattern), Ruleph/Roelof (Schenck), Jacob (his own name — patrilineal junior), Gerret (Cowenhoven), Peter (twice — first d. infant), John, Matthias (NEW — possibly Hendrickson route).\n- 'Matthias' enters Cowenhoven name pool here for the first time — Hendrickson connection bears watching.\n\n2026-05-23 PM5: Cocheu Discrepancy Workflow end-to-end pass complete (Steps 1-7). **Stage 2 own-row diff:** cocheu_number=26 + cocheu_page=21 backfilled; birth_date 1679 → 1679-01-29 (Cocheu pins exact); mother filled (cp_fam_061 Jannetje Pieterse Monfoort, 2nd wife of cp_fam_007 per Cocheu); baptism_place CORRECTED — workbook had 'DRC Flatlands (Flat 111)' but Cocheu says 'bp. Flatbush'; the '(Flat 111)' is a CITATION (Flatlands D.R.Ch. Records p.111), not a place. Workbook reading-convention error retroactively fixed. **Stage 4 wire-completion:** 8 Child| tokens appended to related_enslavers (cp_fam_126/127/128/130/131/132/133 + cp_ens_036). All 8 children's reverse Parent|cp_ens_009 already present (verified pre-write). Brings cp_ens_009 to fully bidirectional with all 9 minted children. **Spouse field cleanup:** parents-of-spouse content ('daughter of Roelof Martense Schenck + Annetje Wyckoff') moved to cp_fam_138 row (already present there); verification-history (HYPOTHESIS→MATCH 5/10) consolidated here in notes. **Stage 5 children Cocheu backfill (cross-sheet):** 9 child rows received cocheu_number + cocheu_page + cp_famsou_028 wire (Gen-5 cp_fam Cocheu_Crossref wiring backlog substantively closed for cp_ens_009 line). Mint Queue follow-up: Roelof Martense Schenck + Annetje Pieterse Wyckoff (Sarah Schenck's parents — Tier-1 Schenck + Tier-1 Wyckoff; previously queued for cp_ens_004 spouse-parents context — same parents).",
