      "notable_records": "1743-07-05 will (Lib. D, p. 152, Middletown Township, Monmouth Co., yeoman); proved 1744-07-17. 1744-12-03 inventory (£618.18.8) lists \"six negros, large Bible, 217 bushels Indian corn, books, 32 barrels flour\" plus extensive bonds and book debts from many neighbors (including William Covenhoven of Flat Lands NY and Rulof + Jacob Covenhoven, likely his own sons). Inventory enslaved-people group is UNNAMED — see cp_rec_008. Executors: 3 sons Roeloff + Jacob + Garret. Witnesses: Joseph Goulder, George Crawford, Elias Golden, Charles Henderson. Inventory takers: Samuel Ogborne, Hendrick Hendrickson, Edward Taylor. UPDATE 2026-04-30: Will text specifies named bequest of 'my Negroe Woman Betty' (= cp_per_243) to son Martin Covenhoven (= cp_ens_036, minted research target). cp_eve_015 enslaved_person_ids updated; cp_rec_008 total 6→5.",
