      "occupation": "Yeoman or Boulter (1746 will manuscript reading ambiguous on this descriptor; W5 close-read 2026-05-03 of NYSA J0038-92 SS2 0512 p1 flagged the word as either \"Yeoman\" or \"Boulter\" — flagged for paleographer review). \"Boulter\" = flour-sifter / sieve-maker as a trade.",
      "father_text": "Jan Gerretse Van Couwenhoven (cp_fam_008)",
      "mother_text": "Gerardina (Gerdientje) de Sille (cp_fam_030)",
      "spouse_text": "Elsje Jansen Staats (cp_fam_031; b. 1686-02-07 Flatlands, d. 1749; dau. of Jan Staats b. abt. 1666 + Annetje Praa/Prat) — m. 1703-11-03 Brooklyn RDC",
      "children_summary": "Per 1746 will (NY Wills Liber 17 p.18) + WikiTree snippets: John/Jan Nicasse (cp_ens_007; b.1709-05-01 Brooklyn d.1778-05-01; eldest, inherited Brookland houses/lands + £300 birthright), Gerrit (cp_fam_033; d.1783-11-17; inherited Raritan NJ farm between Andries Ten Eyck and Peter Bodyn lands + stock of horses + £500 already received), Peter/Pieter (cp_fam_034; bp.1712-04-06 NJ, d.1774, m. Leah Schenck 1735-12-17; inherited Raritan NJ plantation where he already lived + £1000 already received), Gerardina 'Dinah' (cp_fam_035; bp.1705-08-07 Breuckelen RDC, d.aft.1757; m. Simon Van Wicklen cp_fam_036 on 1722-11-05; inherited £300). [W5 CORRECTION 2026-05-03: amount updated from \"£3\" to \"£300\" per manuscript NYSA J0038-92 SS2 0512 p2 reading \"the Sum of three hundred pounds Currant Money of New York … for his birthright.\" Liber 17 abstract's \"£3\" was a transcription error — likely a missed trailing zero pair.] | Cocheu 71:3 (cp_sou_049) adds 6th child cp_fam_153 Elsie⁵ bp. New Utrecht 1723-05-29 (not present in 1746 will).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "WikiTree: https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/VanCouwenhoven-24 (via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24); Geni: https://www.geni.com/people/Nicasius-Kouvenhoven/6000000001255006471; NY Surrogate's Office Liber 8 p.275 — named 'Nicesimus Cowenhoven,' brother and co-executor, in Gerret Janse's 1711 will; NY Surrogate's Office Liber 17 p.18 — will of Nicasius Cowenhowen of Brookland, Kings County, boulter, dated 1746-05-15, proved 1749-11-02 (FamilySearch book 111896 pp.248-249: https://www.familysearch.org/library/books/viewer/111896/?offset=0#page=248). Witnesses: Jacob Brewerton, Francis Hegeman, Adrian Hegeman. | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) — Cocheu 71:1 confirms parentage cp_fam_008 + cp_fam_030, b. 1681-06-30 bp. 1681-07-08 Flatbush Flat 120, d. 1749-09-16, m. 1703-11-03 Elsie — | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 (Jul 1940), pp. 273-276 (cp_sou_049)",
      "notes": "Named as co-executor of brother Gerret's 1711 will (rendered there as 'Nicesimus'). 'Nicesimus' = Latinized/scribal form of Dutch **Nicasius** (confirmed by WikiTree); his maternal grandfather Nicasius de Sille was the namesake. Spouse/children not yet entered — flag for follow-up WikiTree read. EXPANDED 2026-04-24 late PM via his own 1746 will (NY Wills Liber 17 p.18): 'boulter' occupation, Brookland residence, wife Elsje Staats and 4 named children, Raritan NJ landholdings passing to sons Gerrit and Peter. Son-in-law surname rendered 'Van Wilderen' in the printed abstract = **Van Wicklen** per WikiTree and his own 1753 will (scribal/transcription variant).\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3)\n- 71:3 confirms residence 'near the Ferry' in Brooklyn (cp_pla_007 The Ferry).\n- Will May 15 1746 / pro Nov 2 1749 (WNYHS 4:239) — Cocheu citation; matches NY Wills Liber 17 p.18 already in record.\n- Adds 6th child: cp_fam_153 Elsie⁵ bp. New Utrecht 1723-05-29.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1681-06-30 b. Flatlands; bp. Flatbush 1681-07-08 (Flat 120)\n- 1703-11-03 m. Brooklyn DRC\n- ca. 1703-1749 resided 'near the Ferry' Brooklyn\n- 1746-05-15 will dated; 1749-09-16 d. Brooklyn ae. 68\n\n## Kin network\n- Wife Elsie Staats (cp_fam_031) — Holland Soc. entry paper confirms Staats surname (added uncertainty Cocheu flags 'an entry paper at the Holland Soc. says family name was Staats').",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_008;Parent|cp_fam_030;Sibling|cp_fam_026;Sibling|cp_fam_076;Sibling|cp_fam_077;Sibling|cp_fam_078;Spouse|cp_fam_031;Child|cp_ens_007;Child|cp_fam_033;Child|cp_fam_034;Child|cp_fam_035;Child|cp_fam_153",
