      "spouse_text": "Jacoba (Cornelisse) Vanderveer — daughter of Cornelius Janse Vanderveer + Trintje DeMandeville; bp. Brooklyn 1686-04-29 (Brkn 158; REC 68:203, per Cocheu 71:2 cp_sou_048).",
      "children_summary": "Nine children with Jacoba Vanderveer per Cocheu 71:2 cp_sou_048:\n  168. William5 = cp_fam_058 (existing) of Penn's Neck NJ, b. 1705-10-25; m. Cacha or Sophia Lane.\n  169. Triinke5, bp. 1709-10-30 (FM); removed to Kentucky [cp_fam Gen-5 stub PENDING Phase B].\n  170. Cornelius5 of Penn's Neck NJ, bp. 1712-04-06 (FM); m. Hannah Schenck [PENDING Phase B].\n  171. Peter5 of Penn's Neck NJ, bp. 1714-12-05 (FM); removed to Kentucky [PENDING Phase B].\n  172. Jan5 = cp_fam_059 (existing John Covenhoven [II]), bp. 1719-04-12 (FM); d. after 1756; m. by lic. 1752-08-14 Lydia Predmore (NJ Mar 76); removed to Kentucky.\n  173. Unnamed child5, bp. 1724-06-07 (FM, child not named in church record) [NOT MINTED — possibly d. young].\n  174. Gerret5, b. Marlborough NJ 1726-04-27, d. 1812-11-01; m.(1) Neeltje Van Mater, m.(2) Antje Schenck [PENDING Phase B].\n  175. Jacob5 of Penn's Neck NJ, b. abt. 1727; removed to Kentucky [PENDING Phase B].\n  176. Dominicus5 = cp_fam_060 (existing Dominicus Janse) of Windsor NJ, b. abt. 1730; m. Mary Updike. NOTE: workbook prior had cp_fam_060 birth as 1724 (FS HYPOTHESIS) but Cocheu 71:2 places Dominicus's b. as 'abt. 1730' — reconciliation needed; the 1724 baptism may correspond to unnamed #173 instead.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "1756 will: Jan Kouwenhoven of Freehold, Monmouth Co., NJ; written 23 Nov 1756, proved 29 Dec 1756 (NJ Abstracts of Wills, vol. ~XXXII 1751–1760). | FamilySearch profile LTK3-3Q5. | LAND-sheet rows: cp_lan_027 (1737 Penn estate, 6,500 ac), cp_lan_029 (1738 → John [II]), cp_lan_030 (1738 → William), cp_lan_039 (1751 → Dominicus). | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) — Cocheu 71:1 confirms parentage cp_fam_007 + cp_fam_061, b. 1681-04-09 bp. 1681-04-11 Flat 120, m. abt. 1704 Coba Vanderveer (#27 in Willem family Bible numbering) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048)",
      "notes": "Penn's Neck cluster founder (LAND cp_lan_027–_039). Resident Freehold but held Middlesex/Penn's Neck investment land 1737–1751. Joint 1737 grantee with Garret Schenck (Schenck-Vanderveer-Couwenhoven kin network). Wife Jacoba Vanderveer's family ties may explain Schenck partnership. Default cp_fam_### because 1756 will abstract names no enslaved persons; ENSLAVER promotion pending full will text.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1681-04-09 b. Flatlands; bp. 1681-04-11 Flatbush DRC (Flat 120)\n- 1704 abt. m. Jacoba Vanderveer (then in Brooklyn)\n- 1705-10-25 son William #168 born — still in NY at this date\n- between 1705 and 1709 family removed Flatlands → Monmouth Co. NJ (per EDSM 34)\n- 1709 first child bp. in NJ (#169 Triinke 1709-10-30 FM)\n- 1712, 1714, 1719, 1724, 1726 children bp. NJ (Marlborough / Freehold-Middletown)\n- 1756-11-23 will dated; 1756-12-29 will pro. NJ Wills 3:187\n\n### Civic offices\n- (none specifically documented in Cocheu 71:2 — was a yeoman / Penn's Neck-area landholder)\n\n### Kin network — NJ migration cluster\n- One of FIVE Willem-Gerretse-line siblings who migrated to NJ between abt. 1695 (sister Sara cp_fam_071) and 1709: cp_fam_069 Pieter (Freehold), cp_ens_004 Cornelis (Middletown), cp_fam_071 Sara (Schenck-Couwenhoven cluster), cp_ens_002 Albert (Pleasant Valley), cp_ens_009 Jacob (Middletown / Golden Farm), cp_fam_057 John (Penn's Neck), cp_fam_074 Annetje (Monmouth via Williamsen marriage). This is the FOUNDATIONAL Cowenhoven NJ cluster.\n- Wife Jacoba Vanderveer's parents: Cornelius Janse Vanderveer + Trintje DeMandeville — Vanderveer in-law surname enters NJ Cowenhoven kin network here.\n- 4 of 9 children removed to Kentucky (Triinke, Peter, Jacob — and possibly Cornelius's descendants) — early NJ-to-KY migration signal.\n- Children's settlements: Penn's Neck (William, Cornelius, Peter, Jacob = 4 of 9); Windsor (Dominicus); Marlborough (Gerret).\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- His sons named for Cowenhoven patrilineal core (William, Cornelius, Peter, Jan, Gerret, Jacob) + Dominicus (new — possibly maternal Vanderveer or DeMandeville route).\n- Daughter Triinke = Trintje, named for maternal grandmother Trintje DeMandeville. Maternal-grandmother naming.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_007;Parent|cp_fam_061;Half-sibling|cp_fam_066;Sibling|cp_fam_054;Sibling|cp_fam_067;Sibling|cp_fam_068;Sibling|cp_fam_069;Sibling|cp_ens_004;Sibling|cp_fam_071;Sibling|cp_ens_002;Sibling|cp_ens_009;Sibling|cp_fam_074;Sibling|cp_fam_075;Spouse|Jacoba Cornelisse Vanderveer (not minted);Child|cp_fam_058;Child|cp_fam_135;Child|cp_fam_136;Child|cp_fam_137;Child|cp_fam_059;Child|cp_ens_051;Child|cp_fam_139;Child|cp_fam_060;Spouse|cp_fam_072",
