      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #28. Both marriages noted as 'supposed' by Cocheu — confidence may be < MATCH; flag for primary verification later.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1683-04-13 b. Flatlands LI; bp. 1683-04-22 Flatbush DRC (Flat 120)\n- 1704-11-11 m.(1 sup.) Aert Willemse — moved to Monmouth Co. NJ\n- m.(2 sup.) Johannes Antonides Monmouth Co. NJ\n\n### Civic offices\n- (none — wife)\n\n### Kin network\n- 4 children with Aert Willemse (Williamsen surname; NOT minted as cp_fam): #177 William b. 1709-02-18 m. cousin Aeltje cp_fam_069's daughter #116 (Cowenhoven cousin marriage closes a kin loop); #178 Jannetje m. abt. 1732 Leffert Leffertse (EDSM 108); #179 Aeltje m. 1737-12-02 William Barcalow bp. 1714-01-16 son of Derrick Barcalow + Jane Van Arsdale (= cp_fam_067's daughter Jannetje #93 — another cousin marriage closure); #180 Neltje bp. 1720-10-16 d. 1771-11-06 ae. 51-1-13 m. 1742-12-28 Peter Forman son of Jonathan Forman + Margaret Wyckoff (via Forman = cp_fam_068 Neeltje Wyckoff's daughter Geertie's husband Jonathan's nephew? — Forman cluster).\n- ALL 4 children's marriages closed cousin-loops back into Cowenhoven kin: William→cousin Aeltje, Aeltje→cousin via Barkaloo+Van Arsdale, Neltje→cousin via Forman+Wyckoff. Indicative of tight intra-cluster marriage network in early NJ migration generation.\n- 2nd marriage Johannes Antonides — Antonides surname enters Cowenhoven cluster; Cocheu also has Johannes Antonides (#111 Hannah's husband from cp_fam_069 line). Same Antonides? Possibly — flag for primary verification.\n\n### Naming pattern signals\n- (Annetje's children all Williamsen surname; minimal Cowenhoven name carriage through her direct line.)",
