      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 (Jul 1940), pp. 273-276 (cp_sou_049)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #30. Married same date 1709-06-05 as her brother William cp_fam_054 (#29) — joint sibling wedding.\n\n## COCHEU 71:2 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_048)\n\n### Geographic timeline\n- 1689-12-28 b. Flatlands LI\n- 1709-06-05 m. Elbert Willemsen (joint sibling wedding with brother William cp_fam_054 same date)\n\n### Civic offices / Kin network\n- (Cocheu 71:2 provides no further detail; her issue covered in later articles if any.)\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3)\n- Marriage at Flatbush 1709-06-05 (Flatb 96), same date as her brother cp_fam_054's marriage — possible double-wedding ceremony.\n- Williamsen family migrated NJ; children associated with Freehold and Brick Church Marlborough (NJ cluster anchor).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- 1689-12-28 b. Flatlands LI\n- 1709-06-05 m. Flatbush DRC\n- ca. 1717 Williamsen family in Brick Church Marlborough NJ rolls\n\n## Kin network\n- Williamsen line: son #193 Elbert m. Willemtje Schenck (1752) → Schenck cousin link via cp_fam_009 line.\n- Brings Williamsen surname into Cowenhoven kin-network (relevant to disambiguation of any later Williamsen-Cowenhoven matches).",
