      "spouse_text": "Frans Cowenhoven (cp_fam_037) — m. 1727-11-12 NYC RDC (her 1st marriage; not Frans's first — he was 52 and a widower; she's likely substantially younger). Predeceased Frans before 1745.",
      "children_summary": "Martha (cp_fam_040) — biological relationship to Mary supported by will's bequest pattern (silver from Mary's prior ownership passes to Martha). Maternal relationship to Frans's \"natural son\" Samuel (cp_fam_039) is NOT indicated (the will's phrasing distinguishes Samuel from Frans's marriage to Mary).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "NY Surrogate's Office Liber 16 p.400 — will of Frans Cowenhoven (FamilySearch book 111896 p.208) mentions her as 'my late wife Mary' and her silver tankard + 3 spoons; Genealogy.com forum 'CAPT. JOHN FRED and MARTHA' thread (https://www.genealogy.com/forum/surnames/topics/fred/76/) references a Mary Jansen married to Francois-Fran Van Couwenhouven after prior marriages — UNVERIFIED secondary source. | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050)",
      "notes": "Named only as 'Mary' in husband Frans's 1745 will abstract; full name 'Mary Jansen' and prior-marriage hypothesis come from an unverified genealogy.com forum snippet. Owned silver tankard + 3 spoons before marrying Frans, suggesting she brought assets from a prior relationship. Follow-up: verify maiden name, prior marriage(s), and whether Martha was biological daughter or stepdaughter of Frans.\n\n## CORRECTION via Cocheu 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — wife of Frans (cp_fam_037)\nPRE-71:4 workbook entry: 'Mary Jansen' — based on a genealogy.com forum snippet referencing Herring-Cowenhoven family network with hypothetical prior marriages.\nREVISED via Cocheu 71:4 #72 (citing MDC 147 — Manhattan RDC marriage register, primary): wife's name = Maria Brouwn (Brown), m. NY 1727-11-12. The Mary Jansen identification + Herring-prior-marriage hypothesis are both NOT supported by primary records.\nDaughter Martha (cp_fam_040) — Cocheu lists her as Frans's biological daughter (no Herring step-relationship).\n\n## Key implications\n- Maiden surname Brouwn (Brown) — likely a NYC RDC Dutch-English family. Need primary baptism record to verify parents.\n- Frans had THREE marriages (Cocheu 71:4): Catharine Olivier 1709 (cp_fam_155), Maria Brouwn 1727 (this row), Hillegond Bogart 1746 (cp_fam_156).\n- The silver tankard + 3 spoons mentioned in Frans's 1745 will as 'which did belong to my late wife Mary, before our marriage' = Maria Brouwn's, NOT Mary Jansen's.\n\n## Open follow-up\n- Verify Maria Brouwn's parents via Manhattan RDC baptism register (BDC).\n- Confirm whether Martha (cp_fam_040) was daughter of Catharine Olivier (1st wife, more likely based on age) or Maria Brouwn (2nd wife).",
