      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #35.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3)\n- Cocheu flags chronological inconsistency in standard authorities: m. 1694/1695 vs. d. husband 1697 with 4 children — open question.\n- Son #223 Jacob Rapelje of Raritan NJ m. Sarah Brinckerhoff — possible Brinckerhoff cousin link via cp_fam_076's Brinckerhoff children (Sarah may be a Brinckerhoff descendant of Aeltie Stryker line, but unclear without further research).\n\n## Geographic timeline\n- b. 'At the Ferry' Brooklyn (cp_pla_007)\n- 1695-07-27 m. Brooklyn DRC\n- ca. 1695-1697 family Cripplebush LI (cp_pla_027) where husband died\n\n## Kin network\n- Rapelje cluster — 4 children, 1 to NJ (#223 Raritan), 2 stayed Brooklyn/Wallabout area.",
