      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050) | Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 (Jul 1952), pp. 147-156 (cp_sou_058)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #88. NJ Conover-line; Adams family kin connection — bears watching for Conover-Adams cluster.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_050 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 #88)\nBrother of cp_fam_087 Peter Sr. — both at Great Egg Harbor NJ. Pieter-branch NJ Anglo-Quaker cluster.\nWill 1762-05-19 / pro 1771-03-26 (NJWills 5:112).\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n- 'Jeremiah' = wife's father's name (Jeremiah Adams) — affinal naming pattern.\n- 'Joseph', 'Joseph Dale' = English-Anglican-Quaker pattern (continues sibling cp_fam_087's similar pattern).\n- 'Rebecah' = wife's mother's name. Strong Adams-side naming influence.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #88)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #88 — substantial enrichment:\n\n## Will + estate\n- Will dated 1762-05-19 / proved 1771-03-26 (NJA:34:112).\n- Executors: wife Sarah + son John (cp_fam_180).\n- Witnesses: John Ingersoll, Micajah Conover (cp_fam_177 nephew), Rebecca Risley.\n\n## Spouse provenance\n- Wife Sarah Adams — daughter of Jeremiah and Rebecca Adams, and a GREAT-GRANDDAUGHTER of Jeremy Adams of Hartford, Connecticut. New England Puritan kin connection. Referred to as \"Sarah Conover\" in her mother's will (NJA:32:6).\n\n## Kin network signal\n- Sister Mary⁴ (cp_fam_091) married John Adams (son of Jonathan + Barbara) — likely a kin loop within the same Adams family.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_024;Sibling|cp_fam_087;Sibling|cp_fam_089;Sibling|cp_fam_090;Sibling|cp_fam_091;Spouse|Sarah Adams;Child|cp_fam_180;Child|cp_fam_181;Child|cp_fam_182;Child|cp_fam_183;Child|cp_fam_184;Child|cp_fam_185;Child|cp_fam_186",
