      "children_summary": "1 known Risley child (matriline; not minted as cp_fam) per Cocheu 71:4 #295: (295) Jemima Risley b. 1720, m. 1738-05-04 Edward Higbee. Cocheu adds parenthetical: '(Perhaps others.)' — i.e., other children may exist.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050) | Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 (Jul 1952), pp. 147-156 (cp_sou_058)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #90. NJ Conover-line via mother. Named for grandmother cp_fam_018 Hester Pieterse (Pieter cp_fam_005's daughter by Hester Symons).\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_050 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 #90)\nMinimal entry. Higbee family marriage = NJ Anglo-Quaker pattern.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #90)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #90 — massive expansion of children's list (was only 1 known; now 8 listed):\n\n## Spouse + in-law family\n- m. Richard Risley of Egg Harbour Township — son of Richard + Rebecca (Adams) Risley, GRANDSON of Richard Risley of Hartford, Connecticut.\n- His will dated 1737-05-02 / proved 1740-06-17 (NJA:30:401). Hester ('Esther') named sole executrix.\n- Witnesses: Frederick Steelman, John Conover, David Lindsey.\n\n## 8 Risley children (matriline; not minted as cp_fam)\n(i) Peter Risley b.-; m. 1736-01-22 Mrs. Ann (Mann) Carman (NJA:30:85; Cape May Co. Mar.:11). His own will 1759-11-19 / pro. 1767-01-15 named wife Ann + son Richard executors (NJA:33:355-56). 8 children: Peter (b.1739), Richard (b.1742), Ann (b.1744 m. Nehemiah Leeds), Margaret (b.1747), Sarah (b.1750), Elizabeth (b.1752 m. Joseph Estell), Sophia (b.1754 m. Frederick Steelman), Leah (b.1757 m. James Holmes then Abner Doughty).\n(ii) Richard Risley b.-; will 1767-01-15 / pro. 1767-02-20. 4 children: Richard, Thomas (m. Mary Leeds c.1767), Morris (1746-1802 m. Jemima Lake), Rebecca.\n(iii) Thomas Risley b.-; d. intestate, no issue. Admin 1764-09-14 to Peter Risley (NJA:33:356).\n(iv) Mary Risley b.-; m. by 1736-07-17 license John Steelman ('spinster of Great Egg Harbour'; NJA:22:334).\n(v) Jemimah Risley b. 1718-20; m. 1738-05-04 license Edward Higbee (NJA:22:334), son of John + Alice (Andrews) Higbee. d. before 1781-05-20. 6 children: John (b.1739), Sarah (b.~1740 m. John Smith), Edward (b.1741), Alice (b.~1750 m. Thomas Somers), Jeremiah (b.1751-07-05 m. Esther Smith 1773), Richard (b.1753 m. Abigail Steelman 1780).\n(vi) Esther Risley b.-; d. 1786 (inv. 1786-07-22 NJA:36:210). m. 1744-02-09 license John Somers (NJA:22:334), b. 1723-12-30, son of James + Abigail (Adams) Somers. His will 1775-01-10 / pro. 1783-06-23 (NJA:35:365). 7 children: James (b.1745), Thomas (b.1750 m. Alice Higbee 1780), John (b.1759 m. Hannah McLean 1788), Jeremiah, David, Esther (b.1770 m. John Roberts 1789), Abigail (m. Samuel Risley 1784).\n(vii) Sarah Risley b.-; under 21 in uncle Thomas Risley's 1740 will (NJA:30:401).\n(viii) Rebecca Risley b.-; youngest dau. in same uncle's will.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_024;Sibling|cp_fam_087;Sibling|cp_fam_088;Sibling|cp_fam_089;Sibling|cp_fam_091;Spouse|Richard Risley",
