      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:1 (Jan 1940), pp. 69-74 (cp_sou_047) | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050) | Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 (Jul 1952), pp. 147-156 (cp_sou_058)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:1 (cp_sou_047) #91. Named for her mother Mary. Adams kin connection (sister-in-law to her brother John #88's wife Sarah Adams — likely Adams kin loop).\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_050 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 #91)\nd. 1808 (long life — likely b. 1700-1715). m. John Adams (b. ~1700). Adams = English/Anglo NJ family. Note: this is NOT the same Adams family as her brother cp_fam_088 John's wife Sarah Adams (separate Adams lines).\nAdams children's names = English Anglo-Quaker pattern — continues Pieter-branch NJ Great Egg Harbor cluster naming convention.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #91)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #91 — death-date correction + spouse provenance + 3 Adams children:\n\n## Death date DISCREPANCY\n- 83:3: \"Mary Covenhoven probably died before Sept. 24, 1770, as her name does not appear on deeds of that date when her husband [John Adams] conveyed his property to their three sons\" (Glou. Co. Deeds:1:31).\n- Workbook currently shows '1808' — likely a transcription/confusion error. Flagging here; consider field update with HYPOTHESIS flag if no contradicting source.\n\n## Spouse provenance\n- John Adams was son of Jonathan + Barbara Adams (per Rec. v.80, pp.245-46). m. before 1731-12-07 (her mother Mary Gale's will of that date names her 'daughter Mary Adams', NJA:30:191).\n\n## 3 Adams children (matriline; not minted as cp_fam) — substantial detail in 83:3\n(303) John Adams b.-; m. Margaret Garwood b. 1740-09-30, dau. of Thomas + Mary (Ballenger) Garwood. Ensign Rev War (Stryker:448). Will 1797-08-25 / pro. 1798-04-17 (NJA:38:8-9) names 10 children + 2 more known from Atlantic Co. Hist. Soc. Year Book: Mary (1764), Hannah (1765 m. Solomon Mannery), Daniel (1767 d.y.), John (1769 m. Ruth Ireland), Joshua (1771 m. Sarah Boice), Daniel (1773 m. Sarah Chamberlain then Elizabeth Goodbartlett), Abigail (1775 m. John Lake 1796), Jesse (1777 m. Deborah Ireland 1800), Thomas (1780 m. Mary Ely 1805), Margaret (1783 m. Amariah Lake 1801), William (1787 m. Sarah Steelman), Bevinas (1789).\n(304) Jonathan Adams b. 1735-01-06; soldier Rev War (Stryker:485); m. Mary Scull (widow of Ebenezer Ingersoll). Will 1806-12-15 / pro. 1808-06-30 (NJA:40:6). 6 children: Richard (1759-1805 m. Rebecca Ireland 1784), John, Thomas, Milly, Edmond, Sarah.\n(305) Elijah Adams b.-; d. before 1808-01-09. m. Elizabeth — (who later m. James Whiley). 1 known son Jeremiah Adams b.~1780 d. 1857-11-11; m. 1803-01-22 Elizabeth Ireland b. 1786-09-13 d. 1860-04-10, daughter of Clement Ireland + Deborah Conover (cp_fam_177's daughter Deborah, Cocheu #724) — KIN LOOP back to Pieter branch via Micajah⁵ line.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_024;Sibling|cp_fam_087;Sibling|cp_fam_088;Sibling|cp_fam_089;Sibling|cp_fam_090;Spouse|John Adams",
