      "notes": "Cocheu 71:2 #125. Three marriages.\n\n## COCHEU 81:4 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_053) — Cocheu's #125\nThree marriages. Husband (2) Abraham Vandeventer's will 1733-04-25, proved 1733-12-11 (NJA:30:496) names \"wife Altje, her daughter Mary Van Doren, son Peter; **executors father-in-law Cornelius Covenhoven [= cp_ens_004] + brother Isaac Vandeventer**; witnesses Jacob Vandeventer + Roelof Covenhoven (= cp_fam_104) + John Bowne.\" This is **the proof-of-parentage anchor** that Cornelis Willemse Couwenhoven = cp_ens_004 is parent of all #121-#132.\n\nHusband (3) Cornelius Middagh's will dated 1776-11-13 / proved 1778-02-24 (NJA:34:345) — Altje survived him.\n\n## 2 children (1 by each of 1st + 2nd marriages)\n- #396 Mary Van Doren b after 1720 (vD:539) m. her second cousin Albert Covenhoven #442\n- #397 Peter Vandeventer bp 1732-04-16 Freehold-Middletown DRC — believed to have gone to Pennsylvania (Schenck Gen 1883 p.143; Van Doren Fam 1909 pp.71+539; Vandeventer Fam 1943 pp.21+57)",
