      "notes": "Cocheu 71:2 #115. Founder of the Englishtown NJ branch. Will 1777 pro. mid-Revolutionary War (NJ Wills 5:112).\n\n## COCHEU 81:3 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_052) — Cocheu's #115\n- Born 1703-07-11, died 1777-05-03 in Freehold NJ\n- Married 1724-05-01 (or 1725) Mary Theodorus Colyer — buried Old Tennent Cem cp_pla_073\n- Will dated 1777-04-10, proved 1777-05-20: NJA:34:112 — names sons Peter, Theodorus, William, John; daughters Catharine, Mary, Patience, Neltje; granddaughters Lydia + Catharine (children of son Peter); executors: sons Theodorus + William + son-in-law Peter Schenck; witnesses: William A. Covenhoven Jr. + John Jewell + John Morford\n- 11 Gen-6 children minted in Cocheu as #336-#346:\n  - #336 Peter b 1726-05-01 m. 1749 Anne Davis (d. of Thomas + Anne Davis) — 7 children\n  - #337 Catharine b 1727-10-11 bp Freehold-Middletown 1728-01-01\n  - #338 Patience b 1729-04-24\n  - #339 Mary b 1731-06-04 m. 1753-06-18 cousin Squire Petrus Schenck #331 = son of cp_fam_095 + Koert Schenck\n  - #340 Theodorus b 1733-05-24 d 1825-12-10 Old Tennent Cem (NJMis:2:323) — never named wife/children in his own 1815 will\n  - #341 William b 1735-08-13 d 1823-02-13 m. 1767-11-12 Altia Jewell (b 1844 ERROR in Cocheu, prob. 1744; d 1813-03-04 ae 69) — Englishtown NJ farmer, owned Gib Hendrickson farms + mill\n  - #342 Samuel b 1738-08-27 d 1760\n  - #343 Neltje b 1742-03-31 m. ~1762 William LaRue (d 1811-01-12)\n  - #344 Sarah b 1744-06-21 — prob. d before 1777\n  - **#345 John** b 1746-07-11 d 1824-11-03 m. 1770-01-12 Mary Aiken — **Capt. John Walton's NJ Light Dragoons (Revolution)** — bur Old Tennent. (MINTED as cp_fam_198 in this commit.)\n  - #346 Joseph b 1749-07-17 — prob. dy\n- Burial cluster: Old Tennent Cemetery (cp_pla_073) — major Pieter-Willemse line anchor",
