      "spouse_text": "Christina (or Sophia) Lane — bap. 1710-11-26 Marlboro Dutch Church; d. 1787-06-24 age 78; daughter of Cornelius Lane. m. ~1732 (per Cocheu 82:3 #168 [cp_sou_056]). **CORRECTION 2026-05-10**: prior workbook hypothesis \"Catherine Dye, m. 1764 Middlesex\" was wrong — that 1764-08-25 marriage was William's NEPHEW William #549 (son of #170 Cornelius, who emigrated to Mohawk Valley). Removed per Cocheu 82:3 cross-reference.",
      "children_summary": "10 children (per Cocheu 82:3 #168 [cp_sou_056], will dated 1764-11-16 NJA:33:93 names: John, Cornelius, William, Peter, Hermanus, Gilbert, Jacob, Dominicus, Mary [m. Jacob Schenck], Jacoba): (i) John⁶ #538 bap. 1734-10-27 FM, executor of father's will (eldest son), Rev War Pvt Middlesex Co. Militia, of West Windsor, will 1807-05-13 / proved 1815-10-17 NJA:42:103, named son William + son-in-law William Tindall as executors; (ii) Cornelius⁶ #539 bap. 1736-05-30, d. 1787 age 51, bur. Penn's Neck Cem; (iii) William⁶ #540 b. 1738-06-23, m. Lydia Baylis, inventory 1778-09-10 NJA:35:112; (iv) Hermanus (Harmen)⁶ #541 b. 1740-06-05 d. 1804-01-04 age 63y 7m, m. 1764-08-05 Phoebe Bailey b. 1744-04-17 d. 1832-02-02 age 87y 9m 16d, both bur. Penn's Neck Cem (cp_pla_074), will 1803-11-21 / proved 1804-01-21 NJA:39:102 — **MINTED as new ENSLAVER row in Stage 3b**; (v) Peter⁶ #542 b. 1743-10-18 d. 1831 (South Amboy NJ), m. ~1770 Phoebe Dey b. 1748-11-18 d. 1826-05-14 (bur. Cranbury Cem cp_pla_075), Rev War Pvt Capt. Gardiner's Co NJ Militia, will 1825-08-29 / proved 1831-08-20 Trenton Wills 11475L, 10 children incl John P. b. 1778 (m. Lydia Duncan, bur. Cranbury Cem); (vi) Gilbert⁶ #543, m. Rebecca Chambers (daughter of Joseph Chambers of Trenton, will 1777 NJA:34:88); (vii) Jacob⁶ #544, m. 1787-12-13 FM Jemima Williamson; (viii) Dominicus⁶ #545 d. 1805-06, will 1805-10-20 / proved 1806-12-06 NJA:40:82 (of South Brunswick Middlesex Co; named sister Mary Slayback + 5 Mershon nieces/nephews — son apparently predeceased him); (ix) Mary⁶ #546, m.(1) Jacob Schenck of Penn's Neck (bap. 1726-05-01 d. 1768-12-19, son of Roelof + Engeltje Van Doren Schenck), m.(2) John Slayback; (x) Jacoba⁶ #547.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu, Lincoln C. \"The Van Kouwenhoven-Conover Family.\" NYG&BR vol. LXXXII, no. 3 (July 1951): #168 (cp_sou_056). Earlier: Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (cp_sou_048). 1764 Will: NJA:33:93. 1738 Penn's Neck land grant: cp_lan_027-039 cluster. FS L1WB-PR7.",
      "notes": "Eldest son of John Willemse per 1756 father's will. Received Penn's Neck sundry tracts by 1738 deed at age ~33. Distinct from cp_ens_011 William Albertse (Freehold cousin) and cp_ens_026 William Kouwenhoven (Flatlands b. 1758). 1764 Catherine Dye marriage may be 2nd marriage; 1st-marriage data not yet confirmed.\n\n[2026-05-10 per Cocheu 82:3 #168 / cp_sou_056] **Major enrichment + spouse correction**. (1) Spouse changed from \"(unknown for 1st; possible 2nd: Catherine Dye HYPOTHESIS)\" to Christina Lane bap. 1710-11-26 d. 1787-06-24, daughter of Cornelius Lane. The \"Catherine Dye 1764 Middlesex\" record was misattributed: it was the marriage of nephew William #549 (son of #170 Cornelius, who emigrated to Mohawk Valley NY). (2) 10 children fully enumerated. (3) Hermanus #541 minted as ENSLAVER (Stage 3b) — establishes father chain for cp_ens_054 (1814 Phebe + Eliza HC defendant) as: Wolphert > Gerrit > Willem > John > William of Penn's Neck (this row) > Hermanus > William of West Windsor (cp_ens_054). (4) Burial at Old Penn's Neck Cem (cp_pla_074, minted Stage F). (5) Will NJA:33:93 flagged for Stage 4 pull to confirm enslavement.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_057;Spouse|Christina Lane (daughter of Cornelius Lane);Sibling|cp_fam_059 John [II];Sibling|cp_fam_060 Dominicus;Sibling|cp_fam_135 Triinke;Sibling|cp_fam_136 Cornelius (Mohawk Valley);Sibling|cp_fam_137 Peter;Sibling|cp_fam_139 Jacob;Sibling|cp_ens_051 Garret Esq.",
