      "notes": "Cocheu 71:2 #124. **Roelof** name = direct Schenck-route via maternal grandfather Roelof Martense Schenck. Strong onomastic evidence of Schenck inheritance.\n\n## COCHEU 81:4 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_053) — Cocheu's #124\nRoelof + Sarah both bur. Schenck-Covenhoven Cem cp_pla_063.\n\n## 4 children\n- #392 Margaret b 1734-05-06 d 1739-01-21\n- #393 Mary b 1737-07-16 d 1767-11-08 ae 30-3-22 m. 1754-12-25 Daniel Van Mater (b 1728-01-23 d 1786-10-08 in London) — 5 children\n- **#394 Cornelius R.** b 1740-07-29 d 1796-07-12 ae 55-11-14 — m. 1758-12-05 Jannetje Denyse (b 1740-08-19 d 1799-03-26). **MINTED as cp_fam_201 in this commit.** — 10 children all bp Freehold-Middletown DRC including Cornelius R. (b 1783-05-03 m. Mary Stoutenburg) which extends the line to Gen 7.\n- **#395 Sarah** b 1744-07-23 d 1805-11-16 ae 61-3-24 — m. 1762-01-05 Gerrit Schenck (b 1743-10-24 d 1797-09-29 ae 53-11-5; son of cp_fam_187 #233 Gerrit Schenck + cp_fam_146 Jannetje Covenhoven #184 — Schenck-Cowenhoven cousin marriage). Both blind in later life. Bur Schenck-Covenhoven Cem. **MINTED as cp_fam_202 in this commit.** — 9 children including Maria b 1773-12-14 m. Garret I. Conover (son of #174 Gerrit Covenhoven cp_fam_? + Neeltje Van Mater).",
