      "children_summary": "12 children per FS LKCH-5W3: Mary 1730-1802 (L69X-5Q1); Peter 1732-1802 (MJ33-KMJ); John Elias [=cp_ens_020] 1734-1803 (GJ7Y-PV2); Patience 1736-1802 (L69X-5W8); Lydia 1738-1805 (MMHK-1ZD); Jannetje 'Jane' 1739-1785 (M5BR-177); James 1739 (M9FF-G4X); Neeltje 1741-1765 (MR4H-CVM); Eleanor 1741-1765 (KF5R-NDK); Sarah 1743-1801 (GPVZ-6FZ); Daniel 1746 (KPHM-B6C); Aaltja 1748 (KPH9-M4J). 1750 will (Lib. E p. 478) names 7 children + unborn child (sex unknown).",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_044",
      "sources": "NJ Wills, Liber E, p. 478 (will dated 1750-12-15, proved 1751-01-30 modern / 1750-01-30 Old Style); FamilySearch LKCH-5W3 (https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/LKCH-5W3); cp_eve_010; cp_rec_006",
      "notes": "Confirmed identity 2026-05-05 via FS LKCH-5W3 + 1750 will abstract (Lib. E p. 478). Born 1707, son of Pieter Willemse Van Couwenhoven (1671-1751) and Patience Daws (1674-1743) in the Flatlands NY → Monmouth NJ Cowenhoven migration line. Married Willemse Wall 1729 Monmouth NJ. 12 children on FS; will (dated 1750-12-15, proved 1751-01-30 modern) names 7 + unborn child. Father Pieter Willemse outlived him by ~6 months. DOWNSTREAM AUDIT: 1772 manumitter Elias (cp_eve_091) NOT among 12 FS children — likely a nephew via brother Peter Pieterse Covenhoven; cp_eve_091's John Covenhoven co-bondsman is hypothesized = cp_ens_020 son John (age 38 in 1772, Freehold Twp Monmouth).\n\n## CONSOLIDATED FROM cp_ens_044 (audit 2026-05-10)\nFAMILY-row enrichment merged into this ENSLAVER row; original FAMILY row deleted. Original FAMILY notes preserved below.\n\nCocheu 71:2 #117. **Elias** = first appearance of name in Cowenhoven line (after maternal grandfather Elias Daws of Gravesend).\n\n## COCHEU 81:3 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_052) — Cocheu's #117\nElias of Middletown NJ — full Cocheu match:\n- Born 1706-09-12; died 1750-12-25 (Cocheu primary supersedes earlier 'before 1750-12-15' bracket)\n- Married 1729 Williampe Wall (b 1709-03-24 d 1759-03-24 her 50th birthday) — daughter of John + Mary Hubbard Wall\n- Will dated 1750-12-15, proved 1751-01-30 (NJA:30:115): names wife (unnamed), children Peter + John + Patience + Lydia + Jane + Sarah + Anne + unborn child; executors brother Peter Conover (= cp_fam_099 = #119) + John Longstreet of Freehold (#120's husband) + brother-in-law John Wall of Middletown; witnesses Roelef Covenhoven (= cp_fam_104 cousin) + Gerrit Schenck #233 (= cp_fam_187)\n- Buried Schenck-Covenhoven Cemetery cp_pla_063 (HOT:207)\n\n## 10 Gen-6 children minted in Cocheu as #353-#362:\n- #353 Mary b 1730-02-12 bp 1731-03-31 (as Marga) — perh. m. John Schenck\n- **#355 John** b 1733-03-08 Middletown d 1803-04-23 = **cp_ens_020** (ENSLAVER cross-match confirmed). Married (1) 1755-12-08 Eleanor Wyckoff (b 1732 or 1737, d 1793-08-26; dau. of William + Agnes Van Doren Wyckoff); (2) Mrs. Eleanor (Neeltje) Williamson Fields #351 (b 1743-09-30 d ~1830, dau. of cp_fam_097 Aeltie + William Williamson; widow of Michael Fields). **Major civic figure: NJ Provincial Assembly + Council of Safety 1775-76.** Will 1802-12-14 / 1803-05-13 (NJA:39:102): wife Eleanor + son Elias + daughter Agnes + grandchildren John Covenhoven + Eleanor + Kitty Remsen.\n- #356 Patience b 1736-07-06 d 1802-05-29 m. 1754-09-03 Samuel Bowne (b 1722 d 1799-03-11) — 12 children\n- #357 Lydia b 1738-03-11 d 1805-03-16 m. 1757-03-07 Hendrick Hendrickson (Judge Monmouth Co.; b 1737-04-23 d 1811-10-11; bur Holmdel)\n- #358 Jane b 1739-12-30 m. 1765-12-19 Peter Longstreet #374 (cousin via cp_fam_100)\n- #359 Sarah (mentioned in 1750 will)\n- #360 Daniel bp 1746-08-03\n- #361 Altje bp 1748-05-08 d 1765-06-21 (prob. the 'Anne' in father's will)\n- #362 Neeltje bp 1751-05-26 (the 'unborn child' of 1750 will)",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Son: cp_ens_020 John Elias Covenhoven (1734-1803). Brother + will-executor: Peter Pieterse Covenhoven 1712-1774 (FS LKCC-FB8) — not yet on ENSLAVER sheet — his son Elias = cp_ens_045 (1751-1786, FS LKCH-534), nephew + namesake of cp_ens_044. Brother-in-law + will-executor: John Wall of Middletown — not yet on ENSLAVER sheet. Will-witness Roelyf Covenhoven likely a cousin or nephew. Grandson via cp_ens_020: cp_ens_046 Col Elias Covenhoven 1757-1820 (FS KLQS-ZTM). Great-grandson via cp_ens_020 → cp_ens_046: cp_ens_047 Elias Covenhoven jr. 1790-1826 (FS KLQS-8VM).; Child|cp_ens_020",
