      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_010",
      "sources": "Cocheu, Lincoln C. \"The Van Kouwenhoven-Conover Family.\" NYG&BR vol. LXXXII, no. 2 (April 1951): #161 (cp_sou_055). Earlier reference: Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 #161 (cp_sou_048). Original probate: New Jersey, Published Archives Series, First Series, Volume XXX, Abstracts of Wills, 1730-1750, p.116; Trenton, NJ State Archives.",
      "notes": "Cocheu 82:2 #161 (cp_sou_055) confirms identity beyond hypothesis: birth, marriage, death, spouse, three children all primary-source documented. Death date 1746 (admin Oct 24, 1746) supersedes prior 1742 conjecture. PID consolidation 2026-05-10: cp_fam_129 (later mint, 2026-05-09) absorbed into cp_ens_010 (older PID, 2026-04-25) per single-sheet + older-PID rule. Pre-consolidation cp_fam_129 row content preserved in this row. **Roelof** = Schenck-route via maternal great-grandfather; same first name as cp_fam_104 (cp_ens_004 line) and cp_fam_115 (cp_ens_002 line) — 3 cousin Roelofs in Gen 5. Cocheu Discrepancy Workflow pass 2026-05-23 PM7 (cp_ens_010): cocheu_page corrected 22→56 (p.22 was short-ref within Jacob #26's child-list; main entry on p.56). place_FK wiring: birth/death/residence wired (cp_pla_012 Monmouth Co; cp_pla_023 Middletown Twp). Step 4.5 Duplicate-Signature Check: clean (4.5a EVENT 0 pairs; 4.5b token-dupe 0; 4.5c ENS↔FAM split 0). Mint Queue this session: spouse cp_fam Jannetje Hendrickson (b. Holmdel NJ, d. of Daniel + Catherine Van Dyck Hendrickson); 3 unminted children #498 Sarah⁶ (m. Benjamin Van Cleef Jr.), #499 Daniel⁶ (prob unmar.), #500 Catrina⁶ (m. David Vanderveer); place cp_pla for Freehold-Middletown Dutch Reformed Church (blocks baptism_place_id + marriage_place_id wire).",
