      "father_text": "Gerret Janse Van Couwenhoven (cp_fam_026)",
      "mother_text": "Aaltje van der Wijk (cp_fam_028) — CONFIRMED 2026-04-24 via own 1753 will evidence: testator names \"brother Cornelius Cozyn\" and \"brother Gerritt Cozyn\" as executors, which only makes sense as half-brothers via his mother's 2nd marriage to Jacobus Cosine/Cozyn (cp_fam_028 Aaltje remarried Jacobus Cosine bef. 1712-11-03; cp_fam_026 Gerret's 1st wife Lysbet predeceased him and cannot have had post-1712 children). Resolves prior HYPOTHESIS on mother's identity.",
      "spouse_text": "1st: — (unnamed, possibly d.y.); 2nd: Maria Cozine (per Cocheu 71:3 #200)",
      "children_summary": "Per own 1753 will: 9 children combined from two marriages — Pauline (cp_fam_045), Gerritt (cp_fam_046), Altie (cp_fam_047), Gabriel (cp_fam_048), John/Jan (cp_fam_049), Gertruy (cp_fam_050), Essye (cp_fam_051), Marya (cp_fam_052), Annatie (cp_fam_053). Specific bequests: Gerritt (£5 from £100 Cornelius Cosine debt + £20 + silver beaker + best horse), Jan (£15), Altie (20 shillings). Residual split among all 9 children.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "NY Surrogate's Office Liber 8 p.275 — named 'my son John' in father Gerret's 1711 will (heir, with Aeltie, to all real and personal estate). No WikiTree profile located as of 2026-04-24.; NY Surrogate's Office Liber 21 p.96 — own will of John Cowenhoven of Bushwick, carpenter, dated 1753-02-01, proved 1761-08-17 (FamilySearch book 167253 pp.108-109: https://www.familysearch.org/library/books/viewer/167253/?offset=0#page=109). Witnesses: Gabriel Strangh, Abraham Van Ende, Abraham Schenck. Executors: brother Cornelius Cozyn, brother Gerritt Cozyn, cousin Gabriel Duryee. | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 (Jul 1940), pp. 273-276 (cp_sou_049)",
      "notes": "Minor child at time of father's death (1712) — will directs property jointly to wife Aeltie and son John, with executors (wife, uncle Nicesimus, Theodorus Van Wyck) empowered to sell the Bushwyck lands 'if they see cause.' John's mother not named in the will; Gerret had two wives (Lysbet, Aaltje van der Wijk) per WikiTree. Flag: very thin record — WikiTree/source lookup needed before any downstream use. MATCH CONFIRMED 2026-04-24: same person as testator of 1753 will (NY Wills Liber 21 p.96). Previously this was a thin stub with mother uncertain; match evidence fills in full life: residence Bushwick (matches father's Bushwyck lands), occupation carpenter, 2 marriages with 9 children, and crucially the Cozyn half-brothers that CONFIRM his mother as cp_fam_028 Aaltje van der Wijk (her 2nd marriage to Jacobus Cosine produced the Cozyn brothers). The £100 debt owed by Cornelius Cosine to John is consistent with entangled maternal-estate finances between half-brothers. DEFERRED from this pass: 1st wife (unnamed stub), half-brothers Cornelius Cozyn + Gerritt Cozyn (Cozyn-Couwenhoven bridge row), cousin Gabriel Duryee.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 #200)\n- Refines death to Bushwick ~1761 (was 'between 1753'). Confirms 2nd wife Maria Cozine.\n- Cousin link: half-brothers via Aaltje van der Wijk's 2nd marriage to Jacobus Cosine — possible Cozine kin-network.",
