      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_fam_033",
      "sources": "New York, U.S., Wills and Probate Records 1659-1999 — Garret Couwenhoven 1781 will, Vol 0035-0039 pp.222-225 (Ancestry.com 2015; NY Surrogate's Court NY County); WikiTree Van_Couwenhoven-78 (https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Van_Couwenhoven-78); FAMILY cp_fam_033 cross-reference for full biographical data.\n\nCocheu 82:4 #215 (cp_sou_057) - primary identification + 1781 will text WNYHS:12:169-71.",
      "notes": "Sparse ENSLAVER row — biographical data lives in FAMILY cp_fam_033 per project mixed-prefix convention. Bedford-Homestead branch enslaver, brother of cp_ens_007 John (1707-1778) and Nicasius (1742-1793, Van_Couwenhoven-84). The will's collective bequest of \"all my Negroes\" with no individuals named places this row firmly in the UNNAMED-group registry; future inventory or sale records may produce individual names → cp_per_### rows. Added 2026-04-24 late from Garret Couwenhoven 1781 will (NY Wills Vol 0035-0039 pp.222-225).\n\n## CONSOLIDATED FROM FAMILY cp_fam_033 (single-sheet migration 2026-05-10)\nInherited Raritan NJ farm from father Nicasius's 1746 will (between Andries Ten Eyck and Peter Bodyn lands; contemporary Raritan landing was the cluster at modern South Bound Brook/Somerville area). RESOLVED 2026-04-24 late: WikiTree profile Van_Couwenhoven-78 confirmed by Chris; primary residence = New Utrecht (Kings Co. NY), with Raritan as inherited landholding. 1st wife Sarah (surname unknown), 2nd wife Antie Bergen, both per WikiTree snippet. Brother of cp_ens_007 (John, cp_ens_007) and of Nicasius (1742-1793, Van_Couwenhoven-84). ENSLAVER row pending — Chris to share documentary source for Gerret as enslaver; when added, this row will be cross-referenced from ENSLAVER as cp_fam_033 (no new cp_ens_### needed per project mixed-prefix convention). Documented enslaver via 1781-05-09 will bequeathing \"All my Negroes\" 1/3 each to son Johannes, daughter Sarah Schenck, children of dec'd son Necasie — see UNNAMED cp_rec_007 and ENSLAVER row keyed on cp_fam_033 (added 2026-04-24 late).\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 #215)\n- Cocheu refines: 'b. 1711-12' (= 1711 or early 1712), of New Utrecht (cp_pla_009). m.(1) abt. 1741 Sarah —; m.(2) Antie Bergen bp. 1710-03-12 d. 1756.\n- Will dated 1781-05-09; pro. 1784-02-05 (WNYHS 12:169) — already in record likely.\n\n## Kin network\n- 2nd wife Antie Bergen — Bergen surname (Bergen Gen. 1876 p. 553); brings Bergen kin into Nicasius line.\n\n[2026-05-10 STAGE 82:4-T3.1] Cocheu 82:4 #215 enrichment: birth refinement (~1711 -> 1712 New Utrecht), 1st-wife Sarah death date 1756-08-20, 2nd-wife Antje Bergen primary identification (Hans + Sarah Rapelye Bergen's daughter), full will text WNYHS:12:169-71 with named heirs. All children + grandchildren already cross-linked to cp_ens_013 (Johannes), cp_ens_014 (Garret), cp_ens_016 (Nelly Van Pelt = deceased son Nicholas's widow), cp_ens_017 (Catherine Stellerwerf = Johannes's 3rd wife). NEAR-MISS NOTE: this row was almost duplicated by tonight's 82:4 plan due to narrow date-only search; caught by exhaustive multi-criterion scan 2026-05-10.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Sibling|cp_ens_007;Child|cp_fam_032;Spouse|cp_fam_354;Spouse|cp_fam_355",
      "notable_records": "1781-05-09 will (probated 1784-02-05 by Thomas Tredwell, NY Surrogate's Court) — bequeaths \"All my Negroes together with all my household furniture\" divided 1/3 to son Johannes, 1/3 to daughter Sarah Schenck, 1/3 to children of dec'd son Necasie. Total enslaved count UNKNOWN (no individual names, no inventory in this entry). Witnessed by Petrus Van Pelt, John Verkerk Van Nuys, Nichs. Couwenhoven (HYPOTHESIS — brother Nicasius or cousin Judge Nicholas; see cp_rec_007 follow-up).",
