      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:2 #119. **First-cousin marriage** — wife Leah is daughter of his aunt cp_fam_071. Closes 5th Cowenhoven-Schenck cousin loop.\n\n## COCHEU 81:3 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_052) — Cocheu's #119\n- Baptized 1712-04-06 Freehold-Middletown DRC; married cousin Leah Schenck #140 1735-12-17 (HOT:413). Leah's parents Jan Roelofse Schenck + Sarah Covenhoven (cp_fam_071) were also cousins.\n\n## Civic offices\n- **Elder, Reformed Dutch Church Freehold, 1764** (Old Tennent precursor congregation)\n- **Original Trustee, Queens College (now Rutgers University), 1770**\n\n## Will + estate\n- Will dated 1774-03-22, proved 1774-06-07 (NJA:34:111) — requested all real + personal estate sold; £300 each to sons John, Peter, Elias, William, Ruliff (the latter to learn a trade); remainder to all sons + daughters Patience, Sarah, Leah; executors sons John + Elias + William; witnesses Daniel Barkelow + William Hulse + Edmund Harris\n\n## Children (10, all bp Freehold-Middletown DRC)\n- #363 Peter bp 1738-02-12 dy\n- **#364 John P.** bp 1740-03-23 d 1811-12-24 — Old Tennent Cem; m. ~1770 Jane McGalliard. **= cp_ens_050** (ENSLAVER cross-match — confirmed by Cocheu 81:3 in this commit)\n- #365 Patience bp 1742-04-25 m. Albert Covenhoven (son of cp_fam_153 Peter Covenhoven)\n- #366 Sarah bp 1745-02-24 d 1826-05-13 m. 1767-02-19 Joseph Thompson — 12 children\n- #367 Eleanor bp 1747-02-08 m. Johannes Schenck\n- #368 Peter bp 1749-04-09 (no further record)\n- #369 Elias bp 1751-06-09 d 1786-11-15 — drowned at Powles-hook ferry NYC; merchant at Allen-Town NJ; m. 1774-10-02 Catherine Forman; bur NY DRC cemetery\n- #370 William bp 1753-04-11 m. 1783-01-01 Nelly Smock d 1823-02-03\n- #371 Leah bp 1756-05-09 m. 1780-08-31 William Combs Freehold-Middletown DRC\n- #372 Ruliff bp 1758-03-12 m. Rachel Carr (admin'd estate 1792-10-09); 5 children bp 1792-10-12 Old Tennent; widow m. 1799-03-07 John Johnston of Saratoga NY\n\nLeah Schenck death-year corrected 2026-05-20 from 1764 to 1769. Conflict: Cocheu 81:3 (1950) says d.1764; Cocheu 71:2 (1940, earlier vol) says d.1769; FaG headstone says d.1769. Earlier Cocheu vol + FaG agree on 1769; per cross-Cocheu-volume-contradiction handling, defer to earlier vol where it agrees with primary FaG attestation.\n\n\n\n2026-05-20: Spouse Leah Janse Schenck promoted to own row cp_fam_322 per Old Brick mint batch (Tier-1 Schenck intermarriage tracking).",
