      "notes": "PROMOTED 2026-05-17 from cp_fam_159 (FAMILY) to ENSLAVER status via Jack (cp_per_232) 1783 Black Loyalist Directory registration. Per 5/17 mixed-prefix convention: cp_fam_159 row MOVED from FAMILY to ENSLAVER, PID unchanged. Pre-move stale-ref scan identified 12 PID-based references across sibling rows (cp_fam_157, 158, 160-166) + father cp_fam_083 children_summary + cp_fam_294 notes; all PID-based, all continue to resolve. || LIFE-COURSE NOTE: Samuel was deceased by the time of Jack's 1783-09-22 BLD registration — will probated 1783-06-27, three months before. Jack's identification of Samuel as former enslaver is therefore retrospective; Samuel's heirs (children per Cocheu 83:2 #677-682) would have inherited any still-enslaved persons under the 1781 will. || AGE NOTE: Samuel b. 1712, Jack b. ~1723 — only 11 years separates them. Samuel did NOT hold Jack from Jack's birth (Samuel was a child). Probable inheritance from Samuel's father Johannes⁴ (cp_fam_083) — to be verified.",
