      "spouse_text": "Elizabeth Debevoise (daughter of Joost & Mary Remsen Debevoise per Cocheu 82:4 #216, AnN 407; \"Libettie, deceased wife of Peter Covenhoven\" per father Joost's 1765-05-01 will WNYHS:8:100-01) - m. ~1734. **CORRECTION 2026-05-10**: prior workbook spouse field \"Leah Schenck (daughter of Jan Roelofse Schenck) m. 1735-12-17\" was a known DEFERRED data-quality bug from 2026-04-24 mint - it was conflated with cp_fam_099 Peter Pieterse Couwenhoven (Cocheu #119, the Pieter-line cousin Peter who actually married Leah Schenck). Correction primary-source verified by Cocheu 82:4 #216.",
      "children_summary": "5 children per Cocheu 82:4 #216 (will 1786-09-20 / proved 1788-03-29 NJA:36:55 names sons Nicholas + Joseph + daughters Mary + Elizabeth + grandchildren Peter Probasco + Mary Hoagland): (i) **Nicholas6 #661 = cp_ens_023** b. ~1736 d. 1803-03-19 age 66, m. ~1758 Catharine Suydam (daughter of Cornelius Suydam per his 1768-12-12 will NJA:34:513) - Franklin Twp Somerset Co NJ; bur. Garretsen Farm near Bound Brook NJ; will 1802-10-19 / proved 1803-06-22 NJA:39:104; 5 children incl Catharine, Elizabeth, Peter, Cornelius, Nicholas (= cp_ens_022); (ii) Joseph6 #662 bap. 1739-09-16 New Brunswick d. 1814-04-06 age 75, m. ~1768 Mary Field b. 1745-07-17 d. 1798-07-02 (daughter of John Field of Piscataway), bur. Wells Farm North Bound Brook NJ; will 1800-12-24 / proved 1814-05-23 NJA:42:101-02; 9 children: Peter d.y., John, Joseph, Jeremiah of Pluckemin (m. Margaret Voorhees), Garrett d.y., Elizabeth, Elsie, Mary, Ellen; (iii) Mary6 mentioned in father's 1786 will; (iv) Elizabeth6 mentioned in father's 1786 will; plus grandchildren Peter Probasco + Mary (Hoagland) wife of Abraham Hoagland.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "NY Wills Liber 17 p.18 — named 'my son Peter' in father Nicasius's 1746 will (FamilySearch book 111896 pp.248-249), inheriting Raritan NJ plantation where he already lived + £1000 already received; WikiTree (father's page VanCouwenhoven-24) lists him bp.1712-04-06 NJ, d.1774, m. Leah Schenck 1735-12-17 — via WebSearch snippet 2026-04-24. | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 (Jul 1940), pp. 273-276 (cp_sou_049)\n\nCocheu 82:4 #216 (cp_sou_057) - primary identification of spouse Elizabeth Debevoise + 5-children list + Somerset County residence. Will 1786-09-20 / proved 1788-03-29 NJA:36:55. Father Joost Debevoise's 1765-05-01 will WNYHS:8:100-01 names \"Libettie, deceased wife of Peter Covenhoven.\"",
      "notes": "Inherited Raritan NJ plantation where he already lived under father's 1746 will (already received £1000 advance by 1746). Wife Leah Schenck was daughter of Jan Roelofse Schenck — reinforces Couwenhoven-Schenck marriage alliance on this NJ line. DISAMBIG: distinct from another 'Peter Couwenhoven of Freehold, Monmouth NJ' whose 1743 will names wife Patience + children William/Elias/Hannah/Jane/Mary/Aeltje/Anne — that Peter was son of Pieter Willemse Kouwenhoven (1671-1755) via Patientia Dawes, not of cp_fam_027. Flag follow-up for direct WikiTree profile ID.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_049 — Cocheu NYG&BR 71:3 #216)\n- Cocheu 71:3 names PETER's wife = Elizabeth Debevoise dau. Joost Debevoise + Mary Remsen (AnN 407). BUT existing workbook record said spouse = Leah Schenck dau. of Jan Roelofse Schenck + m.1735-12-17. CONFLICT.\n- POSSIBLE RESOLUTION: there are two Peters — cp_fam_034 may be a different Peter than Cocheu's #216. OR the existing record (Leah Schenck/1735) may be wrong. Need to verify against father Nicasius's 1746 will (NY Wills Liber 17 p. 18) which named cp_fam_034 'my son Peter' inheriting Raritan NJ plantation. Cocheu also has #216 'of Raritan NJ b. 1713' — matches cp_fam_034's b. 1712 / Raritan residence.\n- DEFERRED: needs Chris review. Mark as confidence_flag conflict during Stage 1d audit.\n\n[2026-05-10 STAGE 82:4-T1.2] Spouse field corrected per Cocheu 82:4 #216. Prior 2026-04-24 mint had incorrectly attributed \"Leah Schenck m. 1735-12-17\" - that data belongs to cp_fam_099 Peter Pieterse Couwenhoven (Pieter-line cousin Peter, Cocheu #119). The two Peters were conflated at minting. Cocheu 82:4 supplies primary identification: this Peter is the Raritan Valley NJ patriarch (Jan-line via Nicasius Janse cp_fam_027), m. Elizabeth Debevoise daughter of Joost Debevoise + Mary Remsen. Father chain unchanged. 5 children installed including son cp_ens_023 Nicholas of Franklin Twp Somerset (father-chain-completed in same session). DEFERRED flag from prior session is now RESOLVED. || Cocheu citation (moved from full_name 2026-05-13): Cocheu #216, of Raritan Valley NJ",
