      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:2 (Apr 1940), pp. 157-162 (cp_sou_048)",
      "notes": "Cocheu 71:2 #165. Named for older brother Peter #164 who died as infant 1719.\n\n**ENRICHED 2026-05-10 (9 (none)-bucket attribution arc):** children_summary backfilled with 9 named children (FS PIDs per LTT8-HL2 screenshot Chris-shared 2026-05-10). Notable: cp_ens_031 + cp_fam_229 are siblings (Brooklyn Jacob and William Benjamin, b.1750 and 1752) — this is the linking pair that makes cp_ens_055 Wyckoff = cp_ens_031's nephew.\n\n**COCHEU CHILD-LIST FLAG — 2026-05-12**: The children_summary currently lists 9 children (from FS LTT8-HL2 Chris-shared 2026-05-10), but Cocheu NYG&BR 82:2 (Apr 1951) pp.93-94 enumerates exactly 6 children for #165 Peter Jacobse II + Catherine Schenck: (1) Jacobus⁶ #516 = cp_ens_031 Brooklyn Jacob; (2) Roelof⁶ #517 bap. 1752-08-21 (marriage UNDOCUMENTED by Cocheu — possible candidate for the screenshot-5 Roelef × Aeltje Voorhees if FS lookup confirms); (3) Sarah⁶ #518 bap. 1755 d.y.; (4) Maria⁶ #519 bap. 1755 (twin) m. Thomas Shields 1788; (5) John⁶ #520 bap. 1758-04-09 m. Ann English 1783; (6) Antje⁶ #521 bap. 1761 d.y. Cocheu explicitly engages and rules out the EDSM 'six total' question — primary attestation is firm. **William Benjamin (cp_fam_229) does NOT appear in Cocheu's list; he is Cocheu's #443 son in a different line per 82:1 p.38.** Therefore cp_fam_229, cp_ens_055, cp_fam_276 wirings to this row are in dispute. Per Chris 2026-05-12: flag, defer correction; pursue resolution via NJA:36:55-56.",
