      "notes": "**PROMOTED 2026-05-28 from cp_fam_133 (FAMILY) to ENSLAVER status via Cocheu #166 + cp_eve_158 (1792 will) MATCH for cp_per_097 Betty. Per [[feedback-mixed-prefix-no-rename]] (5/17 convention): cp_fam_133 row MOVED from FAMILY → ENSLAVER, PID unchanged (mixed-prefix).** Identification rests on 9-point convergence: (1) testator name 'John Covenhoven yeoman of Middletown'; (2) will dated 1792-02-01; (3) proved 1792-06-08; (4) inventory £472:10:6 taken 1792-06-07; (5) wife Mary; (6) son Jacob (residuary legatee); (7) 3 married daughters Nelly Lane + Sarah Smock + Caty Lane; (8) brother-in-law Garret Hendrickson executor; (9) friend executor Jacob Covenhoven. **5/15 ruled-out elimination reversed**: 'brother-in-law Garret Hendrickson' did NOT mean wife's maiden = Hendrickson; Cocheu confirms wife's maiden = Van Doren; Garret Hendrickson is brother-in-law via different family relationship (likely John's sister married a Hendrickson). Father cp_ens_009 + brother cp_ens_032 (son Jacob⁶ 'miller of Freehold' #522). Detailed adjudication in Johns_Contested_Records row JoM_008.",
