      "raw_related_enslavers": "Parent|cp_ens_009;Spouse|Mary Van Dorn; Parent|cp_fam_138; Child|cp_ens_032",
      "notable_records": "**1792-02-01 Will (proved 1792-06-08), NJA:37:91-92** — bequest names wife Mary; son Jacob (residuary legatee, = cp_ens_032 'Jacob the miller of Freehold'); daughters Nelly Lane, Sarah Smock, Caty Lane (all married daughters). Executors: brother-in-law Garret Hendrickson + friend Jacob Covenhoven. Witnesses: Simon Van Arsdale, Isaac Van Pelt, Cornelius Van Horn, Jacob Van Arsdale, John Schenck Jr., Peter Van Doren. **Inventory £472:10:6** taken 1792-06-07 by John Stillwell + Isaac Covenhoven. Cocheu textual note: 'The omission of the names of Arie, John, and the younger Antje leads to the belief that these children had predeceased their father leaving no issue.' = cp_eve_158.",
