      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-20 during Old Brick / Taylor's Mills batch (Stage 2 / cluster D.1). **Tier-1 Schenck intermarriage** per [[feedback-track-intermarriage-surnames-systematically]] policy — highest priority. Cocheu 82:2 #163 attests \"Neeltje Schenck who was born Apr. 10, 1724, in Monmouth, and died Mar. 25, 1800, a daughter of Roelof & Geesje (Hendrickson) Schenck. Both Gerret and his wife are buried in a family graveyard near Taylor's Mills, Atlantic Township, N.J.\" Stone inscription verbatim: \"In Memory of Ellender wife of Garret Couenhoven who departed this life the 25th of March 1800 aged 75 Years 11 months and 14 days.\" Stone age-math gives DOB 11 Apr 1724 (1 day off from Cocheu's \"Apr. 10, 1724\" — within stone-engraving tolerance). The \"16 May 1725\" displayed on FaG as birth is actually the BAPTISM date per the Beekman 1915 bio text — FaG mis-displays baptism as birth date (per [[feedback_cocheu_age_math_pins_DOB]] expanded 5/19-20 rule about catching mis-labeled FaG display dates). Beekman 1915 quote on memorial: \"Garret, b. November 5, 1716, married October 12, 1744, Neeltje, or Eleanor, daughter of Roelof Schenck and Geesie Hendrickson...\" Her father Roelof Schenck (1692-1766) is a candidate kin-mint for next session — Schenck patriarch with 3 daughters married into Couwenhoven family per Cocheu cross-reference (this Neeltje + Sarah + Katriinke/Gesje per cp_fam_227 entry). Her sister Katriinke Schenck DeHart Couwenhoven (1718-?) = wife of Cocheu #165 Peter Couwenhoven per cp_fam_227 entry — second Schenck-Couwenhoven marriage in same generation.",
