      "children_summary": "Per FS LTK3-SJC + FindAGrave 232809291 + Franklin Ellis 1885: 5 children with first wife Neeltje Van Mater — Jacoba Gerrit Covenhoven 1749-1812 (FS L9CX-L3K, MATCHES \"Cobauchy\" deceased daughter named in 1812 will, \"Cobauchy\" = phonetic rendering of \"Jacoba\"); Benjamin Garret Covenhoven 1753-1801 (FS LKH1-6BK, MATCHES will's \"deceased son Benjamin\" with 7 named grandchildren John, Obadiah, Garret, Catherine, Martha, Elenor, Betsey); Catherine Conover 1755-deceased (FS GBBD-X4R, MATCHES will's \"Catharine\"); John Conover 1766-1775 (FS 9J4V-5S5, died young — NOT the \"John\" in will); Garret Covenhoven 1770-1851 (FS L6WR-RFL, MATCHES will's \"Garret Kovenhoven Jr.\" who received Jack). 5 children with second wife Antje Schenck — Eleanor 1787-12-13 (m. De Lafayette Schenck — MATCHES will son-in-law executor \"Delafayette Schenck\"); Jane 1789-11-09 (m. Stacy Prickot); Ann 1790-09 (m. 1st William Schenck, 2nd Theodore Rue); John 1791-12-17 (m. Ann Smock — MATCHES will's \"John\" co-heir of homestead receiving Callaman); Peter G. 1797-01-02 (m. Charlotte Lyell 1819 — MATCHES will's \"Peter\" co-heir of homestead receiving Joe; \"G.\" patronymic = Garret's son).",
