      "notes": "Mint 2026-05-07 from FindAGrave Memorial 232809291 + WikiTree Van_Covenhoven-2 + FS LTK3-SJC + 1812 will abstract (NJ Wills 1670-1817, Ancestry collection 2793) + Franklin Ellis 1885 History of Monmouth County pp. 748-749. CRITICAL SPELLING NOTE: the K-spelling in \"Garret Kovenhoven\" is an NJ Wills abstractor variant; primary tombstone reads \"GARRET CONOVER ESQ\", FS uses \"Covenhoven\". The K-spelling=Flatlands-branch heuristic per feedback_two_cowenhoven_spellings_by_branch.md applies to PRIMARY-source spellings, NOT to abstractor renderings — Garret was Marlboro/Freehold-Twp NJ his entire life. The \"Senior\" suffix in project records distinguishes from son Garret Jr. (b.1770 d.1851, FS L6WR-RFL — future cp_ens mint candidate). Buried at Old Brick Reformed Church Cemetery, Marlboro — same churchyard family as Brick Reformed records cited in baptism note. 5 Active rows (R112-R116) backfilled with cp_ens_051 + confidence MATCH. Cobauchy = phonetic rendering of \"Jacoba\" (FS L9CX-L3K, daughter from 1st marriage who died 1812, same year as father). Friend/co-executor relationship to cp_ens_030 Cornelius C. Conover surfaces a previously-undocumented social tie between two minted enslavers. Tombstone Esq. title is GARRET's, not \"John Covenhoven Esquire\" who is a separate disambiguation candidate (5 records, 1795 NJ Supreme Court Forman case).\n\n## CONSOLIDATED FROM cp_ens_051 (audit 2026-05-10)\nFAMILY-row enrichment merged into this ENSLAVER row; original FAMILY row deleted. Original FAMILY notes preserved below.\n\nCocheu 71:2 #174. Born in Marlborough NJ — first cp_fam_057 child documented as Marlborough-born (vs siblings of Penn's Neck or Windsor). Long life (1726-1812 = 86 yrs).\n\n\n\n2026-05-20: 2nd wife Antje (Ann) Schenck promoted to own row cp_fam_323 per Old Brick mint batch (Tier-1 Schenck intermarriage tracking). Step-family connection now wired: her mother Jannetje Hendrickson was previously married to Roelof Covenhoven = cp_ens_010.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Sibling|William Jansen Van Couwenhoven 1705-1764 (FS L1WB-PR7); Sibling|Tryntje Janse Couwenhoven 1709-1778 (FS LKDN-6NB); Sibling|Cornelius Jansen Van Kouwenhoven 1712-1804 (FS LKDN-DVN); Sibling|Peter Jansen Van Kouwenhoven 1714- (FS L6PR-RWC); Sibling|John Covenhoven 1719-1778 (FS G9NK-H4L); Sibling|Dominicus Janse Van Couwenhoven 1724-1778 (FS L6MZ-MYB); Sibling|Jacob Jansen Van Kouwenhoven 1727- (FS LKDN-D5H); Friend/Executor|cp_ens_030 Cornelius C. Conover (named in 1812 will as friend + co-executor); Son-in-law/Executor|De Lafayette Schenck (m. daughter Eleanor);; Spouse|cp_fam_323 (2nd wife Antje/Ann Schenck, m. abt. 1786, d. 1803-04-05; FaG #232809646)",
