      "notes": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — child of cp_fam_088 John #88 of Great Egg Harbor NJ.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #289)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #289 — major enrichment:\n\n## Birth + baptism\n- b. about 1741 (was \"about 30 years of age\" when baptized as adult 1771-10-14).\n- Baptized as adult at TRINITY EPISCOPAL CHURCH, Swedesboro NJ — first documented Episcopal/Anglican affiliation on the Pieter branch (departure from Dutch Reformed roots; consistent with Quaker-mother / South-Jersey assimilation).\n\n## Marriage\n- m. same day as baptism, 1771-10-14, at Trinity Episcopal Swedesboro: Sarah Steelman, daughter of James Steelman.\n- Joseph appointed executor of James Steelman's estate 1785-11-24 (NJA:35:371).\n\n## Rev War + estate\n- Served as CAPTAIN in the Revolutionary War (Stryker:387).\n- Admin on his estate granted 1801-12-08 to son James (cp_fam #734); fellowbondsmen James Steelman + Richard Risley (NJA:39:104).\n\n## 4 children (NOT yet minted as cp_fam — Tier 3 deferred):\n(734) James⁶ b. 1774-11-14; d. 1855-04-16. m. 1796-10-12 Rebecca Somers (d. 1820-04-24), dau. of James + Rebecca (Steelman) Somers.\n(735) Joseph⁶ b. 1777-07-02; d. 1850-03-25. m. 1801-02-20 Ruhama Leeds b. 1779-01-21, dau. of Jeremiah + Judith (Steelman) Leeds. Jeremiah Leeds was the first permanent settler on Absecon Beach (now Atlantic City). Both bur. Mt. Pleasant Cemetery, Pleasantville NJ.\n(736) John⁶ b.-; perhaps the John Conover who m. Jemima Blackman 1801.\n(737) Enoch⁶ b.-; living 1823-10 land conveyance (Glou. Co. Deeds:22:187). m. Judith Steelman b. 1785-03-13, dau. of Isaac + Mary (Andrews) Steelman.",
