      "occupation": "",
      "father_text": "Frans Cowenhoven (cp_fam_037) — will's phrasing \"my natural son\" = 18th-century legal acknowledgment of illegitimate (out-of-wedlock) child formally named as heir",
      "mother_text": "unknown — NOT Mary Jansen (cp_fam_038) per will's phrasing (the tankard-before-marriage note distinguishes Samuel from Frans's marriage to Mary). Pending research.",
      "spouse_text": "Sarah Drinkwater (per Cocheu 71:4 #261; m. NY 1726-01-30 MDC 144)",
      "children_summary": "Per Frans's 1745 will: Edward Cowenhoven (cp_fam_042; received £10 legacy from grandfather) and Mary Cowenhoven (cp_fam_043; received £25 legacy from grandfather). Will also references \"all his children\" collectively as residual heirs — implying more than two children.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "NY Surrogate's Office Liber 16 p.400 — will of Frans Cowenhoven identifies him as 'my natural son Samuel' and main heir (estate for life, then proceeds divided among his children). | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050)",
      "notes": "Illegitimate son of Frans (cp_fam_037) formally acknowledged in the 1745 will using the 18th-century legal term 'natural son'. Parallels the pattern of cp_fam_022 Aeltje (du Trieux) Pieters (Pieter Wolphertsen's acknowledged extramarital daughter, Dutch Manuscripts 1642-01-07 court adoption). Inherited Frans's whole estate for his lifetime, with executors instructed to sell after his death and divide proceeds 'among all his children'. Mother unknown — the will's phrasing implies she was NOT Mary Jansen (cp_fam_038). Pending research: life dates, spouse (if any), residence, additional children beyond Edward and Mary.\n\n## ENRICHMENT via Cocheu 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — son of Frans (cp_fam_037)\nCocheu lists Samuel directly as #261 in Frans's Issue: 'Samuel⁵, m. NY, Jan. 30, 1726, Sarah Drinkwater (MDC 144).'\nNote: Cocheu does NOT preserve the 'natural son' framing in the Issue listing, but Frans's own 1745 will explicitly says 'my natural son Samuel' — the 'natural' framing comes from the will itself (NY Surrogate's Office Liber 16 p.400 / WNYHS 4:208). So Samuel was illegitimate but formally acknowledged + heirs in will.\nCocheu confirms Samuel had a wife (Sarah Drinkwater) — i.e., he had a publicly recognized marital household, which is consistent with formal acknowledgment as 'natural son' in the will.\nMarriage 1726-01-30 (MDC 144) is BEFORE Frans's 1727 marriage to Maria Brouwn — consistent with the existing hypothesis that Samuel was b. ca. 1700-1710 to an unknown mother (NOT Mary/Maria; pre-1727).\n\n## branch=Jacob cascade\nInherited from father cp_fam_037 (now resolved to Jacob/Gen 4). Samuel = Jacob branch / Gen 5 (natural son convention per cp_fam_022 precedent — biological blood preserves branch).",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_037;Child|cp_fam_042;Child|cp_fam_043;Spouse|Sarah Drinkwater",
