      "father_text": "Frans Cowenhoven (cp_fam_037) — Cocheu 71:4 #72 lists her directly in Issue (#260): 'Martha⁵, m. John Fred.' REFUTES the genealogy.com Herring-step-parent hypothesis.",
      "mother_text": "Uncertain — likely Catharine Olivier (cp_fam_155, Frans's 1st wife m. 1709) based on age (Martha married before 1745; if b. ~1715 she'd have been from 1st marriage). Alternative: Maria Brouwn (cp_fam_038, 2nd wife m. 1727) if Martha married very young (~1740s-15-yr-old marriage). Cocheu doesn't specify which mother.",
      "spouse_text": "John Fred (cp_fam_041; styled \"Captain John Fred\" per genealogy.com forum) — married before 1745-08-15",
      "children_summary": "",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "NY Surrogate's Office Liber 16 p.400 — Frans's 1745 will names her as wife of son-in-law John Fred, co-heir of silver tankard + 3 spoons, and co-executor; genealogy.com forum 'CAPT. JOHN FRED and MARTHA' thread: https://www.genealogy.com/forum/surnames/topics/fred/76/ (HYPOTHESIS source — suggests Martha Herring, sister of Benjamin Herring Jr., m. Capt. John Fred). | Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050)",
      "notes": "Will's phrasing 'my son-in-law John Fred, and his wife Martha' is ambiguous in 18th-century English: 'son-in-law' could mean biological daughter's husband OR stepson (stepdaughter's husband). Genealogy.com forum source — not verified in primary records — suggests Martha was Martha Herring, daughter of Mary Jansen by a prior Herring marriage, with brother Benjamin Herring Jr.; would make Frans her stepfather. Alternative: biological daughter of Frans + Mary. Will's inheritance-through-Mary pattern (silver from Mary's prior ownership to Martha) is consistent with EITHER reading. Named co-executor; handled probate with husband John Fred in Feb 1749. Follow-up: confirm surname and parentage via baptism records, Herring-family sources, or Dutch Reformed Church of NY records.\n\n## CORRECTION + RESOLUTION via Cocheu 71:4 (cp_sou_050) #260\nPre-71:4 workbook: surname uncertain Cowenhoven-or-Herring; biological-vs-stepdaughter ambiguity (genealogy.com forum hypothesis).\nCocheu 71:4 #72 (Frans's bio) lists Martha as the FIRST in Issue — implies biological daughter of Frans, no Herring step-parent suggested. Combined with the cp_fam_038 correction (Maria Brouwn, not Mary Jansen, no Herring prior marriage), Martha is firmly cp_fam_037's biological daughter.\n\n## Maternal uncertainty (open follow-up)\nFrans had 3 wives (1709 Catharine Olivier, 1727 Maria Brouwn, 1746 Hillegond Bogart) — Martha could be daughter of Catharine (most likely based on age) or Maria (less likely). Hillegond ruled out (m. 1746 = after Martha's own marriage).",
