      "notes": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — child of cp_fam_087 Peter Sr.#87 of Great Egg Harbor NJ.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #282)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #282 — full will + 8 children enriched (was stub):\n\n## Will + estate\n- Resided Galloway Township, Gloucester Co.\n- Will dated 1777-06-04 / proved 1777-08-14 (NJA:34:113).\n- Bequest to wife Katherine: \"all she brought when we married.\"\n- Stipulation: \"son, Jesse [was] to live with his brother David, till he is 21.\"\n- Executors: sons David and Peter.\n- Witnesses: Robert P. Tyrrill, Isaac Somers, Abner Doughty.\n\n## 8 children (per father's will) — NOT yet minted as cp_fam (Tier 3 deferred):\n(714) David⁶ b. ~1755; Rev War service (Stryker:549); d. before 1815-03-07 per Woodbury deed. 5 children: Isaiah⁷ b. ~1790 m. Esther Kaiser (Paradise Twp, Lancaster Co. PA, 1850); Josiah⁷ m. 1805-03-24 Sally Weeks (d. 1857-09-01 Smithville NJ); Eliakim⁷; Mary⁷ m. — Homan; Rebecca⁷ m. 1812-04-05 William Conover (Glou. Co. Mar.A:203).\n(715) Peter⁶ b.-; living 1777, d. before 1815. Prob. = Peter Conover m. 1761-09-04 Priscilla Smith (NJA:22:77). 1 known son: John⁷.\n(716) Jesse⁶ b. ~1765; d. 1850-11-06 Tanners Brook, Atlantic Co., widower aged 85. 1 known son: Rufus⁷ b. ~1798 d. 1848-07-17 Tanners Brook; m. 1823-11-30 Ann Conover.\n(717) Sarah⁶ b.-; m. 1764-08-21 Jacob Eldredge (NJA:22:96), son of Samuel + Mercy (Learning) Eldredge. 4 Eldredge children: Jacob⁷, Mary (Mercy)⁷ m. — Smith, Sarah⁷ m. — Crowell, Priscilla⁷ m. — Shaw.\n(718) Esther⁶ b.-; called Esther Doughty in father's will. 83:3 notes ambiguity re: Abner Doughty's wife — Cocheu suggests Esther may instead have been first wife of Thomas Doughty (will 1801-11-24 / pro. 1805-05-10 NJA:39:136-37).\n(719) Mary⁶ b.-; m. by 1764-09-26 license Elias Gandy \"Gentleman of Great Egg Harbour\" (NJA:22:96), bondsman Jonathan Reed.\n(720) Ann⁶ b.-; no further record.\n(721) Phebe⁶ b.-; youngest daughter per father's will.",
