      "notes": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — child of cp_fam_087 Peter Sr.#87 of Great Egg Harbor NJ.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #285)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #285 — full enrichment:\n\n## Marriage\n- m. by license dated 1750-01-29, Deborah Stanton of Great Egg Harbor. At time of marriage he was called \"of Cape May and Gloucester Counties\" — suggests mobility between these adjacent South Jersey counties.\n\n## Rev War + estate\n- Served in Revolutionary War from Gloucester County.\n- Letters of Administration granted 1797-02-03 to son John Conover (cp_fam #725); fellowbondsmen John Price + Peter Ashman (NJA:38:86).\n\n## 6 children (NOT yet minted as cp_fam — Tier 3 deferred):\n(722) Isaiah⁶ b.-; m1 Mary Bell 1774-11-11 (Mar.rec.:C:567); m2 Barbara Peterson 1814-03-10 (Salem Co. Mar.recs.). Living Salem Co. 1834. 2 children prob. by 1st wife: Abigail⁷ b.~1777 d. 1861-09-30 Egg Harbor (m1 Evan Jeffreys 1796, m2 John Martin 1812); Clement⁷ d. 1819-10-20 Woodstown NJ.\n(723) Micajah⁶ b. ~1761; d. 1826-11-12 aged 65. m. Mary — (d. 1822-08-19 aged 61). Both bur. Woodstown NJ (Salem Co. Cem. recs.:1:144). 5 children: John⁷ (m. Reumah Parvin), Isaiah⁷, Mary Deborah⁷ (m. Abbott Atkinson), Catherine⁷, Israel⁷ (Upper Pittsgrove farmer).\n(724) Deborah⁶ b. 1769-01-26; d. 1841-12-19. m. 1786-03-05 at TRINITY EPISCOPAL CHURCH Swedesboro NJ, Clement Ireland b. 1762-12-25 d. 1835-05-08 (bur. Woodstown). 12 Ireland children listed in detail.\n(725) John⁶ b. 1772-06-01; d. 1847-02-17 Conovertown (Atlantic Co.); \"large landowner... one tract of nearly four thousand acres is still known by the original name of CONOVERTOWN.\" m1. Catherine Price by 1792-10-13 (d. 1804-04-24, \"in her 29th year\"); m2. Mrs. Comfort (Ireland) Price b. 1770-08-25 d. 1848-05-21 (widow of Josiah Price). 8 children. **POTENTIAL ENSLAVER CANDIDATE — pursue via NJ Slavery Records DB next session per Stage 3 deferred queue.**\n(726) Sarah⁶ b.-; no further record.\n(727) Mary⁶ b.-; m. 1814-09-15 (Mar. Rec. Bk.:A:251) Enoch Ireland b. 1772-08-31. 6 Ireland children.\n\n## Naming-pattern signal\n- Daughter Deborah married a Clement Ireland; sister Mary⁴ Adams's grandson Jeremiah Adams married a Deborah Ireland's daughter Elizabeth — Conover-Ireland kin loop, traceable via Pieter branch + Adams cousin line.",
