      "notes": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — child of cp_fam_088 John #88 of Great Egg Harbor NJ.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #288)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #288 — major enrichment + identity clarification:\n\n## Marriage corrections\n- TWICE married. m1: Catherine — (surname unknown; per Lake Fam. 1915, chart p.255).\n- m2: Letitia Clark 1778-10-30.\n- 83:3 explicitly REJECTS prior conflation: \"He was not the Conover, however, who married Catherine Steelman, a daughter of James, with whom he has been confused. That Catherine Conover was mentioned as such in her father's will, dated Oct. 20, 1784 (NJA:35:371), several years after John had married a second time.\" Cocheu footnote: the John Conover-Catherine Steelman question is still unresolved — could be Peter⁵ #282 (cp_fam_174) or David⁵ son of David⁴ #89 (cp_fam_089).\n\n## Estate\n- Admin granted to widow Letitia 1781-05-05; fellowbondsman Enoch Wilson (NJA:22:77 + 35:97).\n- 1798-05-28 deed: \"heirs of John Covenover\" convey property to Peter Boice (Glou. Co. Deeds:1:16) — names children.\n\n## 6 children (NOT yet minted as cp_fam — Tier 3 deferred):\n(728) Isaac⁶ b.-; m. before 1798-05-28, Nancy —.\n(729) Job⁶ b.-; will pro. 1839-05-04; m. Rebecca Somers, dau. of Isaac Somers Sr. + Maryan —.\n(730) Sophia⁶ b.-; d. 1823-03-12. m. 1772-12-23 (NJA:22:95) James Steelman, son of Frederick + Sarah (Somers) Steelman (Lake Fam. 1915, p.244). James d. 1817-10-17.\n(731) Susanna⁶ b.-; m1. before 1798, Enoch Somers; m2. 1804-10-01 Isaac Somers Jr. Both Somers brothers were sons of Isaac + Maryan Somers.\n(732) Sarah⁶ b.-; m. 1774-04-18 David Adams (NJA:22:96).\n(733) Sylvia⁶ b.-; m. — Drake.",
