      "father_text": "John Peterse Couwenhoven (cp_fam_088)",
      "mother_text": "Sarah Adams",
      "spouse_text": "Joseph Dole (b. 1721-03-19; d. 1786-01-05). Son of Joseph + Hannah (Somers) Dole of Great Egg Harbor. Per Cocheu 83:3 cp_sou_058: m. before 1750; Joseph's will dated 1786-01-04 / proved 1786-07-24 (NJA:36:69) named wife Sarah and son Joseph as executors; witnesses Noah Smith, Jonathan + Mary Adams. Sarah lived past 1788. Prior workbook 'Joseph Dale (1721-1780)' (from Cocheu 71:4 cp_sou_050) was a transcription error on both surname and death year.",
      "children_summary": "## 83:3 enrichment (cp_sou_058):\n6 Dole children (matriline; not minted as cp_fam) per Joseph Dole 1786 will (NJA:36:69):\n(a) Rebecca Dole b. 1750-04-27; m. Joshua Garwood b. 1748-03-02, son of Thomas + Mary (Ballenger) Garwood.\n(b) Mary Dole b. 1754-08-24; d. 1829-12-04, prob. unmar.\n(c) Sarah Dole b. 1759-12-13; m. John R. Scull b. 1756-01-30, son of Recompense + Phoebe (Dennis) Scull.\n(d) Hannah Dole b.-; m. 1773-12-27 Daniel Ingersoll b. 1748-11-05, son of Joseph + Mary (Risley) Ingersoll.\n(e) Joseph Dole b.-; living 1788 when heirs sold property to Joshua Garwood.\n(f) Survia (Sophia) Dole b.-; mentioned as Sophia in 1801-06-10 deed.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (Oct 1940), pp. 365-367 (cp_sou_050) | Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 (Jul 1952), pp. 147-156 (cp_sou_058)",
      "notes": "Cocheu NYG&BR 71:4 (cp_sou_050) — child of cp_fam_088 John #88 of Great Egg Harbor NJ.\n\n## SOURCE-NAME ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_058 — Cocheu NYG&BR 83:3 #292)\nCocheu 83:3 (cp_sou_058) #292 — substantial enrichment (husband-name + death-year corrections handled in Tier 1):\n\n## Marriage + husband family\n- m. before 1750 Joseph Dole (b. 1721-03-19; d. 1786-01-05), son of Joseph + Hannah (Somers) Dole of Great Egg Harbor.\n- Joseph Dole's will dated 1786-01-04 / proved 1786-07-24 (NJA:36:69). Named wife Sarah + son Joseph as executors. Witnesses: Noah Smith, Jonathan + Mary Adams.\n\n## Death\n- Sarah lived past 1788 (1788 deed records heirs of Joseph Dole Sr. selling to Joshua Garwood — Sarah is named as still living).\n\n## 6 Dole children (matriline; not minted as cp_fam) — full enumeration in children_summary field. Note Quaker-area surname cluster (Garwood, Scull, Ingersoll) consistent with this branch's Friends-influenced milieu.\n\n## Correction provenance flag\n- Prior workbook entry 'Joseph Dale (1721-1780)' (per Cocheu 71:4 cp_sou_050) was a transcription error on BOTH surname (Dale → Dole) AND death year (1780 → 1786). Rundstrom (descendant) provides the correct dates with NJA citation.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_fam_088;Sibling|cp_fam_180;Sibling|cp_fam_181;Sibling|cp_fam_182;Sibling|cp_fam_183;Sibling|cp_fam_185;Sibling|cp_fam_186;Spouse|Joseph Dole (1721-1786)",
