      "children_summary": "11 per Cocheu 81:3 #354 + FS MJ33-KMJ: (a) John (b. 1757-04-25, FS L69X-5CT); (b) Elias⁷ = cp_fam_303 (b. 1759-02-04, FS L69X-5Z6; d. 1786-11-15 drowning at Powles-Hook ferry, age 27; merchant at Allentown NJ; left a young family; per cp_famsou_017). Note: HYPOTHESIS-STRONG attribution to cp_eve_035 \"Inn Keeper Elias Conover\" RETIRED per cp_famsou_017 — cp_eve_035 needs reattribution to a different/later Elias; (c) Forman (b. 1761-03-17, d. 1762-04-05); (d) Samuel Forman (b. 1762-03-27, m. ____ Lewis 1788); (e) James (b. 1765-06-09, m. Margaret Anderson 1780); (f) Jane (b. 1767-10-19, m. Hendrick Vanderbilt); (g) Anne⁷ (b. 1770-11-05, FS KZ72-HL7) — HYPOTHESIS = \"Ann F. Conover of Upper Freehold\" per cp_eve_076 (1826 manumitter of Cloe Jeffers cp_per_072); (h) Forman (b. 1773-06-06, FS KH7J-3TM); (i) Mary (b. 1775-07-06); (j) Eleanor (b. 1776-11-26, d. 1852, m. Dr. Joseph Leedom 1804, FS L69X-5FR); (k) William (b. 1778-08-20, FS L69J-4RJ). Note Forman-line maternal-honor naming pattern: 3 of 11 children carry \"Forman\" as given/middle name (one died young, replaced by another bearing the same name).",
      "is_enslaver": true,
