      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_071",
      "sources": "Cocheu 81:3 #354 (cp_sou_052); Monmouth Surrogate Probate File 8481 M, Lib. 39 p. 519 (cp_sou_069); FamilySearch MJ33-KMJ",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-14 (this session). Cocheu 81:3 #354 + FamilySearch MJ33-KMJ confirm identity: b. 1732-12-04, d. 1802-03-03 Upper Freehold, m. Hannah Forman 1756, 11 children. Probate File 8481 M / Lib. 39 p. 519 / administrator Anthony F. Taylor of Burlington Co. uniquely matches Cocheu's \"d. in Upper Freehold, N.J., Mar. 3, 1802, in his 70th year\" — no other Peter Covenhoven died in Monmouth in 1802. Two enslaved women (Charlotte cp_per_104, Elizabeth cp_per_105) and one unnamed enslaved man (Wm Lloyd agreement) are documented in his 1802 estate. KEY CAVEAT: Peter died INTESTATE under the 1799 NJ Act for Distribution of Estates of persons not leaving sufficient property to pay all just Debts (insolvent estate). His enslaved property was sold to creditors rather than distributed to heirs — so this row does NOT establish inheritance chains to his 11 children. Son Elias⁷ #354(b) and daughter Anne⁷ #354(g) acquired their post-1802 enslaved property outside this parental path (separate adjudication HYPOTHESIS-STRONG, deferred 2026-05-14). Ancestry placement: son of cp_ens_044, grandson of cp_fam_069 Pieter Willemse Couwenhoven, great-grandson of cp_fam_007 William² Wolfertse — Gerrit branch / Willem sub-branch / generation 6. | 2026-05-17 ENRICHMENT (all-in-one bundle commit with cp_fam_303 + cp_famsou_016 + cp_famsou_017): (a) 1782 Patriot prisoner episode added per cp_famsou_016 — attests Patriot alignment + Esq. standing during Revolutionary War; (b) son Elias⁷ minted as cp_fam_303 per cp_famsou_017 — Allentown merchant who drowned 1786-11-15 at Powles-Hook ferry, age 27; (c) cp_eve_035 \"Inn Keeper Elias Conover\" HYPOTHESIS-STRONG link to Elias⁷ RETIRED — Elias⁷ died 1786 so cannot be a later Inn Keeper; cp_eve_035 needs reassignment in a future commit (likely to a different/later Elias of Upper Freehold).",
      "raw_related_family": "",
