      "notable_records": "cp_eve_152 (1802-03-23 intestate probate inventory, Monmouth Surrogate File 8481 M, Lib. 39 p. 519; administered under 1799 NJ Act for insolvent estates by Anthony F. Taylor of Burlington Co.). Inventory included 1 Negro Wench Charlotte ($100, cp_per_104), 1 ditto Bound to A. Cox until age 18 Elizabeth ($20, cp_per_105), and an Article of Agreement with Wm Lloyd referencing an unnamed Negro man whose survival triggered installment payments 1803-1804 ($117.87 owed). | cp_famsou_016 (1782-02-08 taken prisoner by Loyalist refugees under Lt. Stevenson during Pleasant Valley raid; captured with Hendrick Hendrickson + 2 sons, Garret Hendrickson, Samuel Bowne + son, and Jacques Denice; rescued by Capt. John Schenck of Col. Holmes's regiment — Patriot political alignment attested).",
