      "children_summary": "10 per Cocheu 82:4 #639 — Garret (bap. 1753-09-30, d. young); Eleena (bap. 1755-01-26); Ariantje (bap. 1757-04-17, perh. m. Joseph Willett); Grietje (bap. 1759-05-09, m. Jacob Allen); Janitje (twin to Grietje, bap. 1759-05-09); Garret (bap. 1761-12-25, m. Nellie Heyer, d. 1817-06-13); Aefje (bap. 1764-04-30, m. John Willett); Altje (bap. 1766-05-25); Tunis (bap. 1769-08-27, m. Martha Vanderhoef, d. 1844-04-11); Elizabeth (bap. 1775-01-15, \"not mentioned in her father's will\" per Cocheu)",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_070",
      "sources": "Cocheu 82:4 #639 (cp_sou_057); Monmouth County Slave Manumissions 1787-1844 (cp_sou_016) — manuscripts cp_eve_074 + cp_eve_075 verbatim transcripts",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-14 (this session). Identity locked via Cocheu 82:4 #639 + 7-attestation documentary consistency across the two 1811 manumission deeds (cp_eve_075 + cp_eve_074): statutory certs, deed body docket, deed body, signature line, acknowledgment block, 1814 + 1834 recording clerks — all wrote \"Elizabeth/Elisabeth\" not \"Eleanor.\" Misread-of-Eleanor (cp_ens_021) hypothesis explicitly REJECTED 2026-05-14: same clerk pool (Lewis Gordon + James Robinson, the two Overseers of the Poor) wrote \"Elizabeth\" for this person in 1811 and \"Eleanor\" for cp_ens_021 in 1822 — distinguishing them in real time. William⁶ #639 (her husband) was a farmer of Freehold per his own 1790 will, and the 1810 probate of that will (NJA:41:88) is the legal mechanism by which the enslaved-property passed to Elizabeth as widow — she then disposed of Henry + Yaff by manumission in April 1811, just months after widowhood. Signed with her mark (illiterate). The 23-year filing gap on cp_eve_074's recording suggests her own death may have triggered the 1834 estate-finalization filing. Adjacent Cocheu reference: she's a daughter of Tunis & Helena (Lane) Aumack of the Monmouth Aumack family. Branch is In-law (married into Covenhoven via William⁶ #639).",
