      "father_text": "Petrus Aertse Van Pelt (1704-1781) — per Find a Grave family panel; primary support pending",
      "mother_text": "Antje Dorlandt Van Pelt (1712-unknown) — per Find a Grave family panel; primary support pending",
      "spouse_text": "Nicasius (Nicholas) Cowenhoven — cp_fam_033 Gerret's deceased son per 1781 will; gravestone reads 'wife of Nicholas Cowenhoven' (Nicholas = Anglicized Nicasius). MARRIAGE DATE: WikiTree Van_Pelt-274 lead asserts 1778-10-18 in Brooklyn, but this conflicts with son Garrett's (cp_ens_014) primary-confirmed birth 1774-05-02 — marriage would post-date Garrett's birth by 4.5 years. Either (a) WikiTree date wrong, (b) earlier marriage existed, or (c) 1778-10 might actually be Nicasius's death (matching Chris's October 1778 hypothesis). PRIMARY MARRIAGE RECORD STRONGLY NEEDED. **NICASIUS'S DEATH DATE = MAJOR UNSOLVED MYSTERY** per Chris: shortly before August 1776 OR October 1778. Required documentation.",
      "children_summary": "Per cp_fam_033 Gerret's 1781 will: Nicasius and Nelly's children = '6 children: granddaughters Antie, Geertie, Sarah, Elizabeth, Nieltie + grandson Garret' — 5 daughters + 1 son. Son: Garrett (cp_ens_014, 1774-1840). Daughters' birth dates and adult fates pending Chris's primary research.",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "evidence_status": "not-documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_016",
      "sources": "GRAVESTONE — New Utrecht Cemetery, Bensonhurst, Kings Co. NY: 'In memory of NELLY VAN PELT, wife of Nicholas Cowenhoven, who departed this life Sep[r] 21st 1817, aged 82 years 2 months 4 days.' Find a Grave Memorial #66234788 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/66234788) — multiple gravestone photographs (overview by S Sh, detail by Jackie). CP_FAM_033 GERRET'S 1781 WILL — NY Wills and Probate Records 1659-1999, Vol 0035-0039 pp.222-225 — names widow Nieltie. CROSS-REFERENCE: cp_ens_014 Garrett row (Nelly's son) provides additional family context. DISCOVERY POINTERS (NOT authoritative per feedback_genealogy_aggregator_authority): WikiTree Van_Pelt-274 (https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Van_Pelt-274) asserts birth 1735-07-27, marriage 1778-10-18, death 1817-09-21; the marriage date conflicts with Garrett's 1774 birth and is suspect. Find a Grave Memorial #66234788 family panel — names parents, siblings, husband.",
      "notes": "**CRITICAL UNSOLVED MYSTERY — Husband Nicasius's death date** (per Chris 2026-04-25): either 'shortly before August 1776' OR 'in October 1778'. Primary documentation REQUIRED for chronology of Cowenhoven household management. WikiTree Van_Pelt-274 asserts marriage to Nicasius 1778-10-18, which conflicts with son Garrett's 1774 birth and may indicate the 1778-10 date is actually Nicasius's death misrecorded as marriage in WikiTree. **NELLY'S ENSLAVER ROLE:** per Chris, ran the New Utrecht household 1783-~1795 (Gerret cp_fam_033's death → Garrett's majority). 9-12+ year window where she was primary enslaver; pre-dates the 1799 NY law birth-indenture records that constitute the bulk of cp_ens_014 Garrett's documented Active linkages 1803-1822. **FAMILY NETWORK:** Sister **Elizabeth Van Pelt Cowenhoven** (1745-1786, FaG #66234780) — also married into Cowenhoven family; FUTURE FAMILY/ENSLAVER candidate (two Van Pelt sisters → two Cowenhoven men is a notable interfamily pattern). Other siblings: Rem Van Pelt (1738-1829), Aurt Van Pelt (1748-1829), Sarah Van Pelt Duryee (1750-1813), John Van Pelt (1754-1798), Capt Peter Van Pelt (1776-1809). Parents Petrus Aertse Van Pelt (1704-1781) + Antje Dorlandt Van Pelt (1712-unknown). **Aggregator-vs-primary discipline:** Three different July 1735 birth dates across sources — WikiTree 1735-07-27, FaG indexer 1735-07-23, gravestone-derived ~1735-07-17. Gravestone wins; the 6-10 day variation in aggregator dates underscores why aggregators are leads only. **CHRIS IS A DIRECT DESCENDANT** through this line — Nelly is his 5G-grandmother (mother of his 4G-grandfather Garrett cp_ens_014). Primary research informs this row. **FOLLOW-UPS (PRIORITIZED):** (1) PRIMARY DEATH RECORD for Nicasius Cowenhoven — most important unsolved question; check Brooklyn/Long Island church burial registers, Kings Co. probate filings 1776-1779, family bibles. (2) Primary marriage record for Nelly + Nicasius — likely New Utrecht Reformed Church or Brooklyn DRC register, but date remains uncertain (Garrett b.1774 implies pre-1774 marriage). (3) Nelly's own will/probate — Kings Co. NY Surrogate's filings 1817-18; she was 82yo property holder, very likely had one. (4) Primary baptism/birth record (Van Pelt family — likely New Utrecht Reformed Church 1735). (5) Search Active for pre-1799 Brooklyn/New Utrecht enslaver-side rows variant-name attributable to Nelly. (6) Consider sister Elizabeth Van Pelt Cowenhoven (FaG #66234780) for future FAMILY/ENSLAVER row. (7) Potential FAMILY-sheet promotion of Nicasius Cowenhoven (cp_fam_054 candidate) once death date resolved.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Child|cp_ens_014;Spouse|cp_fam_032",
      "notable_records": "(1) GRAVESTONE — New Utrecht Cemetery, Bensonhurst, Kings Co. NY: 'In memory of NELLY VAN PELT, wife of Nicholas Cowenhoven, who departed this life Sep[r] 21st 1817, aged 82 years 2 months 4 days.' Find a Grave Memorial #66234788 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/66234788) — multiple gravestone photographs (overview by S Sh, detail by Jackie). (2) cp_fam_033 GERRET'S 1781 WILL — names 'widow Nieltie' (= Nelly) + 6 children of deceased son Necasie; primary kin anchor. (3) ROLE AS ENSLAVER — per Chris 2026-04-25: ran New Utrecht household 1783 (after father-in-law Gerret cp_fam_033's death) until son Garrett came of age (~1792-95); operated 9-12+ years as primary enslaver. NO Active-sheet linkages currently attributed to her — pre-dates 1799 NY law birth-indenture records that document Garrett 1803-1817; pre-emancipation-era manumission/sale records may surface under variant Anglicized name (Eleanor / Helen / Widow / Mrs.).",
