      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_050",
      "sources": "FindAGrave Memorial 14358883 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/14358883); WikiTree Covenhoven-41 (https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Covenhoven-41); DAR Patriot ID A026771; NJ Wills 1670-1817 abstract via Ancestry collection 2793",
      "notes": "Mint 2026-05-07 from FindAGrave Memorial 14358883 + WikiTree Covenhoven-41 + 1812 will abstract (NJ Wills 1670-1817, Ancestry db). The \"P.\" patronymic resolves to son of Peter Covenhoven (1712-1774). Buried at Old Tennent Churchyard, Manalapan — same churchyard as cp_eve_131/132 Old Tennent church-membership rows ingested 2026-05-07. 7 Active rows backfilled with cp_ens_050 + confidence MATCH.\n\n## COCHEU 81:3 ENRICHMENT (cp_sou_052) — Cocheu's #364 confirmed match to cp_ens_050\n\n**MATCH evidence:** EXACT match on death date (Cocheu: d. 1811-12-24; cp_ens_050: d. 1811-12-24). Birth: Cocheu gives bp date 1740-03-23 Freehold-Middletown DRC; cp_ens_050 had b 1740-01-06 — consistent (b. early Jan, bp. late Mar = standard 2-3 month lag). Wife Jane McGalliard matches.\n\n## Will\nNJA:41:88 — dated 1811-04-29, proved 1812-03-10. Names sons William + Robert + John; daughters Elizabeth Robinson + Leach Ten Eyck. Executors William + Robert; witnesses Nathaniel + Joseph Rue + Aaron Reed.\n\n## 6 children (per Cocheu)\n- (a) Elizabeth b 1772-08-12 m. James Robinson\n- (b) Peter b 1774-12-19 — prob. dy (not in 1811 will)\n- (c) William I. b 1778-01-03 m. Jane Van Derveer\n- (d) Robert b 1781-06-17 m. Gertrude Sutphin\n- (e) John I. b 1784-08-17 m. Lydia Johnson\n- (f) Leah b 1787-01-03 m. William Ten Eyck\n\n## Burial\nOld Tennent Cem cp_pla_073 — burial-cluster anchor for Pieter-Willemse line.\n\n[2026-05-14 inventory-side enrichment] Probate inventory of File 8944 M (1812-02-10) names three additional enslaved persons not specifically devised in the will text: cp_per_115 Dick ($200), cp_per_116 Franck ($200), cp_per_117 Liz ($25). Plus an unnamed woman + child pair appraised at $110 together — minted as cp_rec_028. Both cohorts wired via new cp_eve_160 (Probate Inventory event). Workbook entries for these three rows previously carried the Ancestry indexer's P-as-L misread (col Z = \"John L. Covenhoven\"); corrected this commit. enslaved_people_linked now totals 10 named persons + 1 unnamed pair.",
