      "children_summary": "10 children (per Cocheu 82:3 #541 [cp_sou_056]): (a) Mary⁷ b. 1766-02-08 d. 1855-03-22, m.(1) 1789-08-02 Garret Schenck, m.(2) George G. Bergen of Dutch Neck NJ; (b) Sarah⁷ b. 1767-02-08 (mentioned in father's will); (c) Elizabeth⁷ b. 1769-03-07 d. 1837-11-16, m. ~1790 Cornelius Covenhoven #485 (= Albert-line cousin, son of cp_ens_003 via cp_fam_137 Pieter line per 82:1 cross-reference); (d) Caty⁷ b. 1771-08-19; (e) Ruth⁷ b. 1774-03-04, m. Joseph Grover; (f) Peggy⁷ b. 1778-10-29, m. Elisha Sortore; (g) Abigail⁷ b. 1779-05-10; (h) **William⁷ b. 1781-10-31, m. 1802-02-02 Catharine Van Voorhees** = cp_ens_054 William Covenhoven of West Windsor (1814 Phebe + Eliza HC defendant); (i) John⁷ b. 1784-05-25, m. Margaret Duncan and \"went West\"; (j) Jacob⁷ b. — (mentioned in father's will).",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "evidence_status": "not-documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_058",
      "sources": "Cocheu, Lincoln C. \"The Van Kouwenhoven-Conover Family.\" NYG&BR vol. LXXXII, no. 3 (July 1951): #541 (cp_sou_056). Probate: 1803-11-21 Will (NJA:39:102). EDSM:Ap.VI (Phoebe Bailey parents).",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-10 STAGE 3b per Chris approval. Confidence flag HYPOTHESIS pending NJA:39:102 will text pull (Stage 4) for direct enslaved-person bequests; identification of person is MATCH-grade (Cocheu 82:3 #541 supplies all vitals primary-source). ENSLAVER status inferred from son cp_ens_054 (William of West Windsor, 1814 Phebe + Eliza HC defendant) inheriting/holding enslaved persons — this implies Hermanus also held enslaved persons, but inference is not proof until 1803 will text confirms. **Establishes father chain for cp_ens_054**: Wolphert > Gerrit > Willem (cp_fam_007) > John (cp_fam_057) > William of Penn's Neck (cp_fam_058) > **Hermanus (cp_ens_058)** > William of West Windsor (cp_ens_054). PID 058 chosen to preserve cp_ens_056/057 reservations (Peter Covenhoven of Middletown / Garret I. Conover scaffolding).\n\n[2026-05-29 ANCESTRY ABSTRACT PULL] NJA:39:102 retrieved via Ancestry. Will bequests + inventory $59.95 + son cp_ens_054's pre-1803 separate enslavement triangulate that Harmen himself was not a documented enslaver. Liber 40 p.430 / File 10012 L flagged for any future full-text confirmation. Per session-log 2026-05-29 (Project Data Sets/Follow-ups/), reclassification deferred until demote-without-PID-rename design decision is settled. When that decision lands, this row is a top candidate for cp_ens → cp_fam treatment.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
