      "children_summary": "Per Cocheu #653 (1989 reprint p.84, NYG&BR 82:4 Oct 1951) 8 children with Robert Benson: (a) Robert⁷ Benson b. Dec. 26, 1785; d. June 27, 1872, unmar.; (b) Catharine⁷ Benson b. Dec. 8, 1786; d. Dec. 22, 1817; m. 1809-09-16 John L. Lefferts (b.1781-10-20 d.1829-01-18, son of Jacobus + Maria Lott Lefferts); (c) John Couwenhoven⁷ Benson b. May 7, 1788; d. May 26, 1788 (infant death); (d) **Egbert⁷ Benson** b. Sept. 1, 1789; d. Feb. 25, 1866; m. 1820-05-17 Maria Cowenhoven (granddaughter of cp_ens_001 Judge Nicholas via cp_ens_019 John N. Cowenhoven of New Utrecht + Susan Martense) — **THIS MARRIAGE IS THE DOCUMENTED ORIGIN OF THE \"BENSONHURST\" NEIGHBORHOOD NAME** (cross-cousin marriage; Maria inherited Van Brunt-Lott dowry land descended through cp_ens_001); (e) John Couwenhoven⁷ Benson b. Sept. 29, 1790; mar. Sarah M. Lawrence and d. in 1823 (name re-used after infant brother (c)); (f) Elizabeth⁷ Benson b. Sept. 27, 1791; (g) Maria⁷ Benson b. Jan. 5, 1793; d. Feb. 21, 1875; m. 1823-04-21 Judge Leffert Lefferts of Bedford, L.I. (b.1774-04-12 d.1847-03-22, son of Leffert Lefferts + Dorothea Covenhoven cp_fam_326) — **SECOND cross-cousin marriage in this nuclear-family generation**; (h) Jane⁷ Benson b. Mar. 13, 1794; mar. Dr. R. K. Hoffman. (Lefferts Fam. 1878, pp.94-96 & 135)",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "enslaver_link": "",
      "sources": "Cocheu, Bertrand L. *The Van Kouwenhoven-Conover Family* (NYG&BR 82:4, Oct 1951, p.84, #653) — main attestation; Lefferts Fam. 1878, pp.94-96 & 135 (Cocheu cited source for child details); Find a Grave Memorial #273277441 (Dinah Cowenhoven Benson) https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/273277441/dinah-benson — note: FaG dates DIFFER from Cocheu by ~20 years (FaG: b.1762-01-08 d.1847-05-20; Cocheu: b.1741-11-15 d.1827-05-20); see notes",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-21 from cp_ens_001 Judge Nicholas Cocheu discrepancy review session. Sister of Judge Nicholas (cp_ens_001), via father cp_ens_007 John⁵. **Bensonhurst-name significance:** Her son Egbert Benson married Judge Nicholas's granddaughter Maria Cowenhoven in 1820 — that union is the documented root of the \"Bensonhurst\" Brooklyn neighborhood name (per cp_ens_001/015/019 row notes referencing Cowenhoven-Benson mansion land descent). Mother Catharina Remsen and Benson in-law family Robert + Catharine (Van Borsum) Benson not yet minted. Granddaughter Maria⁷ Benson (cp_fam_327 child g) married her sister Dorothea's son Leffert⁷ Lefferts — double cross-cousin marriage layer in next generation. | **2026-05-21 evening — DATE DISCREPANCY FLAGGED (REVIEW):** Find a Grave Memorial #273277441 (added this date) gives birth = 8 Jan 1762, death = 20 May 1847 (aged 85), buried Green-Wood Cem Section 28 Lot 10776 — same day-of-month for death (May 20) but YEAR offsets BOTH dates by ~20 (1741→1762; 1827→1847). **Cocheu print (1989 reprint p.84, NYG&BR 82:4 Oct 1951, #653 iv.) verified by image-render = \"b. Nov. 15, 1741; d. May 20, 1827\"** — no OCR ambiguity. Biological plausibility STRONGLY favors FaG: 8 children born 1785-1794 (Cocheu lists same), so Cocheu's 1741 birth = age 44-53 at childbirth, FaG's 1762 = age 23-32. Green-Wood burial (cemetery founded 1838) is consistent with either date IF reinterment from earlier site, as FaG explicitly says (reinterred 1875 \"with her husband\"). No hard primary evidence (gravestone image, baptism register, original will) yet examined. Per workflow source-of-truth rule, Cocheu print is canonical until overridden by hard primary; this is flagged for Chris's review before any date update. Egbert son's FaG memorial #66234695 ALSO names parents as \"Dinah Cowenhoven Benson 1762-1847\" — internal FaG consistency on the 1762/1847 dates. Workbook dates retained as 1741-11-15 / 1827-05-20 per Cocheu pending Chris's primary-evidence review.",
      "raw_related_family": "Parent|cp_ens_007; Parent|cp_fam_332; Sibling|cp_ens_006; Sibling|cp_ens_001; Sibling|cp_ens_034; Sibling|cp_fam_326; Spouse|cp_fam_329; Mother-in-law-of-granddaughter|cp_ens_019; Child|cp_fam_330",
