      "notes": "DEMOTED 2026-05-28 from cp_ens_300 to cp_fam_032: no documented enslaving by Nicasius personally; enslaver-status inference (via widow + son) was over-attribution. If primary documentation of his personal enslaving surfaces, promote to mixed-prefix per project convention. | ENSLAVER STATUS — INFERRED, not directly documented. The enslaved household passes from this New Utrecht agricultural establishment to widow cp_ens_016 Nelly Van Pelt and ultimately to son cp_ens_014 Garret. Direct primary documentation of Nicasius personally enslaving (e.g. a 1790-style federal census record — which is impossible since he died in 1778, pre-Census) has not surfaced and is unlikely to surface for any pre-Revolution New Utrecht enslaver since the institutional record-keeping that produced manumission deeds + censuses post-dates his death. Identity is FIRMLY MATCHed via Cocheu #657 + cp_fam_033 1781 will + wife's gravestone. | Minted 2026-05-28 to resolve cp_ens_014 + cp_ens_016 standalone-enslaver chain (see live-tree standalone-enslaver Phase 2 work). | [NOTABLE_RECORDS] (1) cp_fam_033 GARRET'S 1781 WILL — dated 1781-05-09, proved 1784-02-05; WNYHS:12:169-71. Names 'deceased son Nicholas' + 'widow Nieltie' + 6 grandchildren by Nicholas: Garret, Antje, Geertje, Sarah, Elizabeth, Neeltje Covenhoven. Primary-document confirmation of kinship chain Gerret⁵ (#215) -> Nicasius⁶ (#657) -> Garret⁷ (cp_ens_014). (2) Nelly Van Pelt GRAVESTONE, New Utrecht Cemetery, Bensonhurst, Kings Co. NY: 'wife of Nicholas Cowenhoven' (per FaG #66234788). Confirms husband identity. (3) Bergen Ms. (per Cocheu #657 citation). | [ENSLAVED_PEOPLE_LINKED] (none directly documented during his lifetime — widow cp_ens_016 and son cp_ens_014 became enslavers post-1778 via inheritance of the New Utrecht household) | [BIRTH_RECORD] pending — New Utrecht Dutch Reformed Church baptism record search for Jan 1742 | [DEATH_RECORD] pending — New Utrecht Dutch Reformed Church burial record search for Oct 1778; per Cocheu #657 he \"d. there [New Utrecht]\" | [WILL_PROBATE] NO will documented; he died at age 36 with 6 minor children — likely intestate. His father cp_fam_033 Garret's 1781 will treats the household state. NJ/Kings County Letters of Administration search 1778-1781 pending. | [BURIAL_LOCATION] Presumed New Utrecht Dutch Reformed Church Cemetery (now Most Holy Trinity Cemetery, Bensonhurst) — same location as wife Nelly Van Pelt per FaG #66234788. Specific grave + memorial pending.",
