      "children_summary": "George Cowenhoven (cp_ens_018, b.1764-06-09, d.1805-04-13 aged 40); John Nicholas \"John N.\" Cowenhoven (cp_ens_019, 1769-1806, documented inheritor of New Utrecht properties at father's 1793 death per existing row notes — planned ENSLAVER row Stage C-3); other children pending Chris's primary research. Per Chris 2026-04-25: 1790 federal census Town of New Utrecht confirms Judge Nicholas + son George as first two heads of household in the township; the 1790 household tally [4 white M 16+; 0 white M <16; 2 white F; 1 OFP; 10 SLAVES; total 17] suggests at least 4 adult males in the household — Judge Nicholas + John N. (age 21) + 2 unidentified — likely additional adult sons or extended family pending primary research.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
