      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_015",
      "sources": "GRAVESTONE — New Utrecht Cemetery, Bensonhurst, Kings Co. NY: 'wife of Nicholas Cowenhoven, Esq., ae 72 yrs 5 mos 12 dys'. Find a Grave Memorial #66234784 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/66234784/jane-cowenhoven) — 3 gravestone photographs by Christopher Barnes (Chris). NYC MUNICIPAL ARCHIVES — Old Town Records Collection, Town of New Utrecht 'Births and Manumissions of Slaves' (https://nycrecords.access.preservica.com/uncategorized/IO_e89e72bd-74e7-425e-8da9-1de8c2e19fea/) — cp_per_024 Peter 1816 birth indenture. CROSS-REFERENCE — cp_ens_001 row (Judge Nicholas) provides marriage 1763-09-24 NYC, parents Joris Lott + Maria Van Brunt, dowry of hundreds of acres in New Utrecht.",
      "notes": "Wife of cp_ens_001 Judge Nicholas Cowenhoven (m. 1763-09-24 NYC); survived him by 24 years as a widow (1793-1817). Brought hundreds of acres in New Utrecht as her dowry (per cp_ens_001 row notes), indicating Lott-family wealth. Jane managed the New Utrecht household and continued enslaving people post-1793; cp_per_024 Peter's 1816 birth-indenture documents her continued role as enslaver age 71, 3 years before her own death. **CHRIS IS A DIRECT DESCENDANT** through this line — primary research informs this row. The 1817 gravestone inscription confirms husband's title 'Esq.' (Judge of Kings County Court of Common Pleas). **Active linkage cp_per_024 = MATCH** by name + place + date convergence (Town of New Utrecht, 1816, Jane 71yo). The other Active rows with 'Jane Covenhoven/Conover of Freehold, Monmouth Co. NJ' 1806 (cp_per_085 Ceaser, cp_per_086 Sally) are a DIFFERENT person — NJ Monmouth branch, NOT this Jane. **FOLLOW-UPS:** (a) WikiTree profile for Jannetje Lott / Jane Lott Cowenhoven; (b) primary birth/baptism record (Lott family register); (c) primary marriage record (1763-09-24 NYC — should be in NYC Dutch Reformed or Anglican parish register); (d) Jane's will/probate (likely left one — 72yo property holder); (e) full child roster.\n\n**Children George + John identified 2026-04-25 (Chris):** see cp_ens_018 + cp_ens_019 rows for primary documentation.\n\n**2026-05-21 Cocheu discrepancy review — parallel cleanup from cp_ens_001 own-row pass:** Spouse field collapsed to bare PID (was carrying her late husband's full title + marriage history + widowed date inline). Marriage date/place moved to dedicated cols (marriage_date 1763-09-24, marriage_place New York City, marriage_place_id cp_pla_038). Burial filled from Find a Grave Memorial #66234784 (cp_pla_053 = New Utrecht Reformed Church). Death place_id = cp_pla_009 (Bensonhurst = neighborhood within Town of New Utrecht; same residence). Per Cocheu #654 (1989 reprint p.84, NYG&BR 82:4 Oct 1951, husband Judge Nicholas's main entry): “On Sept. 24, 1763, he mar. Jannetje Lott b. Jan. 14, 1745; d. June 26, 1817, a daughter of Joris & Maria (Van Brunt) Lott.” Per [[reference-cocheu-numbering-conventions]] wives are unnumbered in Cocheu; cocheu_page populated as husband's entry page; cocheu_number left blank.",
