      "occupation": "Widow + household manager / enslaver post-1823 (succeeded husband Johannes cp_ens_013 upon his 1823-09-13 death; documented as \"Mrs. Conover\" head of household on 1830 federal census, p394, Town of New Utrecht)",
      "father_text": "(pending — Stellerwerf family lineage)",
      "mother_text": "(pending)",
      "spouse_text": "Johannes Van Couwenhoven (cp_ens_013), b. 1746-10-04, d. 1823-09-13. Exact-year birth peers (both 1746). Catherine outlived him by ~20 years and ran the New Utrecht household as widow 1823–1843. Marriage date pending primary (likely New Utrecht Reformed Church register, late 1760s given son George b. 1764 and son John b. 1769).",
      "children_summary": "(pending Chris's primary research — Catherine + Johannes's documented children not yet identified. NOTE: George Covenhoven (1764-1805) and John N. Covenhoven (1769-1806), this stage's planned cp_ens_018 + cp_ens_019, are NOT Catherine's sons; per Chris 2026-04-25 they are sons of Judge Nicholas Cowenhoven cp_ens_001 + Jane Lott cp_ens_015. The Garret J. Cowenhoven hypothesis (J. = Johannes-son patronymic, 1822 Nan manumitter) referenced in cp_ens_013's row notes remains a separate deferred follow-up — not yet attributable to Catherine specifically.)",
      "is_enslaver": false,
      "evidence_status": "not-documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_017",
      "sources": "1830 FEDERAL CENSUS — Town of New Utrecht, Kings County, NY, page 394 — \"Mrs. Conover\" entry. FamilySearch image 775-776 of 814, image group 005155934 (https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/3:1:33S7-9YY6-92FR?view=index for image 775; https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/3:1:33SQ-GYY6-9XSG?view=index for image 776). NB: FamilySearch indexes this group under \"Westchester, New York\" but the page margin clearly reads \"New Utrecht / Kings County\". Local archived copies in /Source Documents/New Utrecht 1830 Federal Census - Page 394/. CROSS-REFERENCE: cp_ens_013 Johannes Van Couwenhoven row (her husband, exact-year birth peer 1746, d.1823-09-13). FHNU 3.21.26 deck slide 45 (\"1830 Federal Census\") provides Chris's authoritative reading of the white-side tally. DISCOVERY POINTERS PENDING: WikiTree Stellerwerf / Catharine Stellerwerff lookup; Find a Grave New Utrecht Cemetery for Catharine Cowenhoven (d.1843).",
      "notes": "**SPOUSE LINKAGE = MAJOR FINDING (2026-04-25):** Catherine resolves the \"(pending)\" spouse field on cp_ens_013 Johannes Van Couwenhoven. Both born 1746; she outlived him 1823→1843 and appears as \"Mrs. Conover\" head of household on 1830 New Utrecht census p394 = primary documentation of her continuing as enslaver post-widowhood. **CHILDREN CORRECTION (Chris 2026-04-25):** Earlier draft hypothesized George Covenhoven (1764-1805) + John N. Covenhoven (1769-1806) as Catherine + Johannes's sons based on biological-fit math, BUT per Chris these two are sons of Judge Nicholas Cowenhoven (cp_ens_001) + Jane Lott (cp_ens_015) — confirmed by 1790 federal census, Town of New Utrecht, where the first two heads-of-household entries are Judge Nicholas + son George, and \"John N.\" = \"John Nicholas\" patronymic = the documented inheritor of Judge Nicholas's New Utrecht properties at his 1793 death. Catherine + Johannes's actual children remain pending. **GARRET DISAMBIGUATION (Chris 2026-04-25):** The \"Garret Conover\" head of household one row above \"Mrs. Conover\" on the 1830 census is cp_ens_014 Garret Cowenhoven (Nicasius/Nelly's son, b.1774) — geographic neighbor, not Catherine's son. The hypothesized \"Garret J. Cowenhoven\" (Johannes-son patronymic, manumitter of Nan cp_per_003 1822-06-06; referenced in cp_ens_013 row notes) is a separate person, not yet on the ENSLAVER sheet, and not identified with this 1830 census line. **CHRIS IS A DIRECT DESCENDANT** through the New Utrecht / Jan Gerretse line — this row sits in Chris's documented ancestral cluster. **FOLLOW-UPS (PRIORITIZED):** (1) WikiTree profile lookup for Catherine Stellerwerf / Catharine Stellerwerff — capture wikitree_url + wikitree_id; (2) primary marriage record for Catherine + Johannes (likely New Utrecht Reformed Church 1760s); (3) Catherine's will/probate (Kings Co. NY Surrogate's filings 1843–44; she was 97yo property holder, very likely had one); (4) primary baptism/birth record (Stellerwerf family); (5) Find a Grave memorial search — she would have a stone in New Utrecht Cemetery alongside Johannes; (6) 1820 federal census linkage (would show Catherine + Johannes still co-resident pre-widowhood); (7) **cp_ens_013 spouse field backfill** (paired edit committed with this row 2026-04-25); (8) **cp_ens_014 1830 census tally backfill** (paired Stage C-4 opportunity — 12 persons, 0 colored per Chris 2026-04-25 correction of slide 45 error); (9) Catherine + Johannes's actual children — primary research pending; the Garret J. Cowenhoven (1822 Nan manumitter) hypothesis remains on cp_ens_013's row but no specific person is yet attributed to Catherine.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Spouse|cp_ens_013",
      "notable_records": "(1) 1830 FEDERAL CENSUS — Town of New Utrecht, Kings County, NY, page 394, listed as \"Mrs. Conover\" head of household, 13 persons total. White-side composition (validated against FHNU slide 45 + high-res PDF 1 read 2026-04-25): WHITE MALES — 5-9: 1. WHITE FEMALES — 10-14: 1; 40-49: 2; 70-79: 1 (Catherine herself; her actual age 84 placed her in 80-89 — census-taker under-aged her). Free-colored-side composition (high-res PDF 2 column-placement read 2026-04-25): SLAVES — 0 in all columns; FREE COLORED MALES — Under 10: 2; 10-24: 2; 36-55: 2. FREE COLORED FEMALES — Under 10: 1; 36-55: 1. Total free colored in household = 8; total enslaved = 0. By 1830 Catherine no longer held legally enslaved people, consistent with 1827 NY abolition; the 8 free colored persons are very likely formerly enslaved by Catherine + cp_ens_013 Johannes pre-1827 and remained as household members post-emancipation. Source: FamilySearch image group 005155934, images 775 + 776 of 814 (record indexed under \"Westchester, NY\" at FamilySearch but the image margin clearly reads \"New Utrecht / Kings County\"). (2) Inferred succession to cp_ens_013 Johannes's New Utrecht enslaver role 1823–1843. (3) Co-listed on same census page as \"Garret Conover\" (one row above), who is cp_ens_014 Garret Cowenhoven (Nicasius/Nelly's son, b.1774) per Chris 2026-04-25 — geographic neighbor, not kin.",
      "enslaved_people_linked": "(none on 1830 census — Catherine held 0 enslaved per high-res PDF 2 read; Stage C-4 still needs to scan Active and UNNAMED sheets for pre-1827 enslaver-side rows attributable to \"Catharine Cowenhoven\" / \"Mrs. Conover\" / \"Mrs. Cowenhoven\" / variant Anglicized renderings; Catherine's enslaver role pre-1827 is implied by the 8 free colored persons in her 1830 household)",
