      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_072",
      "sources": "Cocheu NYG&BR 81:3 (Jul 1950) #117 + #360 [cp_sou_054]; Find a Grave Memorial #39831878 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/39831878/daniel-covenhoven); Schenck-Covenhoven Graveyard, Penns Neck NJ — FaG Cemetery #2259696 (https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/2259696/schenck-covenhoven-graveyard); Schenck-Couwenhoven Cemetery, Holmdel NJ — kin-burial cross-reference per Cocheu 81:3 #117 + 81:4 #124; FamilySearch Person KPHM-B6C (https://www.familysearch.org/en/tree/person/details/KPHM-B6C); cp_per_137 + MCHA collection photograph (Chris field photograph, 70 Court Street display)",
      "notes": "## Identification\nCocheu 81:3 #360 (1950) recorded \"Daniel⁶ bap. Aug. 3, 1746; no further record.\" 2026-05-15 (Chris) supplied Find a Grave Memorial #39831878 from Schenck-Couwenhoven Cemetery Holmdel: Daniel Covenhoven b. 1742, d. 18 Feb 1821, aged 78–79. Identification ANCHOR: same family burial ground as father Elias⁵ (cp_ens_044), mother Williampe, uncle Roelof⁵ (cp_fam_104), and family-network Schenck kin per Cocheu 81:3 #117 + 81:4 #124. HYPOTHESIS: birth-year discrepancy 1742 (FaG back-calc) vs 1746 (Cocheu bap.) = 4-yr gap; gravestone age may be misread (stone is heavily weathered per photo); Cocheu's bap. record takes priority pending physical re-examination.\n\n## Disambiguation context\n2026-05-15 disambiguation work on cp_per_137 (Amy 1789 sale) — distinguished from cp_ens_042 Daniel G. Conover by (a) middle-initial rule per project 5/11 hard rule (cp_per_137 doc says \"Daniel\" no initial; Daniel G. used \"G.\" consistently from 1786 marriage onward); (b) death year (1821 vs 1823 probate); (c) burial cemetery (Schenck-Couwenhoven Middletown vs Daniel G.'s Marlboro/Monmouth association). See cp_eve_163 narrative.\n\n## Geographic timeline\n~1742-46 born Middletown Twp, Monmouth Co. NJ (presumed — father resident). 1789 active in Monmouth Co. — purchased Amy from Rulef Vanmater per cp_eve_163 / cp_per_137. 1821-02-18 died Middletown / Holmdel area. Buried Schenck-Couwenhoven Cemetery Holmdel (post-1857 Holmdel; pre-1857 part of Middletown Twp).\n\n## Kin network\nFather: Elias⁵ Covenhoven (cp_ens_044). Mother: Williampe Wall. Siblings per Cocheu #117 enumeration: Mary #353 (b.1730), Peter #354 = cp_ens_071 (b.1732), John #355 = cp_ens_020 (b.1733), Patience #356 (b.1736), Lydia #357 (b.1738), Jane #358 (b.1739), Sarah #359, Anne (in father's 1750 will but not enumerated by Cocheu), Daniel #360 = THIS PID, + unborn child mentioned in 1750 will. Cocheu's \"Children: 10\" with only 8 enumerated suggests Anne + 1 other are missing from the published enumeration.\n\n## Naming pattern signals\n\"Daniel\" — no middle initial attested in any source. Adult name on gravestone: \"Daniel Covenhoven\" (no initial). Per project 5/12 patronymic rule, his Dutch-pattern name would be \"Daniel Eliase Covenhoven\" (= son of Elias) but no middle initial or full patronymic appears in any document. The no-initial profile matches the cp_per_137 1789 bill of sale text exactly.\n\n## Research targets pending\n- Monmouth Co. Surrogate filings 1821-1822 for Daniel Covenhoven probate\n- Freehold-Middletown DRC marriage register 1765-1790 for marriage record\n- Wife / children identification (resolve Cocheu's \"no further record\")\n- Physical re-examination of gravestone to resolve 1742 vs 1746 birth-year discrepancy\n- WikiTree profile creation candidate (no profile located in pre-mint scan)",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "cp_ens_044 (father Elias⁵); cp_ens_020 (brother John, Cocheu #355); cp_ens_071 (brother Peter of Upper Freehold, Cocheu #354)",
