      "mother_text": "Elizabeth Johnson (per cp_fam_143 spouse field; though WikiTree Couwenhoven-133 marks 'mother unknown' so a possible 1st wife of Lucas Willemse cannot be ruled out)",
      "spouse_text": "Femetie / Lammetie Van Voorhees (cp_fam_247) — m. ~1775 Middlesex NJ. Baptized Femetie 1743-07-13 Six Mile Run DRC Somerset Co. NJ; d. 1816-08-07 West Windsor Twp Middlesex Co.",
      "children_summary": "No children documented per WikiTree Couwenhoven-133. Per 1807 will, primary heir of enslaved persons was 'Wife, Lamy' (Lammetie) — no children named.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_063",
      "sources": "WikiTree Couwenhoven-133 (https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Couwenhoven-133); DAR Genealogical Research Database (cp_sou_060): https://services.dar.org/Public/DAR_Research/search_adb/?action=full&p_id=A210200; Calendar of New Jersey Wills Vol. VI (cp_sou_059) p.557 — Lib. 19 p. 389: 1807-02-17 will / proved 1809-01-27. NJ Rev War Slips: Single Citations of the NJ DOD Materials, FHL Roll #569441.",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-10 (session: 9 (none)-bucket enslaver attribution arc). **NEW MINT — upgraded from planned cp_fam to cp_ens after Active sheet scan revealed his 1807 will named 2 enslaved persons.** Brother of cp_ens_035 Lucas (Luke) Conover — both sons of cp_fam_143 Lucas Willemse Couwenhoven (b.1716, d.1777 Windsor NJ). Named in father's 1777 will: 'Son, Rut, 150 acres of land on the south side of my homestead; also 50 acres on Assanpink, called the Bainbridge Pasture' + 'To each of my 3 sons, William, Rut and Luke, £200.' **Rutgert is the 4th Cowenhoven Patriot + enslaver tension case in the project** (alongside cp_ens_020 Col. John Eliase Covenhoven, cp_ens_031 Brooklyn Jacob Cowenhoven, and the implicit DAR-era others). The DAR vs WikiTree day-of-death discrepancy (Jan 5 vs Jan 9 1809) — use DAR as primary (service slip is closer to primary). His brother Luke died ~16 months later, intestate. Wife Lammetie Voorhees (cp_fam_247) survived him to 1816 — became an enslaver in her own right via inheritance of Eve + Bob.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Father|cp_fam_143;Sibling|cp_ens_035 (Luke Conover);Spouse|cp_fam_247 (Lammetie Voorhees)",
      "notable_records": "**Revolutionary War service:** Soldier, Middlesex County Militia, NJ Militia (per DAR A210200, NJ Rev War Slips FHL Roll #569441). **DAR Patriot Ancestor #A210200**. **1807-02-17 will / proved 1809-01-27 East Windsor Twp Middlesex Co. NJ** (Calendar of NJ Wills Vol. VI p.557; Lib. 19, p. 389): 'Wife, Lamy, household and kitchen furniture, a covered waggon, 2 horses, 3 cows, 1 sleigh, **a negro woman named Eve, and a boy named Bob**, to be at her disp[osal].' Inventory taken 1809-01-08, £600.13.6, by Coert Voorhies and David Slaback.",
      "enslaved_people_linked": "cp_per_081 (Eve, adult woman, transferred to widow Lammetie per 1807 will / 1809 probate); cp_per_082 (Bob, boy/child, transferred to widow Lammetie per same will). Active sheet 'Rutes Covenhoven' rows now wireable to this new cp_ens.",
      "will_probate": "1807-02-17 dated / 1809-01-27 proved (East Windsor Twp Middlesex Co. NJ)",
