      "mother_text": "Mary Van Doren (m. 1750-11-05 NJA:22:76; daughter of Arie & Antje Schenck Van Doren; bap. 1731-03-31 Marlboro NJ; survived husband to 1792).",
      "spouse_text": "Sequential wives: (1) Arriantje (d. 1780); (2) Eleanor Smock (d. 1788); (3) Nelly Schenck (mother of Rulef cp_ens_033, b.1791) — three-wives chain not yet primary-verified",
      "children_summary": "14 children per 1815 will: Aaron (mill + carding machine + Plum and Ivy); John (co-executor, $62.50); Jacob Jr. (cordwainer-Jacob, future cp_ens_034 candidate, $125); Margaret Schenck; Mary; Rulef (= cp_ens_033, co-executor + co-residuary heir); Isaac (co-executor + co-residuary heir); Elizabeth Dubois; Anne Denise; Nelly Schanck; Catherine (under 21 in 1815); Jane; Sarah; Arintha. Mother Mary Conover still alive 1815.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_032",
      "sources": "Wills Vol A pp.704-705 (primary); NJ Abstracts Vol XLII File 9130 M (abstract); WikiTree Van_Couwenhoven-94; FS 9XVG-F8C\n\nCocheu 82:2 #522 [cp_sou_055] — primary citation establishing father chain: NYG&BR vol. LXXXII, no. 2 (April 1951), pp. 92-93. Also referenced: NJA:42:102-03 (1815 will).",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-04-28 PM (this session, deferred to 2026-04-28 at end of work). Identity resolved: the \"Jacob Janse\" placeholder was the Miller; mint name normalized to \"Jacob (Van Couwenhoven) Covenhoven.\" Witness \"John I. Holmes\" (per will body) vs. \"John S. Holmes\" (per FamilySearch abstract) — initial visually similar in 1815 script; primary confirmation pending an enlarged image of the witness signatures. Three-wives chain not yet primary-verified; baptisms of Jacob Sr.'s 14 children would settle which wife mothered which child.\n\n[2026-05-10] Father chain established via Cocheu 82:2 #522 (cp_sou_055): Wolphert > Gerrit > Willem (cp_fam_007) > Jacob (cp_ens_009) > John (cp_fam_133) > **Jacob the miller (cp_ens_032)**. Cocheu records baptism Jan 19, 1752 at Freehold-Middletown DRC; workbook birth date 1751-11-11 retained as primary entry per Chris 2026-05-10 directive — Cocheu bap. date may indicate birth ~Dec 1751/early Jan 1752 with 1751-11-11 from alternative source. Three wives + 15-children pattern matches Cocheu exactly. First-cousin marriage to Ariantje #502 (daughter of his uncle Jacob #162 = cp_fam_130). Death date 1815-04-28 matches Cocheu \"Apr 28, 1815\" exactly.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Father|cp_fam_133; Grandfather|cp_ens_009; Sibling|various John Jacobse children (Cocheu #523-#529); Spouse(1)|Ariantje Covenhoven #502 (daughter of cp_fam_130 Jacob Jacobse — first-cousin marriage); Spouse(2)|Eleanor Smock (daughter of John Smock + Elizabeth Covenhoven cp_fam_193 #317); Spouse(3)|Nelly Schenck (daughter of Peter Schenck + Jannetje Hendrickson — same Jannetje who was widow of cp_ens_010 Roelof, Jacob the miller's uncle); Father of cp_ens_033 Rulef Conover.; Child|cp_ens_033; Child|cp_ens_073; Spouse|cp_fam_343; Spouse|cp_fam_346; Spouse|cp_fam_347",
      "notable_records": "1815-04-24 will (cp_eve_004 — corrected this session); will signed 4 days before death. Bequeathed \"my Negro boy Elias\" (cp_per_206) to son Rulef in clause 14. Wife (Nelly Schenck, presumed) entitled to maintenance \"during her widowhood\" per clause 3. | 1812 manumission of Joseph Reeves (cp_eve_068, Monmouth Manumission Book p. 148 — self-described \"Yeoman of Middletown\" on this deed); 1819 post-mortem manumission of Amey by William Conover acting executor (cp_eve_069, Monmouth Manumission Book p. 48).",
      "enslaved_people_linked": "cp_per_206 Elias (1815 will, bequeathed to Rulef); cp_per_164 Charlotte; cp_per_165 Ann (Charlotte's mother — Ann's matrilineal connection makes Charlotte and Elias siblings); cp_per_058 Joseph Reeves (1812 manumission, age 35, cp_eve_068); cp_per_069 Amey (1819 post-mortem manumission via William Conover acting executor, age 26, cp_eve_069)",
