      "notes": "Confirmed identification 2026-05-05 via FS LKCH-534 + Dutch naming-honor pattern. Born 1751 — the year his uncle Elias-A (cp_ens_044) died — and named for the deceased uncle by his father Peter Pieterse Covenhoven, who served as cp_ens_044's will-executor (cp_eve_010, Lib. E p. 478). Married Catherine Forman 1774-10-02; only one child (Eleanor 1776-1859). Died young at age 35 in 1786 (cause unknown). DIFFERENT PERSON from later Eliases: 1804 Inn keeper of Upper Freehold (cp_eve_035), 1812-1816 Colonel of Freehold (cp_eve_061-066), and 1821 Township of Freehold manumitter (cp_eve_089) all post-date Elias-B's 1786 death. Those records belong to a third-generation Elias (or Eliases) — likely a nephew via brother John P. (LKCC-X2L), William (LKCC-J65), or Ruleff (MF66-R67), or a cousin via Willem Pietrse line. 1772 co-bondsman 'John Covenhoven' on cp_eve_091 most likely = older brother John P. Covenhoven 1740-1811 (FS LKCC-X2L), age 32 in 1772, rather than first cousin cp_ens_020 (age 38 in 1772, Freehold Twp not Middletown).",
