      "spouse_text": "Ann Wyckoff (1773-1870, FS L638-9V7) — m. 1790-03-27 Richmond, New York (= Richmond County, today's Staten Island NY). NOTE: Luke's elder brother William cp_ens_026 also married a Wyckoff (Annatie Wyckoff FS L6MR-8F9, m. 1778-12-12 Flatlands RDC) — double-Wyckoff brothers'-marriage pattern, possibly to sisters or cousins; brides born 12 years apart (Annatie 1761, Ann 1773). Echoes the Couwenhoven brothers ↔ Schenck sisters double-marriage in cp_ens_002 + cp_ens_004.",
      "children_summary": "Per Cocheu 82:4 #617 (cp_sou_057, p. 217) — FOUR children by his only wife Ann Wyckoff (m. 1790-03-27 Flatlands; b. 1773-06-24 Flatlands, d. 1870-02-20 aged 96, daughter of Joost & Sarah (Luyster) Wyckoff): (a) Antje⁷ b. 1791-03-15, d. 1880-10-23, unmar. (b) George⁷ b. 1792-12-11, d. 1874-11-21 (aged 81 yrs 11 mos 10 dys); m. 1817-12-25 Helena Duryea. Eldest son; pending cp_fam_NNN or cp_ens_NNN mint. (c) Gerrit⁷ b. 1795-05-15, d.y. (infant death). The name was reused for child (d) per Dutch reuse-of-name convention. Pending cp_fam_NNN mint if Chris wants for completeness. (d) Gerrit⁷ b. 1797-09-23, d. 1887-01-05, unmar. = **cp_fam_301** (Gerrit Kouwenhoven of Flatlands; 1827 JP candidate + Flatlands inspector of elections per cp_famsou_008; long-lived bachelor to age 89; minted 2026-05-17 after pre-mint scan via Cocheu 82:4 deep-read traced him from the 1827 election notice). Cocheu cites 'Wyckoff Fam. 1934, p.241; Fam. Bible rec.' at end of #617.",
