      "children_summary": "7 children per FS KLQS-ZTM: Catherine 1776-1797 (MRZG-GYX); Julia Ann 1781-1834 (LCPV-22G); Eleanor 1785-1866 (KPW7-4NF); Jane Conover 1785-1858 (G426-QBD); John Edward Conover 1786-1833 (M5BT-BHS); Elias jr [=cp_ens_047] 1790-1826 (KLQS-8VM); Eliza 1797 (M5BY-CVF). Mixed Conover/Covenhoven surnaming within this generation.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_046",
      "sources": "FamilySearch KLQS-ZTM (https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/KLQS-ZTM); cp_eve_061-064, cp_eve_066 (Monmouth Black Birth Book BBB 1812-1816); cp_sou_015 (Slave Births 1804-1848 Monmouth NJ collection)",
      "notes": "Confirmed identification 2026-05-05 via FS KLQS-ZTM + age/rank match to cp_eve_061-066 BBB cluster. Born 1757, son of cp_ens_020 John Elias Covenhoven (1734-1803, FS GJ7Y-PV2). Married Anna Fish 1780-10-14 Marlboro NJ; 7 children. Already referenced in cp_ens_020 col R as executor of cp_ens_020's 1802 will. Militia 'Colonel' rank attested in 1812-1816 BBB filings — Revolutionary/War-of-1812 era senior officer (age 55-59 at attestation = correct generation for War of 1812 colonelcy). Died 1820, age 63. CRITICAL DISTINCTIONS: (1) NOT the 1804 Inn keeper of Upper Freehold (cp_eve_035) — separate Elias-C attribution held pending verification of township + occupation overlap; (2) NOT the 1821 Township of Freehold manumitter (cp_eve_089) — Col Elias died 1820, one year before; that record belongs to his son Elias jr (cp_ens_047). Surname appears as both 'Conover' (BBB filings) and 'Covenhoven' (FS, family records) within this generation — all variants point to the same KLQS-ZTM man. | 2026-05-17 ENRICHMENT (cp_famsou_021 1779 Shrewsbury raid): Captured by British April 26, 1779 at age 22, alongside his father cp_ens_020; carried off to NY. This is the earliest documented biographical event for cp_ens_046 — predates his 1780 marriage to Anna Fish by ~18 months. Captivity may have influenced his later military career (militia Colonel by 1812-1816 BBB filings).\n\nCocheu vol 81:3 #355 places his birth in 1756 (1 year earlier than FS KLQS-ZTM and FaG year). FaG stone inspection would settle. Current default = FS + FaG 1757. Burial confirmed Old Brick per FaG cohort screenshot 2026-05-19 (Doc. cohort entry, veteran \"v\" badge visible).\n\n\n\n2026-05-20: Wife Anna Fish promoted to own row cp_fam_324 per Old Brick mint batch.",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Father: cp_ens_020 John Elias Covenhoven (1734-1803). Grandfather: cp_ens_044 Elias Covenhoven (1707-1750). First cousin once removed: cp_ens_045 Elias Covenhoven (1751-1786). Sister: Agnes Johnse Covenhoven 1758-1832 (FS KLQS-Z4V). Wife: Anna Fish (FS LH6T-6JF). Son + heir: cp_ens_047 Elias Covenhoven jr. (1790-1826, FS KLQS-8VM).;; Spouse|cp_fam_324 (Anna Fish, m. 1780-10-14, d. 1821-11-15; FaG #132987285)",
      "notable_records": "cp_eve_061 (Betty cp_per_219 BBB 1812-05-01); cp_eve_062 (Rose cp_per_220 BBB 1813-12-01); cp_eve_063 (Susan cp_per_216 BBB 1814-07-07); cp_eve_064 (Jude cp_per_221 BBB 1815-03-01); cp_eve_066 (James cp_per_222 BBB 1816-10-28). 5 BBB filings 1812-1816 by 'Colonel Elias Conover' / 'Elias Conover' of Freehold. | cp_famsou_021 (1779-04-26 captured by British during Shrewsbury raid at age 22, alongside his father cp_ens_020 John Covenhoven of Monmouth; \"justice Covenhoven and son\" per Penna Evening Post Apr 30, 1779; carried off to NY by British detachment). Earliest documented biographical event for cp_ens_046 — predates his 1780 marriage to Anna Fish by ~18 months.",
      "enslaved_people_linked": "7 attested via BBB 1812-1816: cp_per_218 Lucy (mother, multi-event — 3 children); cp_per_217 Maria (mother, multi-event — 2 children); cp_per_219 Betty 1812; cp_per_220 Rose 1813; cp_per_216 Susan 1814; cp_per_221 Jude 1815; cp_per_222 James 1816.",
      "will_probate": "Pending verification — Col Elias died 1820, expect Monmouth probate; widow Anna Fish d. 1821",
