      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-17 (all-in-one bundle commit with cp_famsou_016 + cp_famsou_017 + cp_ens_071 enrichment). Second son (Cocheu order item (b)) of cp_ens_071 Peter Covenhoven of Upper Freehold + Hannah Forman. Named after paternal grandfather cp_ens_044 Elias⁵ of Middletown per Dutch patronymic convention (grandson-named-for-paternal-grandfather pattern). Merchant at Allentown, NJ (in Upper Freehold Twsp, Monmouth Co.). Drowned attempting to cross Powles-Hook ferry 1786-11-15, age 27, leaving a young family. Identified via 1786 obit explicitly naming \"son of Peter Cowenhoven, Esq. of Monmouth county\" — age + residence + family standing triangulate to cp_ens_071. Previously held HYPOTHESIS-STRONG = \"Inn Keeper Elias Conover of Upper Freehold\" per cp_eve_035 in cp_ens_071's children_summary; this link is RETIRED per cp_famsou_017 (Elias⁷ died 1786-11-15, cannot be the cp_eve_035 Inn Keeper). cp_eve_035 attribution needs reassignment to a different/later Elias (possibly Elias⁷'s son named for father per Dutch convention, or a different Upper Freehold Elias). Wife + children not named in obit; pending future research.",
