      "children_summary": "10 children with Margaret Holman per FS L6TP-F64: Isaac Covenhoven (cp_fam_217, 1791-1832, FS K8X1-7LW); Ann Covenhaven (cp_fam_218, 1794, K8XR-Y2M); Joseph Conover (cp_fam_219, 1796, KCXK-KZG); Hannah Conover (cp_fam_220, 1797-1826, KC9C-YV9); Margaret Ann Covenhoven (cp_fam_221, 1799-1875, L4TP-R2G); Sarah Covenhoven (cp_fam_222, 1803, KHDG-2H9); Thomas Morford Covenhoven (cp_fam_223, 1808-1845, KZGQ-X3F); Katharine Conover (cp_fam_224, 1808, 98BH-5HN); Mary Jane Covenhoven (cp_fam_225, 1810, KHB5-Z1B); William Conover (cp_fam_226, 1810-1862, KZ3T-S1H).",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_038",
      "sources": "PRIMARY: 1806-03-12 + 1808-07-03 Slave Birth Book entries (cp_eve_038 + cp_eve_054, cp_sou_015); 1810-01-06 manumission deed of Joe (cp_eve_077, cp_sou_016, Monmouth Manumission Book pp. 119-120, OPRSFile-24.pdf at /Source Documents/Monmouth Manumissions/).; FamilySearch L6TP-F64 (https://www.familysearch.org/tree/person/details/L6TP-F64); FS L69X-YXJ (father Isaac B); Cocheu 82:1 #146 (cp_sou_054)",
      "notes": "Identified 2026-05-05 from the 1810-01-06 manumission of Joe (cp_eve_077, OPRSFile-24.pdf = Manumission Book pp. 119-120). Same-person identification with the BBB Thomas Covenhoven of Middletown (Farmer) is high-confidence: same first name, same Middletown Township, same Monmouth County, time period overlaps (1806-1810 at minimum). Period-occupation disambiguation rule satisfied (no occupation conflict; Farmer + no-occupation-stated is compatible). The 1810 deed signature shows Thomas Covenhoven (with the typical late-1700s/early-1800s Dutch-Anglicized spelling) sealing personally before Judge Thomas Little of the Court of Common Pleas. Open follow-ups: WikiTree profile, parentage, primary kinship to other Monmouth Covenhovens (Garret/Cornelius/etc. of the same era).\n\nRESEARCH 2026-05-07: Date-gap workstream investigation. Strongest FS candidate identified: **Thomas Covenhoven L6TP-F64** (b. 1767-06-03 Freehold Twp Monmouth NJ; christened 1767-09-13 Monmouth NJ — 1 primary source via 'New Jersey, Births and Christenings, 1660-1980'; 5 child christenings 1794-1808 in NJ documenting Isaac, Anne, Sarah, Thomas Morford, Margaret Morford; 1816 Ohio County Marriage record indicating OH residence by then; FS profile claims d. 1836-11-23 Fountain Indiana but THAT DEATH DATE HAS 0 SOURCES on the profile — so death is still unanchored). Match to cp_ens_038 is HYPOTHESIS-grade only: age fit (39-43 during 1806-1810 events), geographic fit (NJ presence through 1808 + OH by 1816 explains absence of NJ records post-1810), and name fit (Thomas Covenhoven / Thomas Conover both spellings on FS profile, matching cp_ens_038 row's name_variations); BUT no primary record yet directly ties L6TP-F64 to the BBB filings (cp_eve_038/054) or the 1810 Joe manumission deed (cp_eve_077). Possible Duplicate FS profile M5BY-XXL was checked (2026-05-07) — no info, not useful for disambiguation. **Spouse correction:** prior aggregator-grade claim of 'Margaret Holman ca. 1792 Freehold' (in earlier workstream notes) is likely WRONG — children Thomas Morford Conover and Margaret Morford Conover (both b. 1808) carry 'Morford' as middle name, which by period naming convention indicates the mother's maiden surname. Wife's actual maiden name is therefore likely **Margaret Morford**, not Holman. **Open work to promote L6TP-F64 from HYPOTHESIS to MATCH:** (a) compare signature handwriting on OPRSFile-24.pdf (cp_eve_077, Joe 1810 manumission) against the FS reference to 'his own handwriting on daughter's marriage records' under the Name field Reason note on L6TP-F64; (b) NJ Slavery Records search for additional identifying detail on the 1806/1808/1810 Monmouth events; (c) anchor the 1836 Indiana death date to a primary record (FS profile lacks one). Different Thomas to disambiguate FROM: KZK4-R4B (1803-1882, son of Cornelius Covenhoven and Margeret Hans, christened Dutch Reformed Church Freehold and Middletown 1804 — too young to be the cp_ens_038 enslaver active 1806-1810). KZK4-R4B confirmed 2026-05-07 NOT cp_ens_038.\n\n**ENRICHED 2026-05-10 (9 (none)-bucket attribution arc):** Father chain locked via FS L6TP-F64 (Chris-shared screenshot 2026-05-10): Isaac B Covenhoven (1735-1804) = son #447 in cp_ens_011's 1786 will children list (Cocheu 82:1 #146 cp_sou_054). 7-gen patrilineal walk: Wolphert → Gerrit → Willem cp_fam_007 → Albert cp_ens_002 → Willem cp_ens_011 → Isaac B cp_fam_210 → Thomas cp_ens_038. Isaac B had 2 marriages (Hannah Morford 1756 = Thomas's mother; Elizabeth Thompson ~1775).",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Parent|cp_fam_210; GrandParent|cp_ens_011 (William Albertse); GreatGrandParent|cp_ens_002 (Albert Willemse); Mother|cp_fam_211 (Hannah Morford); Stepmother|cp_fam_212 (Elizabeth Thompson); Spouse|cp_fam_213 (Margaret Holman); Sibling|cp_fam_214; Sibling|cp_fam_215; Sibling|cp_fam_216; Child|cp_fam_217; Child|cp_fam_218; Child|cp_fam_219; Child|cp_fam_220; Child|cp_fam_221; Child|cp_fam_222; Child|cp_fam_223; Child|cp_fam_224; Child|cp_fam_225; Child|cp_fam_226",
      "notable_records": "(a) 1806-03-12 Slave Birth Book registration of Samuel cp_per_156 (mother Rose cp_per_157), filed under \"Thomas Covenhoven of Middletown Township (Farmer)\" — cp_eve_038; (b) 1808-07-03 Slave Birth Book registration of Jim cp_per_168 (mother Rose cp_per_157), same enslaver attribution — cp_eve_054; (c) 1810-01-06 Manumission of Joe cp_per_055 (age 21-40, statutory window) — cp_eve_077, Monmouth Manumission Book pp. 119-120; recorded 1810-02-12. Certified at Shrewsbury Township (overseers John West + Peter Wolcott; justices Thos. Little + Elihu Chadwick) rather than Middletown — possible procedural choice (Middletown overseers unavailable Jan 6, 1810).",
      "enslaved_people_linked": "cp_per_055 (Joe — manumitted 1810 cp_eve_077) | cp_per_157 (Rose — BBB mother of Samuel + Jim, cp_eve_038 + cp_eve_054) | cp_per_156 (Samuel — son of Rose, b. 1806 cp_eve_038) | cp_per_168 (Jim — son of Rose, b. 1808 cp_eve_054)",
