      "notable_records": "1802-10-19 will of cp_ens_023 (testator father, manuscript pp. 339-340) names Cornelius co-executor + heir to SW half of 280-ac plantation + Jack immediately + £150 bond forgiven (PRIMARY). 1814-06-28 manumission of Eve cp_per_177, Franklin Twsp Somerset (SCHQ 1.4 p.276). 1819-09-13 manumission of Jack cp_per_179, Franklin Twsp Somerset (SCHQ 1.4 p.277). 1820-09-13 manumission of Dinah cp_per_180, Franklin Twsp Somerset (SCHQ 1.4 p.277). 1834-06-10 manumission of John Cuffee cp_per_182 by 'Cornelius Conover' (SCHQ 2.1 p.50) is POST cp_ens_024's 1822 death — likely his eldest son Cornelius (1795-1873, FS L9CN-WLY) as cp_ens_025+ candidate.",
