      "occupation": "Landholder (inherited New Utrecht estate from cp_ens_001 Judge Nicholas at father's 1793 death); militia officer with rank Major (recognized in dataset framing parallel to \"Judge\" Nicholas; rank tagged in Active R6 1799 manumission AKA col); enslaver",
      "father_text": "Nicholas Cowenhoven (cp_ens_001) — Chief Judge, Kings County Court of Common Pleas; b. circa Sept 1744 New Utrecht, d. 1793-03-07",
      "mother_text": "Jane (Jannetje) Lott Cowenhoven (cp_ens_015) — b. 1745-01-14, d. 1817-06-26 Bensonhurst",
      "spouse_text": "Susan Martense (cp_fam_359, minted 2026-05-30) of Flatbush (m. 1802 — primary marriage record pending; check Flatbush Reformed Dutch Church register)",
      "children_summary": "Maria Cowenhoven b. 1803-04-06, d. 1867; m. Egbert Benson 1820 — Bensonhurst neighborhood naming origin via Maria's inherited grandfather/grandmother farmland (Van Brunt-Lott dowry land descended through Judge Nicholas + Jane Lott to Major John to Maria). Jane Cowenhoven b. 1805-02-01 Flatbush. Both daughters inherited bulk of New Utrecht properties at Major John's 1806 death. | Updated 2026-05-21: Maria minted as cp_fam_331 (b.1803-04-06 d.1867-02-25, m.1820-05-17 Egbert Benson cp_fam_330 — the Bensonhurst-name origin marriage).",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_019",
      "sources": "WikiTree Cowenhoven-72 (https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Cowenhoven-72) — aggregator, leads only, uses incorrect \"H.\" middle initial; Find a Grave Memorial #66234787 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/66234787/john-cowenhoven) — burial + death year, indexer-asserted; brooklyngenealogy.blogspot.com \"The Last Homestead of Modern Bensonhurst\" (Oct 2015, http://brooklyngenealogy.blogspot.com/2015/10/the-last-homestead-of-modern-bensonhurst.html) — secondary biographical narrative including birth/marriage/death dates and daughters' inheritance trail. Active R6 + R13 + R15 = primary archival enslaver records (City of Brooklyn Old Town Records / Town of New Utrecht Old Town Records, NYC Municipal Archives, https://nycrecords.access.preservica.com/).",
      "notes": "Son of Judge Nicholas (cp_ens_001) + Jane Lott (cp_ens_015); brother of George (cp_ens_018, b.1764). The \"N.\" patronymic = Nicholas-son per Brooklyn-Dutch convention (parallel to \"R.\" = Rem-son in cp_ens_005/008). Sometimes misread as \"John H. Cowenhoven\" because manuscript script-N can resemble script-H — including on his own WikiTree profile (Cowenhoven-72) which uses the wrong middle initial; dataset standardizes on \"John N.\" Dataset also adopts \"Major John\" framing parallel to \"Judge Nicholas\" treatment of his father (per Chris 2026-04-25). Direct ancestor of Bensonhurst neighborhood naming via daughter Maria → Egbert Benson 1820 (Maria inherited grandmother Jane Lott's New Utrecht farmland — Van Brunt-Lott dowry). Chris (project lead) is 4th-great-grand-NEPHEW of Major John — Chris descends from cp_ens_018 George (Major John's brother), so Major John is collateral kin, not direct ancestor; both brothers shared parents cp_ens_001 Judge Nicholas + cp_ens_015 Jane Lott. **No primary biographical source ingested yet — birth_record / death_record / will_probate cells flagged pending; Chris will share when located.** Active enslaver phase 1793-1806 (post father's death to own death). 3 MATCH linkages so far; FOLLOW-UP: search Active + UNNAMED for the mothers of Cesar (cp_per_012, b.1800) and Francis (cp_per_014, b.1805) — both should have enslaved-women mothers in Major John's New Utrecht household (see Follow-ups/cp_ens_019_mother_search.md).",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Parent|cp_ens_001; Parent|cp_ens_015; Sibling|cp_ens_018; Child|cp_fam_331;Spouse|cp_fam_359",
      "notable_records": "(1) Active R6 1799-02-28 Brooklyn Manumission of Jacob (cp_per_005) — AKA col 27 \"Major\" attaches the militia rank to this John; \"Other people mentioned: Nicholas R. Covenhoven\" (cp_ens_005, Brooklyn-Bedford cousin) — manumission filed in Brooklyn town clerk's book despite Major John's New Utrecht residence, possibly via cousin Nicholas R. (2) Active R13 1800-05-01 New Utrecht Birth registration of Cesar (cp_per_012) under the 1799 Gradual Abolition Act of NY — \"John N. Cowenhoven.\" (3) Active R15 1805-09-10 New Utrecht Birth registration of Francis (cp_per_014) under same act — \"John N. Cowenhoven.\" (4) Inheritance 1793-03 from cp_ens_001 (Judge Nicholas) of New Utrecht properties. (5) 1820 inheritance pass-through from his estate via daughter Maria → husband Egbert Benson → Bensonhurst neighborhood naming origin.",
      "enslaved_people_linked": "cp_per_005; cp_per_012; cp_per_014",
      "will_probate": "(pending — death 1806-11-03; properties bequeathed to daughters Maria + Jane per secondary; check Kings Co. NY Surrogate's filings 1806-11 through 1807)",
      "burial_location": "New Utrecht Cemetery, Bensonhurst, Kings County, New York. Find a Grave Memorial #66234787 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/66234787/john-cowenhoven)",
