      "children_summary": "Per 1840 will (primary): eldest son Nicholas Cowenhoven (named for paternal grandfather Nicasius per Brooklyn-Dutch convention); son-in-law Major Thompson (executor; given name vs. military rank ambiguous, surname Thompson); plus additional sons + daughters named in bequest clauses but not committed pending Chris's verification of handwriting (per Chris 2026-04-25). Daniel A. Couwenhoven receives a $300 bequest; relation pending. See /Source Documents/Garret Cowenhoven of New Utrecht Will/analysis.md.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_014",
      "sources": "cp_sou_030 — WILL — Will of Garret Cowenhoven, Kings County Surrogate's Court, NY, dated 1840-01-20, probated January 1842 (Allen Spooner, Surrogate); pp. 138-149 of will book (volume/liber pending Chris's verification). Source images + analysis at /Source Documents/Garret Cowenhoven of New Utrecht Will/. CP_FAM_033 GERRET'S 1781 WILL — NY Wills and Probate Records 1659-1999, Vol 0035-0039 pp.222-225. NEW UTRECHT TOWN RECORDS — Old Town Records Collection, NYC Municipal Archives (https://nycrecords.access.preservica.com/uncategorized/IO_e89e72bd-74e7-425e-8da9-1de8c2e19fea/). FIND A GRAVE MEMORIAL #66234781 — https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/66234781/garret-cowenhoven; New Utrecht Cemetery, Bensonhurst, Kings County, NY; gravestone photo by 'S Sh'; inscription 'ae 65 yrs 8 mos 26dys' supplies primary support for both death date 1840-01-28 and (by calculation) birth date 1774-05-02. DISCOVERY POINTERS (NOT authoritative, per feedback_genealogy_aggregator_authority): WikiTree Cowenhoven-6 (https://www.wikitree.com/wiki/Cowenhoven-6); WikiTree Van_Couwenhoven-84 — father Nicasius's profile.",
      "notes": "New Utrecht / Jan-Gerretse line. Father: Nicasius Cowenhoven (1742-1793, deceased by 1781 per cp_fam_033's 1781 will — 'deceased son Necasie'); widow Nieltie = Nelly Van Pelt. **GRANDFATHER:** Gerret Van Couwenhoven (cp_fam_033) — primary kin anchor via 1781 will. **UNCLE:** Johannes Van Couwenhoven (cp_ens_013, 1746-1823) — also enslaver, also New Utrecht; contemporaries operating in the same town. The 'Garret J. Cowenhoven' rendering on cp_per_003 Nan's 1822 manumission is a scribal variant of THIS Garret's name (per Chris 2026-04-25), NOT a different Johannes-son Garret. **DEATH-DATE RESOLUTION 2026-04-25:** Earlier WikiTree '1840-01-20' was indeed a misrecording of will-signing date as death date; primary gravestone (Find a Grave #66234781) confirms actual death 1840-01-28 — eight days after signing the will, consistent with deathbed disposition. **BIRTH-DATE PRIMARY SUPPORT:** Gravestone inscription 'ae 65 yrs 8 mos 26dys' + death 1840-01-28 yields birth 1774-05-02 by arithmetic; matches WikiTree's prior unverified date but now grounded in primary evidence. **CHRIS IS A DIRECT DESCENDANT** — Garrett is his 4th-great-grandfather via the New Utrecht line. Primary research informs this row. **OTHER GARRETS in the dataset (NOT this row):** (a) cp_fam_046 Gerritt Cowenhoven (different person, son of cp_fam_029 John, named in 1753 will, generation removed); (b) NJ-Monmouth Garrets — cp_per_039 Cain 1781 Penn's Neck (Garret too young); cp_per_060/062/065 Monmouth manumissions 1817-1826 ('Garret Rezo Covenhoven' for cp_per_062); cp_per_091 + cp_per_118-122 Freehold 'Garret Covenhoven Senior' testator d. ~1812; cp_per_160-161 Monmouth 1806; (c) cp_per_040 Maria Philips 1827 Bedford 'Garreta Cowenhoven' — could be different Garret or our Garret relocated, unresolved. **SIDE FINDING from Find a Grave search:** cp_ens_001 Judge Nicholas has memorial #66234789 at same New Utrecht Cemetery; Elizabeth Van Pelt Cowenhoven (1745-1786, FaG #66234780) at same cemetery is a Van Pelt-branch lead (potential aunt or sister-in-law of Garrett's mother Nelly Van Pelt). **FOLLOW-UPS:** (a) verify volume/liber for Kings County will book (pages 138-149); (b) Chris's verified child roster from primary research; (c) actual primary birth/baptism record (gravestone supplies date but is a death record, not a birth record per se); (d) potential FAMILY-sheet promotion of father Nicasius (cp_fam_054 candidate); (e) consider cp_per_040 Maria Philips Bedford 1827; (f) consider Elizabeth Van Pelt Cowenhoven for FAMILY-sheet entry (Van Pelt branch).",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Parent|cp_ens_016;Parent|cp_fam_032;Spouse|cp_fam_358",
      "notable_records": "(1) WILL [cp_sou_030] — Garret Cowenhoven of New Utrecht, dated 1840-01-20, probated January 1842 — Kings County Surrogate's Court (Allen Spooner, Surrogate); will book pp. 138-149 (volume/liber pending). Names wife Annetta, eldest son Nicholas, son-in-law Major Thompson as executor; multiple children + bequests; NO enslaved people named (consistent with NY emancipation effective 1827). Source images archived at /Source Documents/Garret Cowenhoven of New Utrecht Will/. (2) NEW UTRECHT TOWN RECORDS — 6 birth indentures under 1799 NY law for enslaved people: Dinah cp_per_013 (b.1803-01-24), Grass cp_per_015 (b.1806), Mink cp_per_016 (b.1809), Lid cp_per_017 (b.1811), Rose cp_per_018 (b.1814), Cate cp_per_019 (b.1817); plus 1822-06-06 manumission of Nan cp_per_003 ('Garret J. Cowenhoven' rendering, scribal variant per Chris). (3) cp_fam_033 GERRET'S 1781 WILL — names 'grandson Garret' via deceased son Necasie + widow Nieltie; primary kin anchor establishing Garret alive in 1781.",
