      "residence_primary": "Freehold Township, Monmouth Co. NJ. Source evidence: (1) 1815-01-16 BBB filings cp_eve_039+059 self-ID \"I Garret I. Conover of Freehold in the County of Monmouth\"; (2) FS KHYN-Q97 parents marriage 1771-04-23 at \"Freehold, Freehold Township, Monmouth, New Jersey\". Generation-skipping note: paternal grandfather cp_fam_131 was \"late of Middletown\" per FaG stone, but cp_fam_131 → Jacob Gerrit branch had relocated to Freehold by 1771.",
      "occupation": "Yeoman / farmer (presumed; Monmouth Dutch landholder generation; no direct occupational attestation in available sources — Cocheu 82:2 #506 enrichment for father Jacob Gerrit may yield more)",
      "father_text": "Jacob Gerrit Van Couwenhoven (FS LZKB-1GX, b.1746-06-19 d.1825-10-18; Cocheu 82:2 #506 son of cp_fam_131 Gerret Jacobse Couwenhoven). NOT YET MINTED in workbook FAMILY sheet — cp_fam_NNN mint candidate (companion to this enslaver mint).",
