      "children_summary": "5 children per FS KHYN-Q97: (a) Jacob Garretse Covenhoven 1800-1828 (FS GT1W-MT5) — eldest son named per Dutch convention after paternal grandfather Jacob; \"Garretse\" patronymic confirms naming chain Jacob→Garret→Jacob; (b) Mary Conover 1802-1886 (FS LH3X-41N); (c) Rebecca Hendrickson Conover 1805-1892 (FS MPLQ-CHP) — middle name memorializes mother's Hendrickson family; (d) Catherine S Conover 1808-1828 (FS L6XC-3Y4); (e) Alice H Conover 1814-1855 (FS LHLQ-PKC). Mixed Conover (4 children) + Covenhoven (1 child, the eldest) surname rendering typical of transitional generation.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_076",
      "sources": "FS KHYN-Q97 (primary identity); FS LZKB-1GX (father Jacob Gerrit); FS LZZJ-TBF (mother Mary Schenck); FS L7JV-CCH (spouse Alice Hendrickson); FS GT1W-MT5 (eldest son Jacob Garretse, validates patronymic); cp_sou_015 (Monmouth BBB); cp_eve_039 + cp_eve_059 (1815 BBB filings); MonmouthSlaveBirths_p050.pdf (manuscript image); Cocheu 82:2 #506 (father Jacob Gerrit — citation pending pull).",
      "notes": "NEW MINT 2026-05-26 PM (Stage 6 Garrets disambiguation commit). Evidence stack — 5 elements MATCH per strict-3+ adjudication convention (reference_adjudication_tier_convention 5/26): (1) patronymic I.=Iacobse via father Jacob Gerrit; (2) age 33 in 1808 / 36 in 1811 / 40 in 1815 filing — all plausible enslaver-of-record ages; (3) \"of Freehold\" township in 1815 BBB self-ID matches FS-confirmed parental marriage Freehold Twp 1771-04-23; (4) eldest son named \"Jacob Garretse Covenhoven\" 1800 (FS GT1W-MT5) — naming chain Jacob→Garret→Jacob validates I.=Iacobse patronymic on this family; (5) \"Conover\" surname form matches GoM_007 family (4 of 5 children Conover). FAN consistency: same-day 1815-01-16 BBB co-filing with cp_ens_046 Col Elias Conover = Freehold-neighbor proximity (not kinship per cp_ens_020 children-list analysis). Promoted from GoM_007 working-sheet row on Garrets_of_Monmouth_County. cp_fam_NNN companion mint for father Jacob Gerrit deferred to next session. BBB-filings-are-enslavement-attestation precedent per cp_ens_066/067 (Williams batch 2026-05-12).",
