      "sources": "Bedford Nicholas Cowenhoven 1809 will (cp_eve_021); 1810-01-27 Brooklyn town manumission certificate (cp_eve_022). See /Source Documents/Nicholas R. Cowenhoven 1809 Will/analysis.md\ncp_famsou_023 (1790 marriage notice in The Daily Advertiser, April 27, 1790) — primary attestation of marriage date + groom + officiant; merged 2026-05-22 from former FAMILY row 289 (now consolidated).\nCocheu, Bertrand L. (NYG&BR 82:4 Oct 1951, p.83-84, #651(e) + #652(c)) — firm birth date 1775-01-28, firm death date 1856-04-01, mother correction to Ida Lefferts.",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-04-28 PM. Sister of Bedford Nicholas (cp_ens_005) per the 1809 will text naming \"my sister Sarah & John Lefferts.\" Mother assumed Magdalene Van Vechten per Chris 2026-04-28 (Rem's 1st wife and documented mother of cp_ens_005); 2nd-wife identity for Rem still pending. Birth/death/marriage dates not yet sourced. Husband John Lefferts minted as cp_rel_007 on the RELATED sheet 2026-04-28 PM. Disambiguation: NOT the same person as Leffert Lefferts of Bedford, who was the third co-executor on Bedford Nicholas's 1809 will and 1810 manumission certificate.\n\n## PROMOTED FROM FAMILY (2026-05-10 single-sheet migration)\nEvidence: Sarah (Cowenhoven) Lefferts — joint enslaver via clause 12 of brother Bedford Nicholas's 1809 will (cp_eve_021): Frank cp_per_155 + Jenny cp_per_197\nOriginal enslaver_status field: Joint enslaver via clause 12 of brother Bedford Nicholas's 1809 will (cp_eve_021): Frank cp_per_155 + Jenny cp_per_197 transferred jointly to Sarah + her husband John Lefferts during the children's minority, with manumission required at age 14. Also named jointly in clause 11 public-charge backstop (Sarah + John bear 1/3 of maintenance for Thomas cp_per_044 + Neen cp_per_045 if either becomes a public charge).\n\n## 2026-05-22 ENRICHMENT + CONSOLIDATION (cp_ens_006 Cocheu review session)\n- **MOTHER CORRECTED** (D1): from 'Magdalene Van Vechten (Rem's 1st wife)' → 'Ida Lefferts (cp_fam_334) — Rem's 2nd wife' per Cocheu #651 explicit '5 children — 4 by Magdalene and 1 by Ida' AND Cocheu #652(c) cross-attestation 'a daughter of Rem Covenhoven No.651 and his 2nd wife, Ida Lefferts.' Original 2026-04-28 mint had honestly flagged 'mother assumed Magdalene per Chris; 2nd-wife identity for Rem still pending' — that pending now resolved.\n- **DATES FILLED** (D2): birth_date=1775-01-28, death_date=1856-04-01 per Cocheu #651(e) + #652(c). Both numbers cross-attest in two separate Cocheu entries.\n- **MARRIAGE INFO** added: marriage_date=1790-04-25, marriage_place text per cp_famsou_023 1790 marriage notice (Rev. Mr. Schoemaker officiating).\n- **CONSOLIDATION** (Finding 2): per [[feedback-mixed-prefix-no-rename]] (5/17 rule), this row was duplicated in FAMILY row 289 (minted 2026-05-17 alongside cp_famsou_023). FAMILY row 289 carried richer marriage data + 'enslaver_status=Possible' analysis + cp_famsou_023 source. All non-duplicating data merged into this ENSLAVER row 59 this session; FAMILY row 289 deleted. Rationale per Chris's 2026-05-22 directive: 'Consolidate into ENSLAVER, delete FAMILY row' — Sarah's 1809-will custodial enslavement of Frank cp_per_155 + Jenny cp_per_197 + public-charge backstops on cp_per_044/045 justify ENSLAVER-sheet residence.\n- cocheu_number=651(e), cocheu_page=83 backfilled.\n- birth_place_id=cp_pla_002 (Town of Brooklyn) presumed.\n- father / mother / spouse fields updated to bare-PID convention per cp_ens_001/007 precedent.",
