      "notes": "Stub-mint 2026-05-06. South Brunswick Twsp, Middlesex Co. NJ, Farmer. 7 enslaved people on record across 6 birth-registration events spanning 1811-1822 (filed in 2 certs 1814-11-29 + 1825-04-09). Two enslaved mothers: Kate (Cyrus 1811 + Pamele 1813) and Betty (George 1815 + Loeser 1817 + Gerrans 1820 + Fran 1822). Manuscript signature on both certs reads 'Johnson Conover'; project canonical 'Cownover' retained per Chris 2026-05-06. Possible kinship to William W. Covenhoven (also South Brunswick) — research follow-up. Other research follow-ups: birth date, death date, spouse, parentage, WikiTree match.\n\nDISAMBIGUATION 2026-05-07 PM (Chris-shared FS L69J-QG2 + WikiTree Conover-1057 screenshots): b.1781 d.1849, m. 1804-06-13 First Presbyterian Church, Cranbury, Middlesex Co. NJ to Ann Elizabeth Disbrow (1785-1841, FS L7G7-53Z).\n\nLINEAGE: 4-generation NJ branch from immigrant Willem Gerritsen Van Couwenhoven (1636-1728) → cp_ens_002 Albert Willemse → cp_ens_011 William Albertse → William W. Covenhoven (HELD cp_ens candidate, 4 enslaved already linked) → cp_ens_049 Johnson. The \"possible kinship to cp_ens_049\" follow-up flagged in 5/6 session is now CONFIRMED: William W. is Johnson's father.\n\nWHITE-CHILDREN-vs-ENSLAVED-CHILDREN PARALLEL (project-significant): Johnson's white children and the enslaved children of Kate (cp_per_133) were born in the same household in the same years: 1811 — Johnson's son Elias Johnson Conover (b.1811, FS M5YJ-28L) + Kate's son cp_per_134 Cyrus (b.1811-06-12, cp_eve_138); 1813 — Johnson's son James Story Conover (b.1813, FS M5YV-FWB) + Kate's daughter cp_per_248 Pamele (b.1813-08-10, cp_eve_139). Two mothers in the same house bearing children in the same years; one bound, one free. Important biographical context for Kate's WikiTree profile.\n\nSIBLING ENSLAVER CANDIDATES (cp_ens follow-on queue): (a) Elias Covenhoven 1780-1845 (FS LD1Y-MBC) — distinct from cp_ens_044/045/046/047 Elias quad, this is the Albert-Willemse line via William W.; (b) William W. Conover Jr. 1783-1837 (FS L6MR-N3S) — same-name-as-father warning; (c) Lucas Covenhoven 1785-1810 (FS L6T5-4J4) — POSSIBLE MATCH for cp_ens_035 Lucas Conover, verification needed (cp_ens_035 residence South Amboy vs. this Lucas presumed Cranbury/South Brunswick; both Middlesex Co. NJ, same approx death year 1810).\n\n[2026-05-10 STAGE 82:1.C] Father chain locked. Father William W. Sr. minted as cp_ens_059 in same session per Chris approval. Generation now formalized as 7. Confidence flipped from blank to MATCH (Cocheu 82:1 #449 [cp_sou_054] supplies all kinship plus 9-children sibling list).",
