      "notable_records": "(1) cp_eve_149 + cp_sou_041 — 1801-04-04 runaway of Harry (cp_per_129), age adult, 5'9\"-5'10\" — cp_per pending mint; runaway ad in True American (Trenton) Apr 14 1801 p.3 with $40 reward signed William Conover; NJ Slavery Records EVE-01030 / NJS-PER-02451. (2) cp_eve_148 — 1814 NJ Supreme Court Case 34538*, State of New Jersey v. William Covenhoven: Habeas Corpus to produce Phebe (cp_per_194), age 40+, status Freed Person at time of case; case file also references Eliza (cp_per_195), daughter of Phebe, status Liminal. (3) 1803-11-21 named co-executor of father Harmen Covenhoven's will (West Windsor). DOCUMENTED ENSLAVED FOOTPRINT: 3 named individuals (Harry 1801; Phebe + Eliza 1814).",
