      "name_variations": "Garret R. Conover (cert form on cp_eve_083 1823); Garret Rezo Conover (deed body form on cp_eve_083); Garret Rezo Covenhoven (Find A Grave canonical Memorial #252782441); Garret Rezo Cowenhoven; Garret Rezo Couwenhoven (orthographic variants per Monmouth Dutch convention). Per Chris 2026-05-05: 'Rezo' = anglicization of REZEAU / RESEAU, the French Huguenot surname carried as a middle name (mother's maiden name convention common in Dutch/Huguenot colonial NJ families). FaG canonical spelling 'Garret Rezo Covenhoven' validates 'Rezo' as a real spelling, not a manuscript misread.",
