      "children_summary": "Two children, both died in infancy: Child #1 d. ~28 June 1823, aged ~0.2.12; Child #2 d. ~14 Dec 1837, aged ~0.5.11. Names lost — children's headstones decayed beyond reading by 1931 per FaG bio note. NO surviving issue documented.",
      "is_enslaver": true,
      "evidence_status": "documented",
      "enslaver_link": "cp_ens_041",
      "sources": "PRIMARY: cp_sou_016 Slave Manumissions, 1787-1844, Monmouth County, NJ — Manumission Book p.111. EXTERNAL: Find A Grave Memorial #252782441 (https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/252782441/garret-rezo-covenhoven). WikiTree / FamilySearch IDs pending; cp_sou_037 (NJ Supreme Court Case 34539 — AMBIGUOUS attribution, see Col U); Cocheu NYG&BR 82:2 #509 (cp_sou_055); EDSM (per Chris-shared screenshot 2026-05-10)",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-05 PM (this session) inline per Chris approval, on the 1-record evidence chain (cp_eve_083 1823) + Find A Grave external anchor Memorial #252782441 (matched 2026-05-05 PM via Chris's screenshot review). Confidence = HIGH. Identification anchored by: (a) name match (FaG canonical 'Garret Rezo Covenhoven' = manuscript deed-body form 'Garret Rezo Conover' = dataset col Z 'Garret Rezo Covenhoven' across all four sources); (b) lifespan fit (b.1787, alive 1823 at age 36 — prime slaveholding age); (c) geography (FaG burial at Conover Family Burial Ground, Colts Neck, Monmouth = Middletown-area, matches cp_eve_083's 'Township of Middletown' residence); (d) Schenck-family network match (his wife Mary Schenck = same Monmouth Dutch Schenck network as cp_ens_040's wife Maria Gerritse Schenck).\n\nDISTINCT from cp_ens_040 Garret Covenhoven of Upper Freehold per 17-year birth gap + different township + different spouse; possibly first cousins or 1st-cousins-once-removed via Schenck endogamy.\n\nTwo children both died in infancy (~1823 + ~1837 per FaG epitaph; stones decayed beyond reading by 1931); no surviving issue documented. Wife Mary Schenck d. 25 Dec 1830 (epitaph age 35.9.3 → b. ~Mar 1795). Garret Rezo himself died 22 Oct 1861 (epitaph age 74.9.25). Burial: Conover Family Burial Ground, Colts Neck, Monmouth County, NJ. Note name change Covenhoven → Conover already in evidence by his death epitaph (consistent with mid-19th-century Anglicization pattern across the Monmouth Dutch Conover/Covenhoven lineages).\n\n(2026-05-08 RESEARCH NOTE superseded — see DISAMBIGUATION below.)\n\n2026-05-08 DISAMBIGUATION: Demoted to ALTERNATIVE attribution for NJ Supreme Court Case 34539 (Habeas Corpus + Contempt for Clara, 1813-1814). Per disambiguation analysis, primary attribution shifted to cp_ens_040 Upper Freehold on three lines of evidence: NAMING (case-file lacks middle initial; this Garret used R./Rezo middle in his 1823 deed and FaG memorial); LIFE-STAGE (this Garret was 26 with no surviving children in 1813; cp_ens_040 was 43 with established standing and just-inherited enslaved man Jack); PATTERN (this Garret has only the 1823 James Lloyd manumission; cp_ens_040 has the 1813 case + 1817 + 1826 documented). Cross-reference retained; SSV00002 Minutes Book 113 review remains path to definitive resolution.\n\n**ENRICHED 2026-05-10 (9 (none)-bucket attribution arc):** Father link via Cocheu 82:2 #509 (cp_sou_055) child (a): 'Garret Rezeau⁷ b. 1786-12-27, m. Maria Schenck 1815-01-19.' Mother Margaret Rezeau cp_fam_203 (new mint this commit). Birth refined from FaG year-only '1787' to Cocheu primary '1786-12-27.' Brother cp_ens_043 Daniel D. died within 16 hours (1861-10-21 per Cocheu vs Garret Rezo 1861-10-22 per FaG/gravestone 1931 reading).",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Father|cp_ens_042 (Daniel G.);Grandfather|cp_fam_131 (Gerret Jacobse);Great-grandfather|cp_ens_009 (Jacob Willemse);Mother|cp_fam_203 (Margaret Rezeau);Sibling|cp_ens_043 (Daniel D., brother);Sibling|cp_fam_204/205/206/207/208 (other cp_ens_042 children — Mary, Tylee, Eleanor, Elizabeth, Daniel d.y.);Cousin (via cp_ens_009)|cp_ens_031 + cp_ens_055 (via cp_fam_132 line)",
      "notable_records": "cp_eve_083 — 1823-05-14 manumission of James Lloyd (cp_per_062), age ~31, in Township of Middletown; deed signed before Overseers Wm. Little + Daniel Haber and Justices of the Peace Samuel Holmes + John Hobart; recorded by Monmouth County Clerk Wm. Ten Eyck. Manumission Book p.111. PARTIAL — deed body continuation pending.",
