      "notes": "Child (d) of Cocheu 82:4 #617 Luke⁶ (= cp_ens_028) by his only wife Ann Wyckoff (m. 1790-03-27 Flatlands). One of 4 children. Named for paternal grandfather Gerret Willemse Kouwenhoven (cp_ens_027) per Dutch naming convention. The name 'Gerrit' was first given to his older brother (c) b. 1795-05-15 who 'd. y.' (died young) per Cocheu; reused for this Gerrit b. 1797-09-23 — same Dutch reuse-of-name pattern documented in cp_ens_027's two-Abigails sequence (cp_ens_027 children #6 + #10) and cp_ens_026's two-Garrets sequence (cp_ens_026 children 1780 infant + 1783 = cp_ens_029). Long-lived bachelor: 89 years old at death 1887-01-05, never married, no children. The 1827 JP candidacy + inspector role (cp_famsou_008) is currently his only non-Cocheu attestation in the project dataset; other civic / occupational / property records pending future research.",
