      "sources": "PRIMARY (manuscript): cp_sou_016 Slave Manumissions, 1787-1844, Monmouth County, NJ — Manumission Book p.34 (cp_eve_087 James Chermo, PARTIAL) + p.44 (cp_eve_088 Sarah, COMPLETE — recorded 22 Oct 1840 by D. F. Ellis Clk). EXTERNAL ANCHORS: (none yet — pending FaG/FS/WikiTree search).; Cocheu NYG&BR 82:2 #509 (cp_sou_055); EDSM (per Chris-shared screenshot 2026-05-10)",
      "notes": "MINTED 2026-05-05 PM (this session) inline per Chris approval, on a 2-record manuscript evidence chain (cp_eve_087 1837 + cp_eve_088 1840 — both Township of Middletown, same manumitter signature, with Charles Conover as kin-signal across both deeds). Per project precedent, 2-record manuscript chain is sufficient for inline cp_ens mint without external biographical anchor (cf. cp_ens_039, cp_ens_040, cp_ens_042 — all minted same-session 5/5 on 2-record chains). External anchor (FaG/FS/WikiTree) pending future search. DISAMBIGUATION: cp_ens_043 Daniel D. Conover of Middletown is DISTINCT from cp_ens_042 Daniel G. Conover of Middletown (different middle initial; 9-12 year date gap; different witness networks: Charles Conover for D. Conover vs William Conover for G. Conover — both kin-signal Conovers but a different one each; both reside Township of Middletown). KIN-SIGNAL STRENGTHENS: Charles Conover served as deed witness on cp_eve_087 (1837) AND as Overseer of the Poor of Middletown on cp_eve_088 (1840). His repeated proximity to Daniel D.'s manumissions — and his civic-office progression — together suggest he is a relative actively involved in Daniel D.'s household-emancipation business. Track for further attestations and possible separate cp_ens mint if he himself appears as enslaver. CIVIC-FIGURE FINDING: Asbury Fountain trajectory parallels Charles Conover's — witness 1837 → Overseer 1840. Pattern of local Middletown civic ladder visible across project events.\n\n**ENRICHED 2026-05-10 (9 (none)-bucket attribution arc):** Per Cocheu 82:2 #509 (cp_sou_055) child (g): 'Daniel⁷ b. 1800-10-10, d. 1861-10-21, m. 1825-05-26 Mary Vanderveer b. 1806-02-21.' Younger brother of cp_ens_041 Garret Rezo. Both brothers died within ~1 day of each other Oct 1861 (Daniel D. 1861-10-21 per Cocheu vs Garret Rezo 1861-10-22 per FaG/gravestone) — striking coincidence; worth future Monmouth Co. newspaper search for joint obituary or shared illness/incident.",
