      "notable_records": "cp_eve_087 — 1837-04-15 manumission of James Chermo (cp_per_079), male, age ~36, in Township of Middletown; deed witnessed by Asbury Fountain + Charles Conover, acknowledged before Justice N. H. DiBrow same day; statutory examination block PARTIAL — recording date and stat-exam officials pending on subsequent page (post-p.34). cp_eve_088 — 1840-05-08 manumission of Sarah (cp_per_080), female, age 21-40 (statutory bracket — no specific age in deed), same Township; deed witnessed by Jonas Clark + Thomas S Bedle (both also serve as Justices of the Peace at the May 6 statutory examination); Overseers of the Poor of Middletown for stat exam: Asbury Fountain + Charles Conover (CIVIC-FIGURE PROGRESSION: same two men served as witnesses on cp_eve_087 1837 — career trajectory from witness → overseer in 3 years); recorded 1840-10-22 by D. F. Ellis Clk (Manumission Book p.44, COMPLETE).",
