      "notes": "Birth-date discrepancy: FS KF5G-DBD records birth 1784-08-24 with sourced christening 1784-10-31 Old Tennent (cannot post-date birth). FaG 14356812 reads birth 13 Dec 1783 (internally consistent with age-at-death 49y 4m 21d). FS-anchored 1784 held primary; FaG 1783 may reflect headstone wear or transcription. Resolve via headstone re-read if SSV/Tennent vestry records surface a baptismal cert. Headstone reads \"WICOFF CONOVER\" per FaG photo — informs name_variations.\n\n**ENRICHED 2026-05-10 (9 (none)-bucket attribution arc):** **cp_ens_055 Wyckoff is cp_ens_031 Brooklyn Jacob's NEPHEW.** Both grandsons of cp_fam_132 Peter Jacobse II. cp_ens_031 (b.1750) and William Benjamin (b.1752) are brothers — 2 years apart. Wyckoff's first name preserves paternal grandmother Catherine Wyckoff (= cp_fam_132's wife per Cocheu 71:2 #165, though her own maiden surname is more often rendered 'Schenck' — Wyckoff likely a kinship-network name from the broader Schenck-Wyckoff-Cowenhoven cluster). Cascade revised from initial Benjamin⁶ #443 hypothesis (incorrect) to cp_fam_132 path (correct per FS L638-M8C screenshot Chris-shared 2026-05-10).\n\n**COCHEU LINEAGE FLAG — 2026-05-12**: This row's grandparent walk via cp_fam_132 Peter Jacobse II is in dispute per Cocheu 82:1 #443. Cocheu's child list for #165 (PoM_003 Peter Jacobse II) has no William Benjamin. The 'Father cp_fam_229 William Benjamin' wiring stays MATCH-grade, but the GRANDPARENT (cp_fam_132 → cp_ens_009) lineage walk in the related_enslavers field is unreliable if Cocheu is correct: cp_fam_229's actual father per Cocheu = Benjamin⁶ #443 (UNMINTED), grandfather = William⁵ #146 (UNMINTED, Manalapin patriarch). Per Chris 2026-05-12: flag, defer; see cp_fam_229 notes for full discrepancy. Resolution path: NJA:36:55-56 will pull.\n\n[BIRTH-DATE RESOLUTION 2026-05-14]: birth_date corrected from 1784-08-24 (FS-displayed value, internally inconsistent with its own 1784-10-31 Old Tennent christening source) to 1783-12-13 per FaG memorial 14356812 gravestone inscription + age-at-death math (1833-05-03 minus 49 yrs 4 mo 21 da = 1783-12-12, within 1 day of gravestone-stated 13 Dec 1783; christening Oct 31 1784 is then a normal ~10.5 month post-birth event). Primary source = gravestone (FaG 14356812); corroborating = Old Tennent Scotch Church christening (FS V5FT-HP4). FS-displayed 1784-08-24 was an FS data error.",
