      "notes": "Minted 2026-05-06 from B-series Stage 3 follow-up to cp_ens_031 (Jacob Brooklyn) work, per To Do M3 ENSLAVER mint queue. TWO attestations across 9 years both in Freehold Township: 1825 witness (Hendrick Conover spelling on deed, cp_eve_070) + 1834 manumitter (Hendrick Covenhoven spelling, cp_eve_072). Birth-date window: must have been at least age-of-majority (21) by 1825 to witness legally → born 1804 or earlier; active manumitter in 1834 with no death record yet located → born ~1770-1804 most likely. KIN HYPOTHESIS: probable son or close kin of cp_ens_037 Jacob Couwenhoven Shoemaker (b. 1773), based on (a) Freehold co-residence, (b) 1825 witness role at Jacob's intimate household legal act (kin typically witness manumission deeds), (c) age-fit if son b. ~1795-1804. Alternative reading: brother of cp_ens_037 (b. ~1770s-1780s). External-source verification needed before promoting kin link from HYPOTHESIS to MATCH (1830/1840 Freehold census, FamilySearch/WikiTree, Schenck-Couwenhoven Cemetery FaG) — see Col R follow-ups. DISAMBIGUATION: distinct from Hendrick Hendrickson of Monmouth Co. (1743-1746 attestations on cp_eve_009 / cp_eve_015 / cp_eve_016 — different person, different surname, ~80 years earlier; in-law to cp_ens_009 Jacob Willemse via the Hendrickson kin network).\n\nUPDATE 2026-05-07: Dates closed at MATCH grade — b. 1805-12-14 Freehold; d. 1850-03-13 Matawan Twp (Freneau), age 44 yrs 2 mos 27 days, cause consumption (1850 Mortality Schedule). Three independent sources agree: WikiTree Conover-1256 + FS K41R-C43 + Find a Grave Memorial 36236819. Family network surfaced: parents Tunis Conover (1769-1844) & Martha Matje Vanderhoef Conover (1767-1848); spouse Ida Smith Conover; children Mary Jane 1832-1832, Tunis 1836-1861, William W. 1842-1913. Son-of-Jacob-Shoemaker hypothesis REJECTED — father is Tunis. Birth-date window in original Col U notes (~1770-1804) was wrong on the early end; Hendrick was 19, not 21+, when he witnessed cp_eve_070 in 1825 — minor age-of-majority anomaly to revisit if relevant. Father Tunis Conover (1769-1844) is an unminted cp_ens candidate (he held no enslaved persons in 1830 per the 'Tunis 7-0-0' household read in 5/6 PM2 ingest, but earlier holdings possible).\n\n**ENRICHED 2026-05-10 (9 (none)-bucket attribution arc):** **First Jan-sub_branch attribution this session.** 8-gen patrilineal walk (ties cp_ens_047 for project record): Wolphert → Gerrit → Jan cp_fam_008 → William Janse cp_fam_151 → cp_ens_012 William Jr. → Tunis cp_fam_248 → Hendrick cp_ens_048. Father Tunis had 2 marriages: 1st Hanna Van Brackle 1783 (2 sons, Hendrick's half-brothers Stephen + Roelof); 2nd Matje Vanderhoef 1788 (9 children including Hendrick, born 8 years into 2nd marriage). 4 children of cp_ens_048 (3 prior + Peter b.1839 newly identified from FS K41R-C43).",
      "raw_related_family": "",
      "raw_related_enslavers": "Parent|cp_fam_248 (Tunis);Parent|cp_ens_012 (William Jr. of Freehold — grandfather);Parent|cp_fam_151 (William Janse — great-grandfather);Mother|cp_fam_250 (Matje Vanderhoef);Stepmother|cp_fam_249 (Hanna Van Brackle — Tunis's 1st wife);Spouse|cp_fam_251 (Ida Smith);Half-siblings|cp_fam_252+253 (Stephen + Roelof, Tunis's 1st-marriage sons);Full-siblings|cp_fam_254-261 (8 from Tunis's 2nd marriage);Children|cp_fam_262-265 (4 children of cp_ens_048)",
      "notable_records": "1825-07-25 witness on Cuffee manumission by cp_ens_037 Jacob Couwenhoven Shoemaker (cp_eve_070, Monmouth Manumission Book p. 180; subject cp_per_064); 1834-07-29 manumitter of Silas Higgins (cp_eve_072, Monmouth Manumission Book p. 25; subject cp_per_066, age 21-40 per statutory certification — deed body p. 26 pending).",
